ety of Chest Pain Centers, Northside is committed to ensuring our patients have access to the highest levels of cardiac care available.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Responsibilities:&nbsp; The RN Cardiovascular Services Coordinator oversees the hospital processes&nbsp;for the Cardiac/Cardiovascular and Neuroscience&nbsp;service lines in order to maintain the hospital&#39;s Chest Pain and Stroke Certifications.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Oversees the collection, compilation, analysis and presentation of Cardiovascular/Cardiac Service and Neuro &nbsp;line&nbsp;data</LI>\n<LI>Supports and promotes the mission of the hospital and the CV/Cardiac Services and Neurosciences&nbsp;Departments</LI>\n<LI>Ensures reliability and validity of&nbsp; the abstracted CV/Cardiac and Neuro/Stroke data</LI>\n<LI>Facilitates timely submission of&nbsp;such data</LI>\n<LI>Maintains working knowledge relative to Conditions of Participation, JCAHO standards and assists Director to perform facility tracers to ensure ongoing compliance, document and&nbsp;evaluate performance improvement requirements to maintain Chest Pain and Stroke certifications</LI>\n<LI>Reports all opportunities to improve processes, policy/procedures</LI>\n<LI>Prepares and presents requested reports regarding Cardiovascular/Cardiac Measures and Neuro/Stroke Care Protocol</LI>\n<LI>Collaborates with physician leadership for presentation of outcome data at department meetings for the purpose of quality improvement</LI>\n<LI>Works collaboratively with Medical Staff coordinator to ensure ongoing medical staff peer review process through chart reviews and physician profiling activities within the defined facility structure</LI>\n<LI>Works collaboratively through daily rounds with enterprise wide departments to support ongoing compliance with Federal, State and regulatory statutes and standards and medical staff and hospital staff education skills requirements</LI>\n</UL>','<DIV>Required Job Qualifications include:</DIV>\n<