 of our Behavioral Health Services.&nbsp; Provide clinical guidance to our staff&nbsp;in all areas of Behavioral&nbsp;Health.&nbsp; &nbsp;The Largo Medical Center&nbsp; Behavioral Health Department consists of&nbsp; an intake and&nbsp;call center; newly remodeled 14 bed Voluntary unit, 16 bed involuntary unit&nbsp;(expanding to 31 beds), a 4 bed emergency unit and 6 bed medical hold unit, based at our Indian Rocks location.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The Manager of the Behavioral Health program demonstrates the skills, scientific judgment, and leadership in planning care blended with concierge level customer service experience for all patients admitted into the Largo Medical Center Behavioral Health programs.&nbsp; The manager is responsible and accountable for planning, directing and implementing care to the Behavioral Health guests in accordance with physician&#39;s orders, policies, procedures, established standards of customer service and administrative policies.&nbsp;&nbsp; The manager will demonstrate clinical knowledge in all areas within the Behavioral Health programming areas (with a base Cognitive Behavioral Therapy foundation).&nbsp; The manager will supervise assigned Behavioral Health&nbsp; staff, and directs clinical and medical flow of all patient care.&nbsp; The manager will serve as a resource person and role model for all personnel. He/she will identify problems or potential problems and communicate them to the Director.&nbsp; The manager is intricately involved in the selection of personnel, their education, discipline and level of expertise. The manager will be responsible for overseeing clinical care to Behavioral Health patients and to act as the liaison to all clinical disciplines invited to participate in patient care. The manager is responsible for all clinical operations, quality reporting, statistical reporting and regulatory requirements. The manager will promote continuity of hospital operations through the interpretation and enforcement of hospital and Behavioral Health policies and procedures.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Licensed RN</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>5&nbsp;years Psychiatric Nurse experience in an acute care facility.</P>\n<P>3 years Nursing leadership experience</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>AHA - BLS</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>Certified or eligible for certification as a Psychiatric Nurse</P>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11011/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=25558-5034','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11011/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=25558-5034',0,0,0,0,1311937742,1311939130),(60,9,5,'01384-5017','rn-cvicu-ft-days-01384-5017',NULL,'RN CVICU (FT Days)','United States-Florida-Brandon','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>Come and join our winning team as a RN in the Cardiovascular Intensive Care Unit.&nbsp;&nbsp;Brandon Regional Hospital&nbsp;has been named a Top 100 Hospital in America five times, and our Intensive Care Unit has been named a Top 100 ICU.&nbsp; We are committed to providing our patients and their families with compassionate care. For more than 30 years our busy, 407-bed acute care facility has been dedicated to quality and devoted to our community.&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Families trust us to meet their needs, knowing that they have access to these Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Spine Care Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care * Women&#39;s &amp; Children&#39;s Center</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Join our friendly community hospital with its close-knit staff of caring professionals located just south of Tampa and discover how we care.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<DIV>Required Job Qualifications include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN.</LI>\n<LI>Current BLS and ACLS certification&nbsp;through the American Heart Association.</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing