tient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Instructs and educates patients and families.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in patient discharge planning.</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>Edward White Hospital is committed to building a healthier community by providing high quality healthcare to our patients. Our 167-bed community hospital, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system, offers dozens of medically complex specialties, including accredited Chest Pain Center with PCI, Advanced Primary Stroke, Wound Care and Hyperbaric Medicine Centers.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Ideally located within minutes of downtown St. Petersburg, our family atmosphere provides a work environment just as unique as our skilled teamwhich is the reason why Edward White Hospital is currently ranked #1 in our entire HCA network for Employee Satisfaction!&nbsp; Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>.&nbsp; EOE</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of Physical Therapy.</LI>\n<LI>B.S. or M.S. in Physical Therapy.</LI>\n<LI>State licensure as a Physical Therapist.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider (American Heart Association).</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00367-1075','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00367-1075',0,0,0,0,1311937780,1311937780),(79,9,5,'00642-1513','food-and-nutrition-services-assistant-f-t-days-wkends-rotate-00642-1513',NULL,'Food and Nutrition Services Assistant (F T) Days Wkends Rotate','United States-Florida-Sun City Center','Food Services & Nutrition',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>The Food and Nutrition Services Worker performs a variety of tasks that facilitate the provision of food services and nutrition support to patients, employees and visitors. These duties include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Performs routine duties related to preparation and serving of food.</LI>\n<LI>Prepares food for cooking by washing, peeling, shredding, slicing, and mixing various food items.</LI>\n<LI>Operates dishwasher or assists with washing/sterilizing dishes, glassware, silverware, utensils, pots, pans, etc.</LI>\n<LI>Cleans kitchen work areas, collects and disposes of garbage.</LI>\n<LI>May assist with food stocking.</LI>\n<LI>Serves food in&nbsp; cafeteria for visitors and staff and in patients room following dietary, sanitary and safety guidelines.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Clears patients&#39; dirty trays and works in dish room when needed.</LI>\n<LI>Works on patient tray assembly line following menu directives for determining food items for each tray.</LI>\n<LI>Delivers food trays to patient areas.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Job qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>High school diploma or GED preferred</LI>\n<LI>6 months food service experience preferred, previous&nbsp; experience in hospital food services preferred.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00642-1513','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00642-1513',0,0,0,0,1311937782,1311937782),(80,9,5,'00643-2909','unit-secretary-surgical-ft-days-wkends-rotate-00643-2909',NULL,'Unit Secretary Surgical (FT) Days Wkends Rotate','United States-Florida-Brooksville','Admitting Registration Clerical & Scheduling',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>&nbsp;The Unit Secretary acts as the primary clerical resource for the unit.&nbsp; Position duties and responsibilities include:</P>\n<P><BR/>\n&nbsp;Performs a range of clerical duties that support the operations of the unit.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Acts as unit receptionist greeting and directing visitors.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Assists in the ordering, receipt and storage of supplies.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Assembles patient charts.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Answers unit telephone, transferring calls, determining when staff members should be paged and taking and forwarding messages.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Serves as an important link in the communication chain ensuring information is transmitted between nursing personnel, other hospital personnel,&nbsp; physicians, patients, family members and other guests.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Assists in entering patient information in Meditech computer system.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Maintains nursing station in neat and orderly manner.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Completes special projects for unit director, supervisors and charge nurses.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.&nbsp;<BR/>\n&nbsp;Orients and mentors new staff members.</P>','<P>Required Qualifications include:<BR/>\n&nbsp;High school degree or equivalent<BR/>\n&nbsp;Previous clerical experience.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Previous experience as a Unit Secretary in a hospital setting preferred.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Strong customer service skills.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Familiarity with medical terminology.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Computer literacy is preferred.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching and some lifting.</P>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-2909','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-2909',0,0,0,0,1311937785,1311937785),(81,9,5,'00309-3025','rn-progressive-care-unit-7a-7p-00309-3025',NULL,'RN Progressive Care Unit 7A 7P','United States-Florida-Bradenton','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>The PCU Registered Nurse reports directly to the unit Clinical Manager, and is responsible and accountable for the delivery of patient care through the utilization of the nursing process in accordance with&nbsp; physicians\' orders, established policies and procedures, established professional standards, and administrative hospital-wide policies.</P>\n<P>&nbsp;<BR/>\n</P>','<P>&nbsp;Graduate from an accredited school of nursing; BSN desired.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Current&nbsp;State Registered Nurse License.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Current American Heart Association Healthcare Provider or American Red Cross Professional Rescuer CPR card.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Current ACLS Provider card required within one year of hire date.<BR/>\n</P>\n<P>&nbsp;<BR/>\n<BR/>\n<BR/>\n</P>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-3025','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-3025',0,0,0,0,1311937787,1311937787),(82,9,5,'01384-4745','sterile-processing-tech-prn-01384-4745',NULL,'Sterile Processing Tech (PRN)','United States-Florida-Brandon','Nursing Support',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>The Sterile Processing Technician is responsible for the preparation of sterile supplies, instruments and equipment.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Job tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Prepares instruments and supplies through cleaning, packing, sterilizing and storing <SPAN>procedures</SPAN>.</LI>\n<LI>Understands principles of sterilization techniques and operates sterilization equipment.</LI>\n<LI>Assembles and sets up instruments trays for operating rooms.</LI>\n<LI>Assists in departmental cost containment efforts.</LI>\n<LI>Performs equipment distribution and routing cleaning and maintenance.</LI>\n</UL>'