tient care needs.</LI>\n<LI>Prioritizes patient care based on acuity level and available resources.</LI>\n<LI>Carries out physician orders.</LI>\n<LI>Assists physician during examination, treatment and procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Administers prescribed medications, changes dressings, cleans wounds, monitors vital signs.</LI>\n<LI>Serves as the primary coordinator of all disciplines for well coordinated patient care.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Instructs and educates patients and families.</LI>\n<LI>Assesses and coordinates patient&#39;s discharge planning needs with members of the healthcare team.</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider.</LI>\n<LI>ACLS&nbsp;and PALS&nbsp;Certification required upon hire.</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01377-991','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01377-991',0,0,0,0,1311937798,1311937798),(87,9,5,'01387-2327','rn-labor-and-delivery-full-time-nights-01387-2327',NULL,'RN Labor and Delivery Full Time Nights','United States-Florida-St Petersburg','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV><SPAN><EM><STRONG>Women&#39;s Services Department</STRONG></EM></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV>Founded in 1969, St. Petersburg General Hospital is a 219-bed facility located in the heart of South Pinellas County, Florida.&nbsp;&nbsp; St. Pete General is part of the HCA West Florida Division of Hospitals, a comprehensive network of hospitals, outpatient surgery and diagnostic imaging facilities, and a complete continuum of specialized healthcare programs that meet the healthcare needs of residents and businesses in West and Central Florida communities.&nbsp; Our parent company, HCA, is the nation&#39;s leading provider of healthcare services.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>SPGH is committed to ensuring our patients have access to the highest levels of care available.&nbsp; The Women&#39;s Center, featuring family centered care, focuses care on the patient and family as one unit. &nbsp;More than 1,500 babies&nbsp;are delivered at St. Petersburg General Hospital each year.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Number of Staff: 75</LI>\n<LI>32 Post Partum/GYN Beds for complete OB/GYN care; this also includes laboring patients and infants (80-90% of patients are Post Partum; may have some medical overflow)</LI>\n<LI>22 Nursery Beds (Level 1 Nursery)</LI>\n<LI>6 Labor/Delivery/Recovery Rooms (2 Operating Rooms)</LI>\n<LI>Skill Mix:&nbsp; RNs, LPNs, Obstetric/Surgical Technologists, and Certified Nursing Assistants</LI>\n<LI>Major Equipment Used: IV pumps, IVAC, Dinamaps, Dopplers, Accu-Check, Accu-Dose, Fetal Monitors, Radiant Warmers, Isolets</LI>\n<LI>Special Certifications Needed:&nbsp; BLS and NRP (ACLS preferred for L&amp;D)</LI>\n<LI>Special Competencies/Skills Needed:</LI>\n<LI>Post Partum/GYN:&nbsp; Prior PP/GYN experience required</LI>\n<LI>Nursery:&nbsp; MUST have prior nursery background; prefer Level 2 or Level 3 experience</LI>\n<LI>Labor and Delivery:&nbsp; Prior L&amp;D nursing experience required</LI>\n</UL>\n<UL>\n<LI>Schedules:&nbsp; 12-hour shifts (0645-1915, 1845-0715) plus 8 hours mandatory on-call for all staff;&nbsp; Full Time is considered 36 hours per week, including every other weekend; overtime available, but not mandatory; Self-scheduling is available</LI>\n<LI>Dress code:&nbsp; Professional scrubs (individual provides their own)</LI>\n<LI>Designated Charge Nurse</LI>\n<LI>Complete computerized charting (&quot;Electronic Health Record&quot;) for patient assessment and care documentation; Labor and Delivery utilizes &quot;OB trace view&quot; for fetal monitoring documentation</LI>\n<LI>Electronic medication administration record (eMAR) is used for the delivery of all medications provided to patients&nbsp;</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>At HCA West and Central Florida\'s 15 hospitals we\'re not just caregivers, we\'re devoted to caring. Located throughout Tampa, St. Petersburg, Sarasota and the greater Orlando area, we\'re on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients. As an integral part of the nation\'s largest healthcare system with more than 15,000 healthcare professionals on our team, we foster an environment where you will be supported, valued and encouraged to grow.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to www.MoreCareerChoices.com.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current Florida licensure as an RN.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS and ACLS&nbsp;Healthcare Provider certifications&nbsp;through the American Heart Association and NRP.</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI><EM><STRONG>Minimum of 1 year experience required.</STRONG></EM></LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01387-2327','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01387-2327',0,0,0,0,1311937800,1311939883),(88,9,5,'01371-2784','nursing-admin-supervisor-01371-2784',NULL,'Nursing Admin Supervisor','United States-Florida-Port Charlotte','Nursing Mgmt & Admin',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV><SPAN>Utilize your strong organizational and leadership skills to&nbsp;guide hospital wide nursing during the&nbsp;day shift.&nbsp;&nbsp;At Fawcett Medical Center you will find a progessive, innovative staff and leadership team dedicated to Quality and Patient Satisfaction.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We are&nbsp;on the path toward Magnet status. This is a 12 hour shift day position 7a-7p with every other weekend.&nbsp;</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West Florida we are on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients; their families and the communities we serve.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The Administrative Supervisor will supervise and coordinate the operational and personnel activities throughout the facility.&nbsp; The Supervisor will act as an administrative liaison for all departments for the defined shift for which he/she is responsible.&nbsp; The&nbsp;Supervisor recognizes that each patient is an individual to be treated with dignity and respect, and is also committed to being responsive to the needs of the patient&#39;s family or significant other.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;The Supervisor-Nursing/Administration combines the knowledge bases of nursing and management to make decisions and or recommendation relative to:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The delivery of responsive quality patient care based on the nursing process.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The assessment of unit staffing needs and the appropriate placement of nursing personnel.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The serving as a resource person and role model for all personnel.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The communication of identified problem situations to the Director of Nursing Services.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To promote continuity of hospital operations through the interpretation and enforcement of hospital policies and procedures.</DIV>','Required Job Qualifications include:<BR/>\n&nbsp;Current licensure as an RN.<BR/>\n&nbsp; Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Nursing preferred.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Minimum of 2 years of clinical nursing experience.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Basic knowledge of main functional areas within the Hospital.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Previous managerial experience in clinical nursing within hospital environment required.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment, strong communication skills and leadership abilities.<BR/>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01371-2784','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01371-2784',0,0,0,0,1311937802,1311937802),(89,9,5,'01323-1841','rn-or-prn-01323-1841',NULL,'RN OR PRN','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P>The Operating Room RN provides nursing care in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</P><UL><LI>Assesses, plans and evaluates the nursing care needs of the patient before, during and after a surgical procedure. </LI><LI>Provides nursing care to the patient undergoing surgical procedures. </LI><LI>Provides comfort and support for pre-operative patients. </LI><LI>Participates in the care of patients receiving conscious sedation. </LI><LI>Carries out physician orders. </LI><LI>Administers prescribed medications, applies dressings, monitors vital signs. </LI><LI>Assists physician during procedures. </LI><LI>Maintains aseptic techniques and actively monitors situations which could lead to breaches in aseptic technique. </LI><LI>Coordinates the operating room with respect to sterility, cleanliness, availability of functioning equipment and supplies.&nbsp; </LI><LI>Ensures the proper handling of specimens. </LI><LI>Serves as the primary coordinator of all disciplines for well coordinated patient care. </LI><LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp; </LI><LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care. </LI><LI>Orients and mentors new staff members. </LI><LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI></UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P><UL><LI>Current licensure as an RN. </LI><LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider. </LI><LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing. </LI><LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills. </LI><LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment. </LI><LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs. </LI></UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-1841','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-1841',0,0,0,0,1311937805,1311937805),(9