mily of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>.&nbsp; EOE</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of a college of Pharmacy accredited by the American Council on Pharmacy Education.</LI>\n<LI>BS or Pharm.D degree&#39; Residency preferred.</LI>\n<LI>State licensure as a Pharmacist.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01371-2762','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01371-2762',0,0,0,0,1311937807,1311937807),(91,9,5,'00146-2674','clinical-educator-rn-registered-nurse-00146-2674',NULL,'Clinical Educator RN Registered Nurse','United States-Florida-New Port Richey','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV>Join us on our Journey to Medical Center of Trinity opening Fall 2011!</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>COMMUNITY HOSPITAL OF NEW PORT RICHEY</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Community Hospital of New Port Richey strives to provide compassionate care to the people it serves with innovation, professionalism and the highest standards of quality. As part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system, we are expanding with another state-of-the-art hospital on 50 acres located in the Trinity area. Medical Center of Trinity will complement our existing 389-bed hospital and these Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center * Joint Care Center * Acute Myocardial Infarction (AMI) * Interventional Cardiac Cath Lab * Spine Care Center * Psychiatric Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care * The Birthplace</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Join us as we grow and continue to offer healthcare professionals an encouraging environment where quality is rewarded.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West and Central Florida&#39;s 15 hospitals we&#39;re not just caregivers, we&#39;re devoted to caring. Located throughout Tampa, St. Petersburg, Sarasota and the greater Orlando area, we&#39;re on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients. As an integral part of the nation&#39;s largest healthcare system with more than 15,000 healthcare professionals on our team, we foster an environment where you will be supported, valued and encouraged to grow.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The RN Clinical Educator is responsible for assessing, planning, implementing and evaluating the educational activities for hospital staff.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities of this position include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Collaborates with hospital managers and staff to assess the learning needs and competency gaps.</LI>\n<LI>Develops, implements and evaluates educational plans/programs.</LI>\n<LI>Facilitates a variety of learning experiences using a range of instructional methods.</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates strong knowledge of healthcare standards and regulations in order to meet related training needs.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in the organization&#39;s compliance with mandatory training requirements.</LI>\n<LI>Utilizes methods, measurements and tools to evaluate achievement of learning goals.</LI>\n<LI>Serves as a consultant for staff in areas of program development, clinical practice and professional development.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in the coordination and continuity of orientation programs.</LI>\n<LI>Serves as an active member of committees focused on such areas as safety, infection control and staff competency.</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates strong knowledge of standards and regulations related to staff development and patient education.</LI>\n<LI>Researches and recommends the purchase of educational materials and equipment.</LI>\n<LI>Coordinates and/or collaborates with external learning institutions as they utilize the hospital as a clinical teaching site.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications Include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current Florida&nbsp;licensure as an RN.</LI>\n<LI>Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Nursing required; Master&#39;s Degree in Nursing preferred.</LI>\n<LI>Minimum 2 years of clinical ICU nursing experience.</LI>\n<LI>Previous instruction experience required.</LI>\n<LI>Competency in utilizing computer programs for developing instructional materials, tracking related data and communicating information.</LI>\n<LI>BLS Healthcare Provider, ACLS Healthcare Provider, Instructor preferred.</LI>\n<LI>Able to speak, read and understand English fluently.</LI>\n<LI>Excellent communicator with engaging and effective presentation abilities.</LI>\n<LI>Requires critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision\n\n <UL>\n<LI>Knowledge of standards and regulations related to staff development and patient education.</LI>\n<LI>Researches and recommends the purchase of educational materials and equipment.</LI>\n<LI>Coordinates and/or collaborates with external learning institutions as they utilize the hospital as a clinical teaching site.</LI>\n</UL>\n</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00146-2674','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00146-2674',0,0,0,0,1311937809,1311939893),(92,9,5,'01387-2340','pharmacist-clinical-coordinator-hospital-experience-01387-2340',NULL,'Pharmacist Clinical Coordinator Hospital experience','United States-Florida-St Petersburg','Supervisors Team Leaders & Coordinators',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>St. Petersburg General Hospital attracts highly skilled medical professionals with a passion for care.