stant Director Requires Hospital Pharmacy Experience Join our Dynamic Pharmacy Team','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Directors & Managers',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>&nbsp;\n\n<DIV><STRONG>Osceola Regional Medical Center</STRONG>, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system, has a proud tradition of providing excellent patient care in the Kissimmee area. Our 257-bed hospital offers the county&#39;s only Level II Neonatal and Open Heart programs and empowers its employees to strive for a higher standard of care. Several Centers of Excellence also highlight our clinical expertise:</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center with PCI * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Orthopedics &amp; Spine Care Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center. Experience our enhanced services and advanced technologies by joining a team of leading professionals. Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals.&nbsp; EOE</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV><I><STRONG>POSITION SUMMARY</STRONG></I>: Assists the&nbsp;Pharmacy Director in overseeing the pharmacy to ensure that patients&#39; pharmaceutical needs are effectively met.&nbsp; Assist the director in establishing policies, procedures, standards and objectives for provision of services and coordinates with other departments to provide maximum level of services to patient/families and hospital staff.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\nDuties include: Participates in Medication Management processes through collaborative teamwork, interaction, and sharing with administration, physicians, nurses, department managers, and other team members.&nbsp; Responsible for contributing to safe medication management where Pharmacy contributes to the process: including: selection, procurement, storage, ordering, transcribing, preparing, dispensing and monitoring medications.&nbsp;&nbsp;Assists in&nbsp;hiring process and makes recommendations to management and staff for making the department successful.&nbsp;Assists in setting goals&nbsp;for P &amp; T Committee and make recommendations in a collaborative team approach to accomplish organizations goals. Views responsibilities and functions as running a business with goal of improving patient&#39;s outcomes. Includes a global view of operations related to supplies, materials, staff, equipment and other support tools needed for the success of the &quot; whole team&quot; and the organization.&nbsp; Participation in the Quality Improvement process is also expected&nbsp;','<P>Education: Minimum of Bachelors degree of Pharmacy from an accredited&nbsp;school of Pharmacy&nbsp;required; PharmD preferred.&nbsp;State&nbsp;of Florida Pharmacist&nbsp; License required; Consultant License preferred.</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>Experience: 3-5 years hospital Pharmacy experience.&nbsp; Hospital Management or&nbsp;Supervisory experience preferred.&nbsp; Additional business, clinical experience or background a plus..&nbsp;</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>Skills: Good skills in team building, human relations, organizational, critical thinking and communication skills, in a detail-oriented, multi-tasks, customer- focused organizational manner. Manages stress appropriately and can make decisions under pressure.&nbsp; Handle multiple priorities, Self directed and motivated to be a team organizer and leader.&nbsp; Willingness and skills to direct activities through completion of planned projects.&nbsp; Computer skills related to Word, Excel; Meditech experience a plus.&nbsp;</P>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11011/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3759','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11011/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3759',0,0,0,0,1311937828,1311939273),(100,9,5,'00642-844','dietary-tech-prn-00642-844',NULL,'Dietary Tech PRN','United States-Florida-Sun City Center','Environmental Services',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>The Diet&nbsp;Tech performs essential duties associated with the processing of menus and diet orders, patient information related to meal patterns, preference