.&nbsp;Demonstrates responsibility techniques.</DIV>\n<DIV>Problem Solving</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp; a.&nbsp;Initiates corrective action in system changes, performance.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp; b.&nbsp;Verbalizes an awareness of problem solving dynamics and involves others in the problem solving activities of the Department.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp; c.&nbsp;&nbsp;Resolves conflict situations utilizing the problem solving approach.<BR/>\n<BR/>\n</DIV>','<DIV>1.&nbsp;Education</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a.&nbsp;Graduate of a school of Physical, Occupational or Speech&nbsp;Therapy approved by the American Physical Therapy Association or school of Occupational Therapy approved by the American Occupational Therapy Association or Speech Language Pathology Association.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b.&nbsp;BA/BS Degree required, Master&#39;s preferred.</DIV>\n<DIV>2.&nbsp;Licensure</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a.&nbsp;Current Florida Physical Therapist, Occupational Therapist or Speech&nbsp;Therapist&nbsp;License</DIV>\n<DIV>3.&nbsp;Experience</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a.&nbsp;Minimum of 3-5 years experience as a Physical, Occupational or Speech&nbsp;Therapist.<BR/>\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b.&nbsp;Minimum of 1-2 years experience in a Supervisory/Director position overseeing Inpatient Rehab Unit.</DIV>\n<DIV>4.&nbsp;Knowledge/Ability</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a.&nbsp;Rehabilitation Services principles, practices and equipment</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b.&nbsp;Physical, emotional and cognitive aspects of care for infants, pediatrics, teenagers, adults and geriatrics</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c.&nbsp;Budgeting, financial process, FTE control</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; d.&nbsp;Personnel management</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; e.&nbsp;Problem Solving techniques</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; f.&nbsp;Ability to develop and implement policies/procedures.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; g.&nbsp;Ability to cope/manage conflict, crises, and stress</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; h.&nbsp;Ability to communicate verbally and in writing</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Physical requirements include, but not limited to:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Medium Work: Lifting 50 lbs Maximum with frequent lifting and/or carrying of objects weighing up to 25 lbs.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01371-2613','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01371-2613',0,0,0,0,1311937849,1311937849),(109,9,5,'25558-5088','recreational-therapist-nctrc-required-25558-5088',NULL,'Recreational Therapist NCTRC Required','United States-Florida-Largo','Behavioral & Social Work',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>Experience a higher degree of patient care at Largo Medical Center, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system. Our 456-bed acute care hospital is located on two campuses-in mid-Pinellas County on the West Coast of Florida, providing medical care for the residents of Largo, and the nearby cities of Clearwater, Seminole, St. Petersburg and the Gulf Beach communities. We are the only area hospital with all private patient rooms.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>We offer career growth, top technologies, and these Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center with PCI *Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Spine &amp; Neuro Center * Breast Center * Cancer Care</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>See how we care and you will experience a supportive environment, great people and a wide array of unique services.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;The Recreational Therapist is responsible for the following:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Demonstrates concern and empathy to patients.&nbsp; Demonstrates responsibility and accountability in providing therapeutic care.&nbsp; Provides therapeutic care in 