ering exceptional care for the patients we serve.&nbsp; Our Surgical Nursing Department, &quot;6 West&quot;, is a 22-bed unit, opened in January 2007 and dedicated to the care of post-op surgical patients.&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV><I>At SPGH, we utilize complete computerized charting (&quot;Electronic Hospital Record&quot;) for our patient assessment and care documentation.&nbsp; We also utilize eMAR, our electronic medication administration record for the delivery of all medications provided to our patients, which has significantly reduced errors associated when administering medications.&nbsp;</I>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Number of Staff: 23 full time employees</LI>\n<LI>Skill Mix:&nbsp; RN, LPN, Unit Secretary, CNA, Student Nurse</LI>\n<LI>Major Equipment Used:&nbsp; IV pumps, IVAC, Dinamaps, Dopplers, Lifting Equipment, Accu-Check, Accu-Dose, Crash Cart</LI>\n<LI>Special Certifications Needed:&nbsp; BLS</LI>\n<LI>Schedules:&nbsp; 12-hour shifts (0645-1915, 1845-0715);&nbsp; Full Time is considered 36 hours per week, including every other weekend; overtime available, but not mandatory; Self-scheduling is available</LI>\n<LI>Dress code:&nbsp; Professional scrubs (individual provides their own)</LI>\n<LI>Designated Charge Nurse who DOES NOT take an assignment on the day shift</LI>\n<LI>Lifting equipment available:&nbsp; Opera, Encore, Maxislides, Z-slides</LI>\n<LI>Teaching hospital with a full complement of interns and family practice residents who are able and willing to assist with ensuring patients get what they need.&nbsp;</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>More options.&nbsp; More opportunities.&nbsp; More places for you to express your passion for quality and expand your potential for success.&nbsp; With 16 hospitals to choose from, there is no limit to what you can do at HCA West Florida. Join us at St. Petersburg General Hospital, centrally located in the heart of St. Petersburg, for the next exciting step in your career!</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbs