es therapeutic modalities, and performs other activities according to the plan of care established by the licensed physical therapist and as permitted by the State Board of Physical Therapy Examiners.</LI>\n<LI>Assists the physical therapist during patient testing, evaluations and complex procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Instructs patients on segments of the plan of care including proper use of wheelchairs, crutches, canes braces and prosthetic appliances and devices.</LI>\n<LI>Documents in computerized documentation system.&nbsp; Prepares correspondence and reports related to plan of care and patient progress.</LI>\n<LI>Directs activities of technicians, students, and volunteers as assigned.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in performance improvement and program development as assigned, to include but not limited to: data gathering, chart reviews, compilation of data into a report.</LI>\n<LI>Performs duties with full understanding of&nbsp; related age specific factors.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>Brandon Regional Hospital is committed to providing our patients and their families with compassionate care. For more than 30 years our busy, 407-bed acute care facility has been dedicated to quality and devoted to our community. We have been named a Top 100 Hospital in America five times, and our Intensive Care Unit has been named a Top 100 ICU.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Families trust us to meet their needs, knowing that they have access to these Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Spine Care Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care * Women&#39;s &amp; Children&#39;s Center</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Join our friendly community hospital with its close-knit staff of caring professionals located just south of Tampa and discover how we care.&nbsp; Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>. EOE</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited Physical Therapy Assistant program</LI>\n<LI>State licensure as a Physical Therapy Assistant.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking and judgment particularly in determining when to inform the therapist of a significant change in the patients condition.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider (American Heart Association).</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting patients and /or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-5050','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-5050',0,0,0,0,1311937908,1311937908),(141,9,5,'01323-3121','rn-ekg-cv-prn-01323-3121',NULL,'RN EKG CV (PRN)','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>RN responsible to perform diagnostic cardiovascular studies to the cardiac patient in both the outpatient and inpatient setting.&nbsp; Provides nursing care by assessing the patient pre-procedure and assists the Cardiologist in the various diagnostic cardiac testing.&nbsp; Examples:&nbsp; Trans-Esophageal Echocardiograms (TEE\'s) Exercise Stress Testing, Nuclear Stress Testing, Stress Echo\'s with or without the use of contrast, Dobutamine Stress tests and Tilt Table Tests.&nbsp;&nbsp; Administers conscious sedation and other prescribed medication or pharmacological agents during and post cardiac testing.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Cardiology Nurse accepts rotating weekends and holiday on call responsibilities for the Stress Lab.</DIV>','<UL>\n<LI>Current FL RN License</LI>\n<LI>Current BLS and ACLS certifications thru American Heart Association</LI>\n<LI>Experience in Arrahythmia analysis and cardiac anatomy</LI>\n<LI>Stress Lab experience preferred&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3121','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3121',0,0,0,0,1311937911,1311937911),(142,9,5,'01384-4631','rn-nicu-prn-01384-4631',NULL,'RN NICU (PRN)','United States-Florida-Brandon','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV>Brandon Regional Hospital is committed to providing our patients and their families with compassionate care. For more than 30 years our busy, 407-bed acute care facility has been dedicated to quality and devoted to our community. We have been named a Top 100 Hospital in America five times, and our Intensive Care Unit has been named a Top 100 ICU.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Families trust us to meet their needs, knowing that they have access to these Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Spine Care Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care * Women&#39;s &amp; Children&#39;s Center</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Join our friendly community hospital with its close-knit staff of caring professionals located just south of Tampa and discover how we care.</DIV>\n&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The&nbsp;RN in the NICU provides direct nursing care in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Cares for infants transitioning to extra uterine life.</LI>\n<LI>Assesses, plans and evaluates patient care needs.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Carries out physician orders.</LI>\n<LI>Provides nutritional assessment and care to the infant.</LI>\n<LI>Administers prescribed medications, changes dressings, monitors vital signs.</LI>\n<LI>Assists physician during examination, treatment and procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Serves as the primary coordinator of all disciplines for well coordinated patient care.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Instructs and educates patients and families.</LI>\n<LI>Assesses and coordinates patient&#39;s discharge planning needs with members of the healthcare team.</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<DIV>Required Job Qualifications include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN.</LI>\n<LI>Current BLS certification through the American Heart Assocation required.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Current NRP and PALS required.</LI>\n<LI>Previous experience in a Level 3 NICU required.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West and Central Florida&#39;s 15 hospitals we&#39;re not just caregivers, we&#39;re devoted to caring. Located throughout Tampa, St. Petersburg, Sarasota and the greater Orlando area, we&#39;re on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients. As an integral part of the nation&#39;s largest healthcare system with more than 15,000 healthcare professionals on our team, we foster an environment where you will be supported, valued and encouraged to grow.<BR/>\n<BR/>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to www.MoreCareerChoices.com.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The Comprehensive Hospital System Serving West &amp; Central Florida</DIV>\n<DIV>Blake Medical Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Brandon Regional Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Central Florida Regional Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Community Hospital of New Port Richey</DIV>\n<DIV>Doctors Hospital of Sarasota</DIV>\n<DIV>Edward White Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Englewood Community Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Fawcett Memorial Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Largo Medical Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Northside Hospital &amp; Tampa Bay Heart Institute</DIV>\n<DIV>Oak Hill Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Osceola Regional Medical Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point</DIV>\n<DIV>South Bay Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>St. Petersburg General Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>EOE</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-4631','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-4631',0,0,0,0,1311937914,1311937914),(143,9,5,'01323-2302','rn-cdu-prn-01323-2302',NULL,'RN CDU (PRN)','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<SPAN>Assesses patient/family health problems and resources; takes a leadership role in the development, implementation and outcomes evaluation of a plan for nursing care provided by the nursing team. Provides technical nursing care and interventions to designated patient populations. This position requires providing service to one or more age populations including young adult through geriatric patient population in a manner that demonstrates an understanding of the functional/developmental age of the individual served.</SPAN><BR/>\n</SPAN>','<SPAN>Graduate of an accredited RN School of Nursing; one year recent acute care experience required; one year recent critical care/PCU experience preferred; excellent written and verbal communication skills; Bilingual (English/Spanish) preferred.<BR/>\n<BR/>\nCurrent Florida RN license. Current BLS and ACLS thru American Heart Association required.&nbsp; CCRN preferred.</SPAN></SPAN>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-2302','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-2302',0,0,0,0,1311937916,1311937916),(144,9,5,'01323-3519','charge-rn-labor-delivery-nights-01323-3519',NULL,'Charge RN Labor Delivery Nights','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>The Charge Nurse supervises nursing service activities in assigned nursing unit for the duration of the assigned shift or in the absence of nursing management.&nbsp; The task and responsibilities of this position include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Participates actively in the planning and distribution of patient assignments.</LI>\n<LI>Evaluates the effectiveness of care and addresses any issues that affect the desired patient outcomes.</LI>\n<LI>Supports nursing staff in communication with physicians to include accepting doctors&#39; orders and communicating patient condition.</LI>\n<LI>Facilitates the process of reporting patient status to the following shift of nursing personnel.</LI>\n<LI>Manages the nursing care of assigned patients in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Assesses plans and evaluates patient care needs.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Assesses and coordinates patient&#39;s discharge planning needs with members of the healthcare team. .</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n</UL>','<UL>\n<LI>Current FL RN license</LI>\n<LI>Current BLS and NRP thru American Heart Association</LI>\n<LI>Previous experience in L&amp;D and supervisory/charge position.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3519','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3519',0,0,0,0,1311937917,1311937917),(145,9,5,'00309-3032','pharmacist-registered-hospital-experience-join-our-dynamic-pharmacy-team-00309-3032',NULL,'Pharmacist (Registered) Hospital Experience Join our Dynamic Pharmacy Team ','United States-Florida-Bradenton','Pharmacy & Pharmacy Tech',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>Experience a higher standard of care at Blake Medical Center located in Bradenton, Florida just minutes from the Gulf Coast beaches. Our 383-bed acute care facility has been named a nine-time &quot;100 Top Hospital&quot; and a &quot;100 Top Cardiovascular Hospital&quot; by Thompson Reuters, formerly known as Solucient. With a strong commitment to quality care, advanced technology and professional development we make sure our employees are well cared for too.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Along with dozens of specialties and accredited treatment programs, our award-winning hospital also features several Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Chest Pain Center with PCI * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care * Joint Care * Spine Care Center</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Develop you career by joining our 13-acre tropical campus ideally situated less than one hour south of Tampa.&nbsp; Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. <A HREF=\"http://www.EOE\">EOE</A></DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Following physicians&#39; orders, the Pharmacist compounds and dispenses medications and other pharmaceuticals.&nbsp; Position tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Maintains strong knowledge of hospital policies and government regulations and dispenses accordingly.</LI>\n<LI>Consults with physicians and nursing staff regarding patient reactions, errors and complaints.</LI>\n<LI>Determines and consults on possible drug interactions.</LI>\n<LI>Assists in the supervision and training of pharmacy technician personnel.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in Drug Utilization Review.</LI>\n<LI>Assists with quality improvement initiatives, inventory and ordering of pharmaceuticals.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Utilizes knowledge of age specific needs of patient in performance of duties and responsibilities.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of a college of Pharmacy accredited by the American Council on Pharmacy Education.</LI>\n<LI>BS or Pharm.D degree.</LI>\n<LI>State of Florida&nbsp;licensure as a Pharmacist.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11014/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-3032','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11014/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-3032',0,0,0,0,1311937919,1311938668),(146,9,5,'00311-3222','rn-registered-nurse-surgical-services-or-days-00311-3222',NULL,'RN Registered Nurse Surgical Services OR Days','United States-Florida-Hudson','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>Enjoy Monday through Friday in our OR!&nbsp; Perioperative training available for the motivated candidate!</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>REGIONAL MEDICAL CENTER BAYONET POINT</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Experience our commitment to compassion and care at Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system. Our 290-bed facility boasts many awards and accolades, particularly for our nationally acclaimed Heart Institute. Our dedication to patients is reflected in the ongoing recognition of our Centers of Excellence, which include:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Advanced Certification for Heart Failure * Chest Pain Center with PCI * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Located on Florida&#39;s West Coast, our suburban location just 45 minutes from Tampa offers a friendly work environment, award winning staff and the opportunity to strengthen your career.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point is in the process of application for a Level II trauma designation.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West and Central Florida&#39;s 15 hospitals we&#39;re not just caregivers, we&#39;re devoted to caring. Located throughout Tampa, St. Petersburg, Sarasota and the greater Orlando area, we&#39;re on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients. As an integral part of the nation&#39;s largest healthcare system with more than 15,000 healthcare professionals on our team, we foster an environment where you will be supported, valued and encouraged to grow.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The Operating Room RN provides nursing care in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Assesses, plans and evaluates the nursing care needs of the patient before, during and after a surgical procedure.</LI>\n<LI>Provides nursing care to the patient undergoing surgical procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Provides comfort and support for pre-operative patients.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in the care of patients receiving conscious sedation.</LI>\n<LI>Carries out physician orders.</LI>\n<LI>Administers prescribed medications, applies dressings, monitors vital signs.</LI>\n<LI>Assists physician during procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Maintains aseptic techniques and actively monitors situations which could lead to breaches in aseptic technique.</LI>\n<LI>Coordinates the operating room with respect to sterility, cleanliness, availability of functioning equipment and supplies.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Ensures the proper handling of specimens.</LI>\n<LI>Serves as the primary coordinator of all disciplines for well coordinated patient care.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider.</LI>\n<LI>CNOR Certification preferred.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-3222','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-3222',0,0,0,0,1311937921,1311939869),(147,9,5,'00144-1844','certified-nursing-asst-prn-days-nights-00144-1844',NULL,'Certified Nursing Asst (PRN) Days Nights','United States-Florida-Largo','Nursing Support',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>Responsible for patient care under the direct supervision of a Registered Nurse.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>PERFORMANCE OUTCOMES:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV><B>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B> <B>Individual Leadership/Practices Professionalism:</B> Performs, participates, implements and evaluates personal performance, opportunities for personal growth and ability to change.<B>&nbsp;</B></DIV>\n<DIV><B>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B> <B>Customer Service:</B> Demonstrates customer service skills with both internal and external customers.<B>&nbsp;</B></DIV>\n<DIV><B>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B> <B>Hospital/Departmental Policies and Procedures:</B> Knowledgeable of all policies and procedures that affect the outcomes of patient care, employee rights and responsibilities.</DIV>\n<DIV><B>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B> <B>Performance Improvement:</B> Performs, participates, implements and evaluates performance improvement activities within the departmental level.</DIV>\n<DIV><B>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B> <B>Financial Accountability:</B> Identifies opportunities for waste reduction and department efficiency.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV><B>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B> <B>Communication:&nbsp;</B> Works as a team member through interaction, assistance and demonstration.</DIV>\n<DIV><B>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B> <B>Job Specific:</B> Performs functions as assigned to position.</DIV>\n</DIV>','<DIV>\n<DIV><STRONG>EDUCATION REQUIRED AND/OR PREFERRED:</STRONG> (list required and preferred separately)</DIV>\n<DIV>High School graduate or GED required</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV><STRONG>EXPERIENCE REQUIRED OR PREFERRED:&nbsp;</STRONG></DIV>\n<DIV>CNA Required.</DIV>\n<DIV>One year Patient care experience required.</DIV>\n<DIV><STRONG>SKILLS, KNOWLEDGE, AND ABILITIES:</STRONG></DIV>\n<DIV>Demonstrated skills in organization, verbal and written communications, customer service, math, analysis, reading, following instruction, basic computer usage.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV><STRONG>LICENSURE/CERTIFICATION:</STRONG> (list required and preferred separately)</DIV>\n<DIV>BLS.</DIV>\n</DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-1844','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-1844',0,0,0,0,1311937923,1311937923),(148,9,5,'00327-2515','rn-ortho-neuro-surgical-unit-00327-2515',NULL,'RN Ortho Neuro Surgical Unit','United States-Florida-Sanford','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>Assess patient/family health problems and resources; takes a leadership role in the development implementation and outcomes evaluation of a plan for nursing care provided by the nursing team.&nbsp; Provides technical nursing care primarily with Surgical Patients-Neurosurgey, Orthopedics, and General Surgery and Medical neuro patients.</SPAN></P>','<UL CLASS=\"noindent\">\n<LI>Current FL RN License</LI>\n<LI>Current BLS and ACLS thru American Heart Association</LI>\n<LI>Basic EKG Interpretation</LI>\n<LI>One year general Medical / Surgical experience int he hospital setting</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-2515','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-2515',0,0,0,0,1311937925,1311937925),(149,9,5,'00327-2604','rn-surg-svcs-or-00327-2604',NULL,'RN Surg Svcs OR','United States-Florida-Sanford','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>The Operating Room RN provides nursing care in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Assesses, plans and evaluates the nursing care needs of the patient before, during and after a surgical procedure.</LI>\n<LI>Provides nursing care to the patient undergoing surgical procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Provides comfort and support for pre-operative patients.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in the care of patients receiving conscious sedation.</LI>\n<LI>Assists physician during procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Coordinates the operating room with respect to sterility, cleanliness, availability of functioning equipment and supplies.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Ensures the proper handling of specimens.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current FL RN License.</LI>\n<LI>Current&nbsp;BLS&nbsp;certification thru&nbsp;American Heart Association&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Previous OR experience required</LI>\n<LI>Be able to take calls</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-2604','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-2604',0,0,0,0,1311937927,1311937927),(150,9,5,'01323-3676','rn-critical-care-nights-01323-3676',NULL,'RN Critical Care Nights','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>The ICU/CCU RN manages the nursing care of critically ill patients in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; Assesses patient/family health problems and resources; takes a leadership role in the development, implementation and outcomes evaluation of a plan for nursing care provided by the nursing team.&nbsp; Provides technical nursing care and interventions to designated patient populations.&nbsp; This position requires providing service to one or more age populations including young adult through geriatric patient population in a manner that demonstrates an understanding of the functional/developmental age of the individual served.&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current FL RN License</LI>\n<LI>Current BLS and ACLS certifications thru American Heart Association</LI>\n<LI>Previous experience as ICU RN in hospital setting is a plus</LI>\n<LI>CCRN preferred</LI>\n</UL>\n</DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3676','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3676',0,0,0,0,1311937929,1311937929),(151,9,5,'01323-2598a','social-worker-bsw-prn-01323-2598a',NULL,'Social Worker BSW (PRN)','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Behavioral & Social Work',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>Position Responsibilities:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Demonstrates uncompromising ethics and personal integrity by adhering to the highest standards of ethical behavioral.</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates dignity and respect by not perpetrating rumors that adversely affect customer relations and work place moral.&nbsp; Shares information regarding concerns only with appropriate people.</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates team spirit and initiative to improve the quality of the decision-making process.</LI>\n<LI>Takes initiative to assist other staff in completion of their assignments, as needed.</LI>\n<LI>Accepts reassignment and additional duties, when necessary, in a flexible and positive manner.</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates the knowledge and skills necessary to provide care, based on physical, psycho/social, educational, safety and related criteria, appropriate to the age of patients served in his/her assigned service area.</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates competency in interpretation of patient\'s self-reported behavior related to age of the patient.</LI>\n<LI>Understands the cognitive, physiologic, and psychological growth and maturational development of the patient as it relates to his/her age.</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates ability to access age specific data.</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates the ability to integrate age specific factors into the plan of care and involves the patient and family in the care plan process as appropriate to age.&nbsp; (Age of Patient Population Served: Adult to Geriatric).</LI>\n<LI>Implements discharge planning processes.</LI>\n<LI>Effectively interviews patient and family members, and other support system personnel, to access the bio-psycho-social status of the patient scheduled for discharge.&nbsp; Formulates a discharge plan in a timely manner that matches patient with services best able to meet the patient\'s needs.&nbsp; Provides ongoing assessment during hospitalization to ensure appropriate referrals based on status at the time of discharge.</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates the ability to effectively communicate the recommendations of the treatment team to the patient, the patient\'s family, caregivers and other support systems.</LI>\n<LI>Effectively assesses the psycho-educational needs of the patient, family, caregivers and support systems.</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates the ability to increase the awareness of existing community resources to the patient, family, and caregivers.</LI>\n<LI>Effectively performs in a leadership role as a treatment team member in the treatment team process.</LI>\n<LI>Provides appropriate treatment based on the psychosocial assessments and the recommendations of the treatment team.&nbsp; Performs individual and family counseling, provides psycho-educational resources and facilitates group counseling.</LI>\n<LI>Consistently conducts a psychosocial assessment within 72 hours of admission.</LI>\n<LI>Counsels patients and their families regarding psychosocial needs or problems related to their mental heath treatments.&nbsp; This includes concerns regarding housing, insurance, medications compliance and financial issues.</LI>\n<LI>Provides psycho-educational materials and resources to the patients, families, and other caregivers.</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates the ability to effectively advocate for the patient.</LI>\n<LI>Provides family and individual therapy based on recognized therapeutic techniques.&nbsp; Gives and receives constructive feedback appropriately.</LI>\n<LI>Embraces the concept that as professionals in the complex and ever changing field of mental health treatment Behavioral social workers must be active life-long learners.&nbsp; Accepts the added responsibilities of being a master/licensed level professional in terms of educational demands.</LI>\n</UL>','<DIV>Department Specific Criteria:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Clinical skills and practice congruent with accepted best practice standards of care</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates professionalism by appearance, actions, self-development, and guest relations</LI>\n<LI>Uses interpersonal skills, which convey a positive and supportive attitude</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates flexibility with schedule changes or changing job assignments to meet patient care needs.</LI>\n<LI>Excellent language and communication skills.</LI>\n<LI>Excellent interpersonal skills with demonstration of a team approach to work.</LI>\n<LI>Able to handle high stress situations.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates advance practice in assessment and clinical skills and ability to plan and facilitate therapy groups.</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>Qualifications:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Bachelors&nbsp;in Social Work&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Two years of case management/social work experience required.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-2598a','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-2598a',0,0,0,0,1311937931,1311937931),(152,9,5,'01323-3642','rn-cdu-nights-01323-3642',NULL,'RN CDU Nights','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>Assesses patient/family health problems and resources; takes a leadership role in the development, implementation and outcomes evaluation of a plan for nursing care provided by the nursing team. Provides technical nursing care and interventions to designated patient populations. This position requires providing service to one or more age populations including young adult through geriatric patient population in a manner that demonstrates an understanding of the functional/developmental age of the individual served.<BR/>\n</P>','<P>Graduate of an accredited RN School of Nursing; one year recent acute care experience required; one year recent critical care/PCU experience preferred; excellent written and verbal communication skills; Bilingual (English/Spanish) preferred.<BR/>\n<BR/>\nCurrent Florida RN license. Current BLS and ACLS thru American Heart Association required.&nbsp; CCRN preferred.</SPAN></SPAN></P>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3642','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3642',0,0,0,0,1311937934,1311937934),(153,9,5,'01387-2353','rn-icu-full-time-nights-01387-2353',NULL,'RN ICU Full Time Nights','United States-Florida-St Petersburg','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>Intensive Care Unit (ICU)</DIV>\n<DIV>Founded in 1969, St. Petersburg General Hospital is a 219-bed facility located in the heart of South Pinellas County, Florida.&nbsp;&nbsp; St. Pete General is part of the HCA West Florida Division of Hospitals, a comprehensive network of hospitals, outpatient surgery and diagnostic imaging facilities, and a complete continuum of specialized healthcare programs that meet the healthcare needs of residents and businesses in West and Central Florida communities.&nbsp; Our parent company, HCA, is the nation&#39;s leading provider of healthcare services.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>SPGH is committed to ensuring our patients have access to the highest levels of critical care available.&nbsp; Our <B>Intensive Care unit (ICU)</B> is a 21-bed Medical/Surgical Intensive Care unit, offering exceptional care for the patients we serve.</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>&nbsp;Number of Staff: 36</LI>\n<LI>Skill Mix:&nbsp; RNs, LPNs, Student Nurses, and Critical Care Patient Care Technicians</LI>\n<LI>Major Equipment Used: Phillips Monitoring equipment,&nbsp; IV pumps, SCD machines, feeding pumps, CVVHD, PACS,&nbsp; Accuchek machines, Accu-dose, Standard Critical Care Equipment</LI>\n<LI>Special Certifications Needed:&nbsp; ACLS, BLS</LI>\n<LI>Special Competencies/Skills Needed:&nbsp; Formal Critical Care training class in the past preferred; must pass a critical care skills/knowledge test prior to hire</LI>\n<LI>Schedules: &nbsp;12-hour shifts (0645-1915, 1845-0715); Full Time is considered 36 hours per week, including every other weekend; overtime available, but not mandatory; Self-scheduling is available.</LI>\n<LI>Dress code:&nbsp; Professional scrubs (individual provides their own)</LI>\n<LI>Designated Charge Nurse</LI>\n<LI>Complete computerized charting (&quot;Electronic Health Record&quot;) for patient assessment and care documentation, , Clinical Monitoring Interface, Iatrics Visual Flowsheet&nbsp;&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Electronic medication administration record (eMAR) is used for the delivery of all medications provided to patients&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Critical Care Internship Program (CCIP) offered three times per year7-week critical care training course derived from the Essentials of Critical Care Orientation (ECCO) through AACN Care of the Acute and Critically Ill Patient guidelines, offered on site to our current employees seeking the &quot;next step&quot; into critical care.</LI>\n<LI>Lifting Equipment available:&nbsp; Opera, Encore, Maxislides, Z-slides&nbsp;</LI>\n</UL>','<DIV>Required Job Qualifications include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider and ACLS through the American Heart Association.</LI>\n<LI>National Institute of Health Stroke Scale Certification required (NIHSS cert course available online at www.strokeassociation.org).</LI>\n<LI>Successful completion of a Critical Care Training Course.</LI>\n<LI>Successful completion of an EKG/Telemetry Training Course.</LI>\n<LI>Minimum of 1 year prior ICU RN experience required.</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01387-2353','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01387-2353',0,0,0,0,1311937936,1311939889),(154,9,5,'01387-2350','lpn-endoscopy-lab-full-time-days-01387-2350',NULL,'LPN Endoscopy Lab Full Time Days','United States-Florida-St Petersburg','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>Under the direction of the RN, the Endoscopy LPN&nbsp; works with&nbsp; Physicians, Anesthesiologists, RN&#39;s and other personnel&nbsp; member of the GI team to coordinate patient care activities in the Endoscopy department.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Notes and carries out physicians&#39; and nurses&#39; orders providing needed assistance in performing endoscopic procedures..</LI>\n<LI>Gathers equipment for cleaning and sterilization. .</LI>\n<LI>Attends to&nbsp;the cleaning, sterilization&nbsp;and maintenance of endoscopes and related equipment.</LI>\n<LI>Maintains work area in a neat orderly manner.</LI>\n<LI>Assists in the monitoring of the patient through the procedure.</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an LPN or LVN in the State of Florida.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider through the American Heart Association.</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited practical or vocational nursing program.</LI>\n<LI>Prior Endoscopy Technician/Endoscopy LPN experience REQUIRED.</LI>\n<LI>Must live within a 30-minute radius for on-call requirements.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01387-2350','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01387-2350',0,0,0,0,1311937938,1311937938),(155,9,5,'00311-00011','rn-registered-nurse-regional-medical-center-bayonet-point-florida-00311-00011',NULL,'RN Registered Nurse Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point Florida','United States-Florida-Hudson','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point is home to the nationally recognized Heart Institute and has served Florida\'s Gulf Coast for the last 25 years. Our passion and commitment are reflected in the ongoing recognition our hospital has received. <BR><BR>Among notable credits, we\'ve been named one of \"America\'s Best Hospitals\" in Heart and Heart Surgery by U.S. News &amp; World Report, named a \"Top 100\" hospital seven times according to the HCIA/Solucient, accredited with commendation by the JCAHO, and been ranked a \"Top 100\" cardiovascular hospital five times according to Solucient. In 2006, we received the annual performance achievement award, \"Get with the<BR>Guidelines Coronary Artery Disease\" from the<BR>American Heart Association. <BR><BR>With 290 beds, we offer a spectrum of services seldom found in a small community setting. In addition to our acclaimed Heart Institute, some of our most interesting specialties include: </DIV><UL TYPE=disc><LI>Accredited Chest Pain Center </LI><LI>JCAHO Stroke Program </LI><LI>Cancer Care Center </LI><LI>Neurosurgical Services </LI><LI>Advanced Same-Day Surgery </LI><LI>Regional Infusion Center </LI><LI>Wound Care </LI><LI>Accredited Hyperbaric Oxygen Treatment Program </LI><LI>Regional Center For Orthopedics &amp; Surgical Services </LI></UL><DIV>While we bring state-of-the-art care to Florida\'s Suncoast, we\'re also sensitive to your personal aspirations. That\'s why we\'re proud to provide a convenient, suburban Gulf Coast location just 45 minutes from the city of Tampa. </DIV><DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN\n </LI><LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider. ACLS PALS NRP may be required in specific areas&nbsp;\n</LI><LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing. </LI></UL>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>loney.moses@hcahealthcare.com</A></P>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-00011','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-00011',0,0,0,0,1311937940,1311939914),(156,9,5,'01384-4595','rn-case-manager-prn-01384-4595',NULL,'RN Case Manager (PRN)','United States-Florida-Brandon','Case Management',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>Join us at Brandon Regional, part of the growing HCA West Florida hospital system. Our friendly community hospital boasts a close-knit caring staff of professionals that looks out for its family, neighbors and friends. We offer area-leading specialties at our 407-bed facility, including:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Cardiac &amp; Interventional Services</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Cardiac Surgery</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Emergency Services</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * General Surgery</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Neonatal Intensive Care (Level II &amp; III)</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Pediatrics</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>\n<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current Florida RN license.</LI>\n<LI>CCM preferred&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Minimum&nbsp;3 years of clinical nursing experience.</LI>\n</UL>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>As an integral part of the nation&#39;s largest healthcare system, HCA West Florida hospitals give employees more support than you can possibly imagine. Each of our hospitals is fully equipped with the latest technology and the greatest resources, so you can provide the highest quality care possible. In return for your dedication, we offer a generous benefits package, tuition reimbursement and professional learning opportunities. Plus a lot of extra incentives that make life much more rewarding.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>To learn more about Brandon Regional Hospital please visit: www.MoreCareerChoices.com</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current Florida RN license.</LI>\n<LI>CCM preferred&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Minimum&nbsp;3 years of clinical nursing experience.</LI>\n<LI>Knowledge of CMS guidelines and experience working with payor specific guidelines and contractual rules preferred.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision meeting firm deadlines.</LI>\n<LI>Assertive and persuasive communication skills, action oriented.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-4595','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-4595',0,0,0,0,1311937942,1311939654),(157,9,5,'00311-3224','rn-registered-nurse-emergency-services-10am-10pm-780-00311-3224',NULL,'RN Registered Nurse Emergency Services 10am 10pm 780','United States-Florida-Hudson','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>Join our ER Team&nbsp;as we progress toward Level II Trauma Designation!</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>REGIONAL MEDICAL CENTER BAYONET POINT</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Experience our commitment to compassion and care at Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system. Our 290-bed facility boasts many awards and accolades, particularly for our nationally acclaimed Heart Institute. Our dedication to patients is reflected in the ongoing recognition of our Centers of Excellence, which include:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Advanced Certification for Heart Failure * Chest Pain Center with PCI * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Located on Florida&#39;s West Coast, our suburban location just 45 minutes from Tampa offers a friendly work environment, award winning staff and the opportunity to strengthen your career.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point is in the process of application for a Level II trauma designation.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West and Central Florida&#39;s 15 hospitals we&#39;re not just caregivers, we&#39;re devoted to caring. Located throughout Tampa, St. Petersburg, Sarasota and the greater Orlando area, we&#39;re on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients. As an integral part of the nation&#39;s largest healthcare system with more than 15,000 healthcare professionals on our team, we foster an environment where you will be supported, valued and encouraged to grow.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The Emergency Department RN provides direct nursing care in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Assesses, plans and evaluates patient care needs.</LI>\n<LI>Prioritizes patient care based on acuity level and available resources.</LI>\n<LI>Carries out physician orders.</LI>\n<LI>Assists physician during examination, treatment and procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Administers prescribed medications, changes dressings, cleans wounds, monitors vital signs.</LI>\n<LI>Serves as the primary coordinator of all disciplines for well coordinated patient care.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Instructs and educates patients and families.</LI>\n<LI>Assesses and coordinates patient&#39;s discharge planning needs with members of the healthcare team.</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current Florida licensure as an RN</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as&nbsp;American Heart Association ACLS&nbsp;BLS PALS&nbsp;Healthcare Provider.</LI>\n<LI>CEN&nbsp;Certification Preferred.</LI>\n<LI>TNCC Certification required within 6 months of hire</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-3224','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-3224',0,0,0,0,1311937944,1311939924),(158,9,5,'00643-2958','evs-assistant-ii-prn-00643-2958',NULL,'EVS Assistant II PRN','United States-Florida-Brooksville','Environmental Services',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>The Environmental Services Technician performs a variety of general cleaning tasks to maintain patient rooms, offices, hallways and other assigned areas.&nbsp; These include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Follows specific procedure to perform terminal cleaning of patient rooms and prepares rooms for new patients.</LI>\n<LI>Uses industrial cleaning agents and equipment following appropriate safety procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Operates mechanical floor cleaners, polishers and vacuums.</LI>\n<LI>Moves furniture and other objects as needed in order to ensure adequate cleaning.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Job qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>High school diploma or GED preferred</LI>\n<LI>Ability to read, write, speak and understand English preferred</LI>\n<LI>6 months housekeeping experience in a healthcare or hotel setting preferred</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-2958','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-2958',0,0,0,0,1311937946,1311937946),(159,9,5,'00309-2981','ft-reg-pharmacy-technician-ii-hospital-exp-preferred-1074-1500-hourly-00309-2981',NULL,' FT Reg Pharmacy Technician II Hospital Exp Preferred $10.74 $15.00 Hourly','United States-Florida-Bradenton','Pharmacy & Pharmacy Tech',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>Following physicians&#39; orders, the Pharmacy Tech assists pharmacists&nbsp;by filling routine orders for unit does and prepackaged&nbsp;pharmaceutical&nbsp;dispenses medications.&nbsp; Position tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Counts, packages, and labels unit does for inspection by pharmacist.</LI>\n<LI>Assists pharmacists as directed, including filling orders and preparing labels.</LI>\n<LI>Prepares I.V. mixtures and operates automated systems.</LI>\n<LI>Maintains pharmacy inventory and performs clerical duties.</LI>\n<LI>Maintains strong knowledge of hospital policies and government regulations and performs dispensing duties&nbsp;accordingly.</LI>\n<LI>Assists with quality improvement initiatives, inventory and ordering of pharmaceuticals.</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Orients and mentors staff.</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<DIV>Required Job Qualifications include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>High School graduate or equivalent</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>National certification as a Pharmacy Tech (CPhT)</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>State certification as a Pharmacy Tech</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Previous pharmacy tech experience in a hospital setting preferred.</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-2981','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-2981',0,0,0,0,1311937948,1311939960),(160,9,5,'00309-1941','rn-cvicu-prn-00309-1941',NULL,'RN CVICU (PRN)','United States-Florida-Bradenton','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P>The ICU/CCU RN manages the nursing care of critically ill patients in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</P><UL><LI>Assesses plans and evaluates patient care needs.&nbsp; </LI><LI>Carries out physician orders. </LI><LI>Administers prescribed medications, changes dressings, cleans wounds, monitors vital signs. </LI><LI>Provides respiratory and ventilator management and monitoring for patients. </LI><LI>Serves as the primary coordinator of all disciplines for well coordinated patient care. </LI><LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp; </LI><LI>Instructs and educates patients and families. </LI><LI>Assesses and coordinates patient\'s discharge planning needs with members of the healthcare team. </LI><LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care. </LI><LI>Orients and mentors new staff members. </LI><LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI></UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P><UL><LI>Current licensure as an RN. </LI><LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider and ACLS. </LI><LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing. </LI><LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills. </LI><LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment. </LI><LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI></UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-1941','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-1941',0,0,0,0,1311937950,1311937950),(161,9,5,'00642-1063a','rn-pcu-prn-00642-1063a',NULL,'RN PCU (PRN)','United States-Florida-Sun City Center','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV>Help deliver superior service to the patients at South Bay Hospital, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system. Our team strives to provide effective and efficient care in our 112-bed hospital, which will soon be joined by an all-new medical complex. With new communities breaking ground each year, this is an ideal location to experience our commitment to your career and our community.&nbsp; We support our talented staff with advanced technologies throughout our hospital and Centers of Excellence including:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>* Chest Pain Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center</DIV>\n&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The&nbsp;Registered Nurse in Progressive Care reports directly to the unit Clinical Manager, and is responsible and accountable for the delivery of patient care through the utilization of the nursing process in accordance with&nbsp; physicians&#39; orders, established policies and procedures, established professional standards, and administrative hospital-wide policies.<BR/>\n</DIV>','<DIV>&nbsp;Graduate from an accredited school of nursing.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Current&nbsp;State Registered Nurse License.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Current BLS and ACLS certification required through the American Heart Association.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Minimum 1 year experience in a step-down unit required.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West and Central Florida&#39;s 15 hospitals we&#39;re not just caregivers, we&#39;re devoted to caring. Located throughout Tampa, St. Petersburg, Sarasota and the greater Orlando area, we&#39;re on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients. As an integral part of the nation&#39;s largest healthcare system with more than 15,000 healthcare professionals on our team, we foster an environment where you will be supported, valued and encouraged to grow.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to www.MoreCareerChoices.com.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The Comprehensive Hospital System Serving West &amp; Central Florida</DIV>\n<DIV>Blake Medical Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Brandon Regional Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Central Florida Regional Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Community Hospital of New Port Richey</DIV>\n<DIV>Doctors Hospital of Sarasota</DIV>\n<DIV>Edward White Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Englewood Community Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Fawcett Memorial Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Largo Medical Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Northside Hospital &amp; Tampa Bay Heart Institute</DIV>\n<DIV>Oak Hill Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Osceola Regional Medical Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point</DIV>\n<DIV>South Bay Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>St. Petersburg General Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>EOE</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00642-1063a','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00642-1063a',0,0,0,0,1311937952,1311937952),(162,9,5,'00311-3170','rn-registered-nurse-emergency-services-3p-3a-780-00311-3170',NULL,'RN Registered Nurse Emergency Services 3p 3a 780','United States-Florida-Hudson','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV>Spend your Nights with our Emergency Team as we progress to Level II Trauma Designation!</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>REGIONAL MEDICAL CENTER BAYONET POINT</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Experience our commitment to compassion and care at Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system. Our 290-bed facility boasts many awards and accolades, particularly for our nationally acclaimed Heart Institute. Our dedication to patients is reflected in the ongoing recognition of our Centers of Excellence, which include:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Advanced Certification for Heart Failure * Chest Pain Center with PCI * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Located on Florida&#39;s West Coast, our suburban location just 45 minutes from Tampa offers a friendly work environment, award winning staff and the opportunity to strengthen your career.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point is in the process of application for a Level II trauma designation.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West and Central Florida&#39;s 15 hospitals we&#39;re not just caregivers, we&#39;re devoted to caring. Located throughout Tampa, St. Petersburg, Sarasota and the greater Orlando area, we&#39;re on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients. As an integral part of the nation&#39;s largest healthcare system with more than 15,000 healthcare professionals on our team, we foster an environment where you will be supported, valued and encouraged to grow.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The Emergency Department RN provides direct nursing care in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Assesses, plans and evaluates patient care needs.</LI>\n<LI>Prioritizes patient care based on acuity level and available resources.</LI>\n<LI>Carries out physician orders.</LI>\n<LI>Assists physician during examination, treatment and procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Administers prescribed medications, changes dressings, cleans wounds, monitors vital signs.</LI>\n<LI>Serves as the primary coordinator of all disciplines for well coordinated patient care.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Instructs and educates patients and families.</LI>\n<LI>Assesses and coordinates patient&#39;s discharge planning needs with members of the healthcare team.</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as&nbsp;American Heart Association ACLS&nbsp;BLS PALS&nbsp;Healthcare Provider.</LI>\n<LI>CEN&nbsp;Certification Preferred.</LI>\n<LI>Previous ER experience required.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-3170','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-3170',0,0,0,0,1311937955,1311939854),(163,9,5,'01387-2351','rn-womens-services-ob-gyn-post-partum-full-time-nights-01387-2351',NULL,'RN Women s Services (OB GYN Post Partum) Full Time Nights','United States-Florida-St Petersburg','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>Women&#39;s Services Department</DIV>\n<DIV>Founded in 1969, St. Petersburg General Hospital is a 219-bed facility located in the heart of South Pinellas County, Florida.&nbsp;&nbsp; St. Pete General is part of the HCA West Florida Division of Hospitals, a comprehensive network of hospitals, outpatient surgery and diagnostic imaging facilities, and a complete continuum of specialized healthcare programs that meet the healthcare needs of residents and businesses in West and Central Florida communities.&nbsp; Our parent company, HCA, is the nation&#39;s leading provider of healthcare services.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>SPGH is committed to ensuring our patients have access to the highest levels of care available.&nbsp; The Women&#39;s Center, featuring family centered care, focuses care on the patient and family as one unit. &nbsp;More than 1,000 babies&nbsp;are delivered at St. Petersburg General Hospital each year.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Number of Staff: 75</LI>\n<LI>32 Post Partum/GYN Beds for complete OB/GYN care; this also includes laboring patients and infants (80-90% of patients are Post Partum; may have some medical overflow)</LI>\n<LI>22 Nursery Beds (Level 1 Nursery)</LI>\n<LI>6 Labor/Delivery/Recovery Rooms (2 Operating Rooms)</LI>\n<LI>Skill Mix:&nbsp; RNs, LPNs, Obstetric/Surgical Technologists, and Certified Nursing Assistants</LI>\n<LI>Major Equipment Used: IV pumps, IVAC, Dinamaps, Dopplers, Accu-Check, Accu-Dose, Fetal Monitors, Radiant Warmers, Isolets</LI>\n<LI>Special Certifications Needed:&nbsp; BLS and NRP (ACLS preferred for L&amp;D)</LI>\n<LI>Special Competencies/Skills Needed:</LI>\n<LI>Post Partum/GYN:&nbsp; Prior PP/GYN experience required</LI>\n<LI>Nursery:&nbsp; MUST have prior nursery background; prefer Level 2 or Level 3 experience</LI>\n<LI>Labor and Delivery:&nbsp; Prior L&amp;D nursing experience required</LI>\n<LI>Schedules:&nbsp; 12-hour shifts (0645-1915, 1845-0715) plus 8 hours mandatory on-call for all staff;&nbsp; Full Time is considered 36 hours per week, including every other weekend; overtime available, but not mandatory; Self-scheduling is available</LI>\n<LI>Dress code:&nbsp; Professional scrubs (individual provides their own) - nurses wear royal blue theme</LI>\n<LI>Designated Charge Nurse</LI>\n<LI>Complete computerized charting (&quot;Electronic Health Record&quot;) for patient assessment and care documentation; Labor and Delivery utilizes &quot;OB trace view&quot; for fetal monitoring documentation</LI>\n<LI>Electronic medication administration record (eMAR) is used for the delivery of all medications provided to patients&nbsp;</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current Florida&nbsp;licensure as an RN in the State of Florida.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider through the American Heart Association and NRP.</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Manage stress appropriately.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01387-2351','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01387-2351',0,0,0,0,1311937957,1311939872),(164,9,5,'00643-0049','licensed-physical-therapy-assistant-prn-weekends-weedays-00643-0049',NULL,'Licensed Physical Therapy Assistant PRN Weekends Weedays','United States-Florida-Brooksville','Therapy & Rehabilitation',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>Under the supervision and direction of a licensed physical therapist, The Licensed Physical Therapy Assistant (LPTA) assists in the practice of physical therapy. Responsibilities and tasks include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Carries out treatment plans that have been established by a licensed physical therapist for inpatients and outpatients.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Directs and aids patients in therapeutic exercise, gait and functional training, applies therapeutic modalities, and performs other activities according to the plan of care established by the licensed physical therapist and as permitted by the State Board of Physical Therapy Examiners.</LI>\n<LI>Assists the physical therapist during patient testing, evaluations and complex procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Instructs patients on segments of the plan of care including proper use of wheelchairs, crutches, canes braces and prosthetic appliances and devices.</LI>\n<LI>Documents in computerized documentation system.&nbsp; Prepares correspondence and reports related to plan of care and patient progress.</LI>\n<LI>Directs activities of technicians, students, and volunteers as assigned.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in performance improvement and program development as assigned, to include but not limited to: data gathering, chart reviews, compilation of data into a report.</LI>\n<LI>Performs duties with full understanding of&nbsp; related age specific factors.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>Oak Hill Hospital, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system, is a 214-acute care hospital in the community of Brooksville. Our experienced healthcare team is dedicated to diagnosing and treating patients faster than any hospital in the county. We are the area&#39;s second largest private employer and offer the only comprehensive heart program in Hernando County. We go out of our way for our patients by offering an expanded ED and these Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center with PCI * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Orthopedics &amp; Spine Care Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Located near the family-friendly town of Brooksville, Oak Hill Hospital is situated on Florida&#39;s Nature Coast, which offers fishing, boating, bird watching and hiking. Join us and see why we&#39;re excited to be in one of Florida&#39;s fastest growing counties. Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>. &nbsp;EOE</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited Physical Therapy Assistant program</LI>\n<LI>State licensure as a Physical Therapy Assistant.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking and judgment particularly in determining when to inform the therapist of a significant change in the patients condition.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider (American Heart Association).</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting patients and /or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-0049','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-0049',0,0,0,0,1311937959,1311937959),(165,9,5,'00146-2209','cook-prn-variable-shifts-00146-2209',NULL,'Cook (PRN) Variable Shifts','United States-Florida-New Port Richey','Environmental Services',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV XMLNS=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><FONT FACE=Arial>The Cook&nbsp;performs a variety of tasks that facilitate the provision of food services and nutrition support to patients, employees and visitors.&nbsp; These duties include:</FONT></DIV><UL><LI><FONT FACE=Arial>Prepares, seasons, and cooks food for patients, staff, visitors, and special functions. </FONT></LI><LI><FONT FACE=Arial>Reviews menus to determine types and quantities of food. </FONT></LI><LI><FONT FACE=Arial>Prepares quality food in sufficient quantities to cover all service requirements. </FONT></LI><LI><FONT FACE=Arial>Coordinates timing of preparation in order to meet service schedules for patients, staff, visitors and catering services. </FONT></LI><LI><FONT FACE=Arial>Adheres to standardization of recipes and portion control to prevent food waste and control cost. </FONT></LI><LI><FONT FACE=Arial>Provides care and sanitation of equipment in production area. </FONT></LI><LI><FONT FACE=Arial>Adheres to sanitation and safety standards&nbsp;(HACCP) </FONT></LI><LI><FONT FACE=Arial>Participates in the process of ordering supplies. </FONT></LI><LI><FONT FACE=Arial>Gives directions to personnel who assist in food preparation. </FONT></LI><LI><DIV ALIGN=left><FONT FACE=Arial>Utilizes knowledge of age specific needs of patient in performance of duties and responsibilities.</FONT></DIV></LI><LI><DIV ALIGN=left><FONT FACE=Arial>Orients and mentors new staff members.</FONT></DIV></LI></UL>','<DIV XMLNS=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><FONT FACE=Arial>Job qualifications include:</FONT></DIV><UL or more in-depth Certification as Food Service Manager preferred. </FONT></LI><LI><DIV ALIGN=left><FONT FACE=Arial>Ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment. </FONT></DIV></LI><LI><DIV ALIGN=left><FONT FACE=Arial>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV></LI><LI><DIV ALIGN=left><FONT FACE=Arial>Ability to deal with stressful situations and to stand for long periods of time</FONT></DIV></LI></UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00146-2209','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00146-2209',0,0,0,0,1311937961,1311937961),(166,9,5,'01323-3119','rn-pacu-recovery-prn-01323-3119',NULL,'RN PACU Recovery (PRN)','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>The PACU RN provides nursing care in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Assesses, plans and evaluates the nursing care needs of the patient in the immediate post-operative or post-procedural period.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Provides comfort and support for post-operative patients.</LI>\n<LI>Evaluates responses to treatments and interventions.</LI>\n<LI>Carries out physician orders.</LI>\n</UL>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN.</LI>\n<LI>Current&nbsp;CPR and ACLS certifications thru American Heart Association</LI>\n<LI>ICU/CCU experience preferred</LI>\n<LI>Previous experience in PACU/Recovery is a plus</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3119','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3119',0,0,0,0,1311937963,1311937963),(167,9,5,'00327-1980','rn-outpatient-surgery-prn-00327-1980',NULL,'RN Outpatient Surgery (PRN)','United States-Florida-Sanford','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P>Provide safe and effective nursing care to all patients utilizing the nursing process. Responsible for the direction and supervision of assigned personnel delivering patient care. </P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>','<P>Additional Information: RN license, at least 1 year general nursing experience, ACLS and BLS. Great IV skills and EKG competency. Ability to take emergency call. </P>\n<P><BR>&nbsp;</P>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-1980','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-1980',0,0,0,0,1311937965,1311939538),(168,9,5,'01147-58A','fans-asst-prn-01147-58a',NULL,'FANS Asst. (PRN)','United States-Florida-Sarasota','Environmental Services',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P>The Food and Nutrition Services&nbsp;Assistant performs a variety of tasks that facilitate the provision of food services and nutrition support to patients, employees and visitors. These duties include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Performs routine duties related to preparation and serving of food.</LI>\n<LI>Prepares food for cooking by washing, peeling, shredding, slicing, and mixing various food items.</LI>\n<LI>Operates dishwasher or assists with washing/sterilizing dishes, glassware, silverware, utensils, pots, pans, etc.</LI>\n<LI>Cleans kitchen work areas, collects and disposes of garbage.</LI>\n<LI>May assist with food stocking.</LI>\n<LI>Serves food in&nbsp; cafeteria for visitors and staff and in patients room following dietary, sanitary and safety guidelines.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Clears patients&#39; dirty trays and works in dish room when needed.</LI>\n<LI>Works on patient tray assembly line following menu directives for determining food items for each tray.</LI>\n<LI>Delivers food trays to patient areas.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Job qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>High school diploma or GED required.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to read, write, speak and understand English preferred</LI>\n<LI>6 months food service experience preferred, previous&nbsp; experience in hospital food services preferred.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01147-58A','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01147-58A',0,0,0,0,1311937967,1311937967),(169,9,5,'00367-594','fans-assistant-00367-594',NULL,'FANS Assistant','United States-Florida-St Petersburg','Environmental Services',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P>The Food and Nutrition Services Worker performs a variety of tasks that facilitate the provision of food services and nutrition support to patients, employees and visitors. These duties include:</P><UL><LI>Performs routine duties related to preparation and serving of food. </LI><LI>Prepares food for cooking by washing, peeling, shredding, slicing, and mixing various food items. </LI><LI>Operates dishwasher or assists with washing/sterilizing dishes, glassware, silverware, utensils, pots, pans, etc. </LI><LI>Cleans kitchen work areas, collects and disposes of garbage. </LI><LI>May assist with food stocking. </LI><LI>Serves food in&nbsp; cafeteria for visitors and staff and in patients room following dietary, sanitary and safety guidelines.&nbsp; </LI><LI>Clears patients\' dirty trays and works in dish room when needed. </LI><LI>Works on patient tray assembly line following menu directives for determining food items for each tray. </LI><LI>Delivers food trays to patient areas. </LI><LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI></UL>','<P>Job qualifications include:</P><UL><LI>High school diploma or GED preferred </LI><LI>Ability to read, write, speak and understand English preferred </LI><LI>6 months food service experience preferred, previous&nbsp; experience in hospital food services preferred.</LI></UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00367-594','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00367-594',0,0,0,0,1311937969,1311937969),(170,9,5,'00643-0146','speech-language-pathologist-prn-weekends-00643-0146',NULL,'Speech Language Pathologist (PRN) Weekends','United States-Florida-Brooksville','Therapy & Rehabilitation',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>The Speech Language Pathologist is responsible for planning and administering medically prescribed treatment programs for the rehabilitation of speech, language, cognitive and oral motor disorders.&nbsp; Job tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Counsels, educates and instructs patients and their families regarding their speech-language pathology treatment</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates competency in rehabilitation procedures</LI>\n<LI>Maintains accurate patient records</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>Oak Hill Hospital, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system, is a 214-acute care hospital in the community of Brooksville. Our experienced healthcare team is dedicated to diagnosing and treating patients faster than any hospital in the county. We are the area\'s second largest private employer and offer the only comprehensive heart program in Hernando County. We go out of our way for our patients by offering an expanded ED and these Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center with PCI * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Orthopedics &amp; Spine Care Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Located near the family-friendly town of Brooksville, Oak Hill Hospital is situated on Florida\'s Nature Coast, which offers fishing, boating, bird watching and hiking. Join us and see why we\'re excited to be in one of Florida\'s fastest growing counties. Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>. &nbsp;EOE</DIV>\n<DIV><BR/>\n</DIV>','<P>Job qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Degree in Speech Language Pathology required.</LI>\n<LI>Must be currently licensed by the state as a Speech Language Pathologist</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider required (American Heart Association).</LI>\n<LI>Previous experience in an acute care hospital setting required.</LI>\n<LI>Requires strong communication and interpersonal skills.</LI>\n<LI>Must be able to work in a fast-paced environment.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-0146','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-0146',0,0,0,0,1311937971,1311937971),(171,9,5,'00311-0229','clinical-dietitian-prn-00311-0229',NULL,'Clinical Dietitian (PRN)','United States-Florida-Hudson','Environmental Services',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV>Experience our commitment to compassion and care at Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system. Our 290-bed facility boasts many awards and accolades, particularly for our nationally acclaimed Heart Institute. Our dedication to patients is reflected in the ongoing recognition of our Centers of Excellence, which include:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Advanced Certification for Heart Failure * Chest Pain Center with PCI * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Located on Florida&#39;s West Coast, our suburban location just 45 minutes from Tampa offers a friendly work environment, award winning staff and the opportunity to strengthen your career.</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV><STRONG>PRN Schedule:&nbsp;&nbsp;Weekday shifts available</STRONG></DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The <STRONG>Clinical Dietitian</STRONG>&nbsp;leads the processes in place to ensure that the patients&#39; nutritional needs are met.&nbsp; Job tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Conducts and implements comprehensive nutritional assessments for patients</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>Assesses, plans, writes and evaluates patient diets.</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Plans menus in accordance with patient dietary requirements and general dietetic standards and regulations.</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>Instructs and counsels patients on dietary restrictions/recommendations.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in multidisciplinary teams providing input regarding treatment&nbsp;plans.</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Directs and supervises personnel in the process of planning, preparing, and serving food to patients.</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>Maintains records of patient reaction to prescribed diets.</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Monitors, records and communicates as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Utilizes knowledge of age specific needs of patient in performance of duties and responsibilities.</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Orients and mentors new staff members.</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<DIV>Job qualifications include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Bachelors Degree in Dietetics or Nutrition required.</LI>\n<LI>American Dietetic Association Registration strongly preferred (R.D.)</LI>\n<LI>Must have current state licensure as a Dietitian (L.D.)</LI>\n<LI>Previous experience as a hospital dietitian preferred.</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs</DIV>\n</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West and Central Florida&#39;s 15 hospitals we&#39;re not just caregivers, we&#39;re devoted to caring. Located throughout Tampa, St. Petersburg, Sarasota and the greater Orlando area, we&#39;re on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients. As an integral part of the nation&#39;s largest healthcare system with more than 15,000 healthcare professionals on our team, we foster an environment where you will be supported, valued and encouraged to grow.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to www.MoreCareerChoices.com.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The Comprehensive Hospital System Serving West &amp; Central Florida</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Blake Medical Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Brandon Regional Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Central Florida Regional Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Community Hospital of New Port Richey</DIV>\n<DIV>Doctors Hospital of Sarasota</DIV>\n<DIV>Edward White Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Englewood Community Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Fawcett Memorial Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Largo Medical Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Northside Hospital &amp; Tampa Bay Heart Institute</DIV>\n<DIV>Oak Hill Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Osceola Regional Medical Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point</DIV>\n<DIV>South Bay Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>St. Petersburg General Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>EOE</DIV>\n<DIV><B><BR/>\n</B>&nbsp;</DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-0229','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-0229',0,0,0,0,1311937973,1311939547),(172,9,5,'01384-5051','physical-therapy-assistant-full-time-join-our-dynamic-rehab-team-01384-5051',NULL,'Physical Therapy Assistant Full time Join our dynamic Rehab team ','United States-Florida-Brandon','Therapy & Rehabilitation',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>Under the supervision and direction of a licensed physical therapist, The Licensed Physical Therapy Assistant (LPTA) assists in the practice of physical therapy. Responsibilities and tasks include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Carries out treatment plans that have been established by a licensed physical therapist for inpatients and outpatients.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Directs and aids patients in therapeutic exercise, gait and functional training, applies therapeutic modalities, and performs other activities according to the plan of care established by the licensed physical therapist and as permitted by the State Board of Physical Therapy Examiners.</LI>\n<LI>Assists the physical therapist during patient testing, evaluations and complex procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Instructs patients on segments of the plan of care including proper use of wheelchairs, crutches, canes braces and prosthetic appliances and devices.</LI>\n<LI>Documents in computerized documentation system.&nbsp; Prepares correspondence and reports related to plan of care and patient progress.</LI>\n<LI>Directs activities of technicians, students, and volunteers as assigned.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in performance improvement and program development as assigned, to include but not limited to: data gathering, chart reviews, compilation of data into a report.</LI>\n<LI>Performs duties with full understanding of&nbsp; related age specific factors.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>Brandon Regional Hospital is committed to providing our patients and their families with compassionate care. For more than 30 years our busy, 407-bed acute care facility has been dedicated to quality and devoted to our community. We have been named a Top 100 Hospital in America five times, and our Intensive Care Unit has been named a Top 100 ICU.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Families trust us to meet their needs, knowing that they have access to these Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Spine Care Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care * Women&#39;s &amp; Children&#39;s Center</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Join our friendly community hospital with its close-knit staff of caring professionals located just south of Tampa and discover how we care.&nbsp; Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>. EOE</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited Physical Therapy Assistant program</LI>\n<LI>State of Florida&nbsp;licensure as a Physical Therapy Assistant.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking and judgment particularly in determining when to inform the therapist of a significant change in the patients condition.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider (American Heart Association).</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting patients and /or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-5051','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-5051',0,0,0,0,1311937977,1311937977),(173,9,5,'00643-2880','vice-president-of-quality-and-risk-management-00643-2880',NULL,'Vice President of Quality and Risk Management','United States-Florida-Brooksville','Quality Risk & Safety',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>Oak Hill Hospital, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system, is a 214-acute care hospital in the community of Brooksville. Our experienced healthcare team is dedicated to diagnosing and treating patients faster than any hospital in the county. We are the area&#39;s second largest private employer and offer the only comprehensive heart program in Hernando County. We go out of our way for our patients by offering an expanded ED and these Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center with PCI * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Orthopedics &amp; Spine Care Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Located near the family-friendly town of Brooksville, Oak Hill Hospital is situated on Florida&#39;s Nature Coast, which offers fishing, boating, bird watching and hiking. Join us and see why we&#39;re excited to be in one of Florida&#39;s fastest growing counties.</DIV>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>The&nbsp;<STRONG>Vice President of Quality and Risk Management</STRONG> is responsible for the following:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Demonstrates responsibility and accountability in the organizational wide direction and facilitation of performance&nbsp; assessment, reassessment, development and implementation of the Quality/Performance Improvement program in accordance with all regulatory requirements.</LI>\n<LI>Utilizes, integrates, and interprets data to assist organization in its improvement efforts, and promote optimal patient outcomes. Works collaboratively with Senior Management to develop strategic quality initiatives.</LI>\n<LI>Leads organizational performance efforts for JCAHO, core quality measures, COP and&nbsp; regulatory and all other accrediting and regulatory agencies. Ensures compliance with JCAHO, and all legal, regulatory and accrediting agency requirements are met.</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates responsibility and accountability for organizational wide occurrence reporting system; analyzes and reports trends and identifies appropriate interventions to reduce risk and liability to the organization.</LI>\n<LI>Develops and implements educational programs for employees, medical staff and board members on analysis of risk assessment, historical and concurrent occurrence and claims data and national trends.</LI>\n<LI>Facilitates and directs organizational wide risk management program to ensure compliance with statutory mandates, regulatory requirements and accreditation standards of professional organizations, i.e., JCAHO, OSHA, etc.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in and provides leadership for organizational disaster preparedness and patient safety initiatives.</LI>\n<LI>Applies the principles of continuous quality improvement in delivery of services, through measuring, monitoring and assessing risk management&nbsp; processes and systems.</LI>\n<LI>Acts as an active member of peer review committees; analyzes cases and outcome data and collaborates with physicians to promote and improve practice and&nbsp; optimal patient outcomes.</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates knowledge of the occurrence reporting system and reports trends in occurrences to staff quarterly.&nbsp; This information is used to improve patient safety.&nbsp; Addresses patient safety in the Performance Improvement Plan.</LI>\n</UL>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>','<UL>\n<LI>Bachelor&#39;s Degree or Post Graduate Degree in a healthcare related field.</LI>\n<LI>More than&nbsp;five years of experience in a&nbsp;hospital environment.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Previous experience in accreditation, quality or utilization management</LI>\n<LI>Knowledge of State, Federal, and JCAHO regulations.</LI>\n<LI>Current Florida licensure as a Registered Nurse. Current Florida License in Healthcare Risk Management</LI>\n<LI>Certified Professional in Healthcare Quality (CPHQ) preferred.<BR/>\n</LI>\n</UL>\n<P>emily.giorgi@hcahealthcare.com</A> or 727-772-5148</P>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10141/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-2880','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10141/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-2880',0,0,0,0,1311937979,1311938995),(174,9,5,'00309-3003','certified-nursing-asst-rehab-ft-nights-00309-3003',NULL,'Certified Nursing Asst (Rehab) FT Nights','United States-Florida-Bradenton','Nursing Support',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>Working under the supervision of a nurse, the CNA/Patient Care Tech/Aide&nbsp;performs various patient care activities necessary in caring for the personal needs and comfort of patients.&nbsp; The position&#39;s tasks and responsibilities include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Bathes, dresses/undresses patients assist with personal hygiene.</LI>\n<LI>Serves and collects food trays.&nbsp; Assists with patient feeding.</LI>\n<LI>Transports, positions&nbsp; and drapes patients for exams and treatments.</LI>\n<LI>Assists patients in ambulating.</LI>\n<LI>Takes and records vital signs, weights and I &amp; O.</LI>\n<LI>Performs non sterile dressing changes.</LI>\n<LI>Passes and collects bed pans.</LI>\n<LI>Changes bed linens.</LI>\n<LI>Provides encouragement, support and comfort to patients and family members.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications Include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>High School Graduate or equivalent <STRONG></STRONG>required.</LI>\n<LI>Current BLS certification&nbsp;through the <SPAN>American Heart Association</SPAN> required.</LI>\n<LI>Successful completion of a Nursing Assistant training program.</LI>\n<LI>Florida Certification as a Nurse Assistant required.</LI>\n<LI>Previous hospital related experience is desired.</LI>\n<LI>Working knowledge of medical terminology.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to quickly make decisions to report patient condition with minimal supervision.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-3003','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-3003',0,0,0,0,1311937981,1311937981),(175,9,5,'01387-1739','rn-critical-care-icu-prn-01387-1739',NULL,'RN Critical Care (ICU) PRN','United States-Florida-St Petersburg','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>Intensive Care Unit (ICU)</DIV>\n<DIV>Founded in 1969, St. Petersburg General Hospital is a 219-bed facility located in the heart of South Pinellas County, Florida.&nbsp;&nbsp; St. Pete General is part of the HCA West Florida Division of Hospitals, a comprehensive network of hospitals, outpatient surgery and diagnostic imaging facilities, and a complete continuum of specialized healthcare programs that meet the healthcare needs of residents and businesses in West and Central Florida communities.&nbsp; Our parent company, HCA, is the nation&#39;s leading provider of healthcare services.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>SPGH is committed to ensuring our patients have access to the highest levels of critical care available.&nbsp; Our <B>Intensive Care unit (ICU)</B> is a 21-bed Medical/Surgical Intensive Care unit, offering exceptional care for the patients we serve.</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>&nbsp;Number of Staff: 36</LI>\n<LI>Skill Mix:&nbsp; RNs, LPNs, Student Nurses, and Critical Care Patient Care Technicians</LI>\n<LI>Major Equipment Used: Phillips Monitoring equipment,&nbsp; IV pumps, SCD machines, feeding pumps, CVVHD, PACS,&nbsp; Accuchek machines, Accu-dose, Standard Critical Care Equipment</LI>\n<LI>Special Certifications Needed:&nbsp; ACLS, BLS</LI>\n<LI>Special Competencies/Skills Needed:&nbsp; Formal Critical Care training class in the past preferred; must pass a critical care skills/knowledge test prior to hire</LI>\n<LI>Schedules: &nbsp;12-hour shifts (0645-1915, 1845-0715); Full Time is considered 36 hours per week, including every other weekend; overtime available, but not mandatory; Self-scheduling is available.</LI>\n<LI>Dress code:&nbsp; Professional scrubs (individual provides their own)</LI>\n<LI>Designated Charge Nurse</LI>\n<LI>Complete computerized charting (&quot;Electronic Health Record&quot;) for patient assessment and care documentation, , Clinical Monitoring Interface, Iatrics Visual Flowsheet&nbsp;&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Electronic medication administration record (eMAR) is used for the delivery of all medications provided to patients&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Critical Care Internship Program (CCIP) offered three times per year7-week critical care training course derived from the <SPAN>AACN Care of the Acute and Critically Ill Patient</SPAN> guidelines, offered on site to our current employees seeking the &quot;next step&quot; into critical care.</LI>\n<LI>Lifting Equipment available:&nbsp; Opera, Encore, Maxislides, Z-slides&nbsp;</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>More options.&nbsp; More opportunities.&nbsp; More places for you to express your passion for quality and expand your potential for success.&nbsp; With 16 hospitals to choose from, there is no limit to what you can do at HCA West Florida. Join us at St. Petersburg General Hospital, centrally located in the heart of St. Petersburg, for the next exciting step in your career!</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider and ACLS through the American Heart Association.</LI>\n<LI>Successful completion of a Critical Care Training Course.</LI>\n<LI>Successful completion of an EKG/Telemetry Training Course.</LI>\n<LI>Minimum of 1 year prior ICU RN experience required.</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10141/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01387-1739','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10141/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01387-1739',0,0,0,0,1311937983,1311939004),(176,9,5,'00144-03182','rn-pacu-prn-00144-03182',NULL,'RN PACU PRN','United States-Florida-Largo','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>Largo Medical Center is a 256- bed acute care hospital located in mid-Pinellas County on the West Coast of Florida.&nbsp; Largo Medical Center enjoys a superb reputation in the community, attributable in large measure to our high customer service to our patients and we are the only area hospital with private rooms for all patients.&nbsp; Additionally, we have been repeatedly ranked among the top 100 U.S. hospitals for overall care, and we\'ve earned the top 100 U.S. designation specifically for our cardiovascular, orthopedic, stroke and intensive care services.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Features at our hospital include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Cardiovascular/Open Heart with 2 dedicated heart surgery suites.&nbsp; 250 Open Heart surgeries per year.</LI>\n<LI>Comprehensive Cardiac Catheterization Services</LI>\n<LI>Florida Knee and Ortho Pavilion (Elective Joint Surgery center)</LI>\n<LI>State of the art surgery &amp; ambulatory care center</LI>\n<LI>Florida Breast Institute</LI>\n<LI>10 Multifunction Surgical Suites</LI>\n<LI>4 Endoscopic Suites</LI>\n<LI>16 private pre-op rooms</LI>\n<LI>Spacious Emergency department with 29 Private ED Treatment rooms</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The PACU RN provides nursing care in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Assesses, plans and evaluates the nursing care needs of the patient in the immediate post-operative or post-procedural period.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Provides comfort and support for post-operative patients.</LI>\n<LI>Evaluates responses to treatments and interventions.</LI>\n<LI>Carries out physician orders.</LI>\n<LI>Anticipates case specific needs based on knowledge of procedure and pathophysiology regarding patient and procedure.</LI>\n<LI>Manages patient&#39;s pain.</LI>\n<LI>Administers prescribed medications and monitors vital signs.</LI>\n<LI>Maintains aseptic technique and actively monitors situations which could lead to breaches in aseptic technique.</LI>\n<LI>Serves as the primary coordinator of all disciplines for well coordinated patient care.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN.</LI>\n<LI>2 years Hospital PACU experience or 2 years ICU experience perferred.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider, ACLS, PALS.</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10141/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-03182','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10141/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-03182',0,0,0,0,1311937985,1311939014),(177,9,5,'00144-4769','rn-tele-progr-care-ft-days-00144-4769',NULL,'RN Tele Progr Care FT Days','United States-Florida-Largo','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>The RN&nbsp;Tele/Progr Care&nbsp;provides direct nursing care in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Assesses plans and evaluates patient care needs.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Carries out physician orders.</LI>\n<LI>Administers prescribed medications, changes dressings, cleans wounds, monitors vital signs.</LI>\n<LI>Serves as the primary coordinator of all disciplines for well coordinated patient care.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Instructs and educates patients and families.</LI>\n<LI>Assesses and coordinates patient&#39;s discharge planning needs with members of the healthcare team.</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN</LI>\n<LI>Current AHA certification as a BLS &amp; ACLS.</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-4769','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-4769',0,0,0,0,1311937987,1311937987),(178,9,5,'01147-315','respiratory-therapist-rrt-prn-01147-315',NULL,'Respiratory Therapist RRT (PRN)','United States-Florida-Sarasota','Therapy & Rehabilitation',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">Come work with the most enthusiastic and friendly staff. &nbsp;</SPAN>Doctors Hospital is a 168-bed facility that uses the latest technology.&nbs