s.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Number of Staff:&nbsp; 35</LI>\n<LI>7 Main Operating Rooms plus 2 Open Heart (CVOR) Rooms</LI>\n<LI>Type of General Cases:&nbsp; Total Joints, Orthopedics, Spine, General, GU, GYN, ENT, Thoracic, Vascular, and Plastics</LI>\n<LI>Approximate Number of Cases Performed:&nbsp; VariesGeneral: 7-20 per day, 3000-3500 annually; CV: 1-2 per day on average&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Skill Mix:&nbsp; Registered Nurses and Surgical Technologists (Certified and Non-certified)</LI>\n<LI>Major Equipment Used:&nbsp; Steris OR tables, lights, and sterilizers, Valley Lab cautery units, headlights, Stryker and Olympus video systems, Stryker and Anspauch powered- instrumentation, Zeiss microscopes, STEALTH, CUSA, specialized tables (cysto, Jackson, Andrews),&nbsp; Olympus endoscopes,&nbsp; Harmonic Scalpel and Ligasure units; Medtronic Cardioblate or Atrium Atricure (for CV/MAZE procedures), Guidant Scope and Stryker Video System (for CV/Endoscopic Vein Harvest).</LI>\n<LI>Special Certifications Needed:&nbsp; CNOR preferred for RNs, but not required; CST preferred for Surg Techs. BCLS certification required through the American Heart Association.</LI>\n<LI>Special Competencies/Skills Needed:&nbsp; Must have a minimum of ONE year of hospital CVOR experience&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Schedules:&nbsp; 8-hour shifts, Monday-Friday, with on-call requirements</LI>\n<LI>Dress code:&nbsp; Scrubs (individual provides their own)</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>High School Diploma or equivalent.</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of a formal surgical technologist program or equivalent training.</LI>\n<LI><STRONG>MUST have prior CVOR OR tech experience; minimum of 3-5 years preferred.</STRONG></LI>\n<LI>Certification as a Surgical Technologist <STRONG>required</STRONG>.</LI>\n<LI><STRONG>Must live within a 30-minute drive time radius of the hospital for on-call requirements</STRONG>.</LI>\n<LI>Detail-orien