1384-4782','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-4782',0,0,0,0,1311938030,1311938030),(197,9,5,'01323-3512','advanced-registered-nurse-practitioner-specialty-saturday-sunday-monday-01323-3512',NULL,'Advanced Registered Nurse Practitioner Specialty (Saturday Sunday Monday)','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Part-time',NULL,'<P>The Advanced Practice Nurse demonstrates a high level of clinical competence that creates an environment of clinical excellence resulting in improved individual and group clinical outcomes.&nbsp; Facilitates individualized, evidence-based, highly effective care to patients and families through coordination/collaboration of the entire healthcare team.&nbsp; Through role modeling, coaching and demonstration, fosters learning for the staff and promotes outcomes-oriented nursing practice.</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>','<UL>\n<LI>Current FL ARNP license</LI>\n<LI>Current DEA registration</LI>\n<LI>Masters Degree in Healthcare or related field</LI>\n<LI>Current BLS and ACLS certifications thru American Heart Association</LI>\n<LI>Proficient in NIHSS</LI>\n<LI>Previous Neuro exprience is a plus</LI>\n<LI>Available to work Saturday, Sunday, and Monday</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3512','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3512',0,0,0,0,1311938032,1311938032),(198,9,5,'00367-1298','rn-medical-surgical-surgical-unit-full-time-days-experience-required-00367-1298',NULL,'RN Medical Surgical (Surgical Unit) Full TIme Days Experience Required','United States-Florida-St Petersburg','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV><EM><STRONG><SPAN>Medical/Surgical Nursing Department</SPAN></STRONG></EM></DIV>\n<DIV>Founded in 1976, Edward White Hospital is a 167-bed facility located in the heart of South Pinellas County, Florida.&nbsp;&nbsp; Edward White Hospital is part of the HCA West Florida Division of Hospitals, a comprehensive network of hospitals, outpatient surgery and diagnostic imaging facilities, and a complete continuum of specialized healthcare programs that meet the healthcare needs of residents and businesses in West and Central Florida communities.&nbsp; Our parent company, HCA, is the nation&#39;s leading provider of healthcare services.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Our patient profile ranges from a diabetic care patient to one who&#39;s just undergone an elective surgery.&nbsp; Our Medical/Surgical Nursing Department consists of 30 beds, with a mixture of semi-private and private rooms.&nbsp; We are expecting further growth with the addition of surgical beds to our med/surg unit in the next 6 months.&nbsp; The Med/Surg Nursing staff is dedicated to the care of the general medical and post-op surgical patients we serve.&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>At EWH, we utilize complete computerized charting (&quot;Electronic Hospital Record&quot;) for our patient assessment and care documentation.&nbsp; We also utilize eMAR, our electronic medication administration record for the delivery of all medications provided to our patients, which has significantly reduced errors associated when administering medications.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Number of Staff: 40</LI>\n<LI>Skill Mix:&nbsp; RN, LPN, Unit Secretary, CNA, Student Nurse</LI>\n<LI>Major Equipment Used:&nbsp; IV pumps, IVAC, Dinamaps, Dopplers, Lifting Equipment, Accu-Check, Omni-Cell, Crash Cart, Feeding pumps, etc.</LI>\n<LI>Special Certifications Needed:&nbsp; BLS required, ACLS preferred</LI>\n<LI>Special Skills or Competencies Needed:&nbsp; Prior nursing experience, preferable in an acute care setting; critical thinker, positive attitude, organized, team player, eager to learn and teach others; Orthopedic experience desired</LI>\n<LI>Schedules:&nbsp; 12-hour shifts (7-7)&nbsp; Full Time is considered 36 hours per week, including every other weekend; Self-scheduling is available</LI>\n<LI>Dress code:&nbsp; Professional scrubs (individual provides their own)</LI>\n<LI>Designated Charge Nurse who DOES NOT regularly take an assignment</LI>\n<LI>Lifting equipment available:&nbsp; Opera, Encore, Maxislides, Z-slides</LI>\n<LI>Family atmosphere hospital where &quot;everybody knows your name&quot;</LI>\n<LI>Ratings! Ratings!! Ratings!!! --&nbsp; In the Top 15%&nbsp;of all of HCA (nationwide) for Employee satisfaction</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>At HCA West and Central Florida&#39;s 15 hospitals we&#39;re not just caregivers, we&#39;re devoted to caring. Located throughout Tampa, St. Petersburg, Sarasota and the greater Orlando area, we&#39;re on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients. As an integral part of the nation&#39;s largest healthcare system with more than 15,000 healthcare professionals on our team, we foster an environment where you will be supported, valued and encouraged to grow.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to www.MoreCareerChoices.com.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<DIV>Required Job Qualifications include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN in the State of Florida.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider through the American Heart Association.</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI>Minimum 1 year experience&nbsp;(acute care/hospital) required.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00367-1298','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00367-1298',0,0,0,0,1311938035,1311938035),(199,9,5,'01384-5116','rn-case-manager-01384-5116',NULL,'RN Case Manager','United States-Florida-Brandon','Case Management',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">Our friendly community hospital boasts a close-knit caring staff of professionals that looks out for its family, neighbors and friends. We offer area-leading specialties at our 407-bed facility, including:</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">Cardiac &amp; Interventional Services</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Cardiac Surgery</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Emergency Services</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * General Surgery</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Neonatal Intensive Care (Level II &amp; III)</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Pediatrics</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</SPAN></P>\n<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current Florida RN license.</LI>\n<LI>Minimum&nbsp;3 years of clinical nursing experience.</LI>\n<LI>Knowledge of CMS guidelines and experience working with payor specific guidelines and contractual rules preferred.</LI>\n</UL>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">please visit: www.MoreCareerChoices.com</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current Florida RN license.</LI>\n<LI>Minimum&nbsp;3 years of clinical nursing experience.</LI>\n<LI>Knowledge of CMS guidelines and experience working with payor specific guidelines and contractual rules preferred.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision meeting firm deadlines.</LI>\n<LI>Assertive and persuasive communication skills, action oriented.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-5116','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-5116',0,0,0,0,1311938037,1311939644),(200,9,5,'01384-4515','fans-assistant-prn-01384-4515',NULL,'FANS Assistant PRN','United States-Florida-Brandon','Environmental Services',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P>The Food and Nutrition Services Worker performs a variety of tasks that facilitate the provision of food services and nutrition support to patients, employees and visitors. These duties include:</SPAN></P>\n<UL>\n<LI><SPAN>Performs routine duties related to preparation and serving of food.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Prepares food for cooking by washing, peeling, shredding, slicing, and mixing various food items.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Operates dishwasher or assists with washing/sterilizing dishes, glassware, silverware, utensils, pots, pans, etc.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Cleans kitchen work areas, collects and disposes of garbage.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>May assist with food stocking.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Serves food in&nbsp; cafeteria for visitors and staff and in patients room following dietary, sanitary and safety guidelines.&nbsp;</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Clears patients&#39; dirty trays and works in dish room when needed.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Works on patient tray assembly line following menu directives for determining food items for each tray.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Delivers food trays to patient areas.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</SPAN></LI>\n</UL>','<P>Job qualifications include:</SPAN></P>\n<UL>\n<LI><SPAN>High school diploma or GED preferred</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>6 months food service experience preferred, previous&nbsp; experience in hospital food services preferred.</SPAN></LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-4515','https://hca.taleo.net/careersecti