d Nurse is responsible and accountable for the planning, directing, and provision of nursing care to patients in accordance with the Florida Nurse Practice Act, physician&#39;s orders, recognized nursing techniques, policies, procedures, established standards and administrative policies.&nbsp;To provide safe and effective nursing care for criticallyl ill intensive care&nbsp;and Neuro&nbsp;level patients utilizing the nursing process.</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current FL RN License</LI>\n<LI>Current CPR and ACLS certifications thru American Heart Association</LI>\n<LI>Critical Care Certification is a plus</LI>\n<LI>Previous Neuro and ICU experience preferred</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-2499','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-2499',0,0,0,0,1311938102,1311938102),(231,9,5,'01385-3750','charge-rn-medical-surgical-3-west-full-time-days-01385-3750',NULL,'Charge RN Medical Surgical (3 West) Full Time Days','United States-Florida-St Petersburg','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>Northside Hospital and Tampa Bay Heart Institute</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Medical/Surgical Nursing Department</DIV>\n<DIV>Founded in 1976, Northside Hospital and Tampa Bay Heart Institute is a 288-bed facility located in the heart of South Pinellas County, Florida.&nbsp;&nbsp; Northside is part of the HCA West Florida Division of Hospitals, a comprehensive network of hospitals, outpatient surgery and diagnostic imaging facilities, and a complete continuum of specialized healthcare programs that meet the healthcare needs of residents and businesses in West and Central Florida communities.&nbsp; Our parent company, HCA, is the nation&#39;s leading provider of healthcare services.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Our Medical/Surgical Nursing Department is a 74-bed unit (37 Medical/37 Surgical), offering exceptional care for the patients we serve.&nbsp; Our patient profile ranges from a diabetic care patient to one who&#39;s just undergone an elective surgery.&nbsp; At Northside, we utilize complete computerized charting for our patient assessment and care documentation.&nbsp; We also utilize eMAR, our electronic medication administration record for the delivery of all medications provided to our patients.&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Number of Staff: 90</LI>\n<LI>Skill Mix:&nbsp; RN, LPN, Unit Secretary, CNA, Student Nurse</LI>\n<LI>Major Equipment Used:&nbsp; IV pumps, IVAC, Dinamaps, Dopplers, Lifting Equipment, Accu-Check, Accu-Dose, Crash Cart</LI>\n<LI>Special Certifications Needed:&nbsp; American Heart Association BLS, ACLS preferred.</LI>\n<LI>Special Competencies/Skills Needed: Prior Nursing experience preferred; IV certification course for LPNs</LI>\n<LI>Schedules:&nbsp; 12-hour shifts (7-7);&nbsp; Full Time is considered 36 hours per week, including every other weekend</LI>\n<LI>Dress code:&nbsp; Tasteful scrubs (individual provides their own). As of 9/1/2010, royal blue scrubs will be required for nursing staff.</LI>\n<LI>Designated Charge Nurse/Clinical Coordinator&nbsp;&nbsp;</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>More options.&nbsp; More opportunities.&nbsp; More places for you to express your passion for quality and expand your potential for success.&nbsp; With 15 hospitals to choose from, there is no limit to what you can do at HCA West Florida. Join us at Northside Hospital &amp; Tampa Bay Heart Institute, centrally located in the heart of St. Petersburg, for the next exciting step in your career!</DIV>','<DIV>Required Job Qualifications include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider through the American Heart Association.</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI>Minimum of 3-5 year of clinical nursing experience.&nbsp; Prior Charge or Supervisory experience desired.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01385-3750','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01385-3750',0,0,0,0,1311938104,1311939578),(232,9,5,'01384-4790','rn-med-surg-ortho-prn-01384-4790',NULL,'RN Med Surg Ortho (PRN)','United States-Florida-Brandon','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV>Brandon Regional Hospital is committed to providing our patients and their families with compassionate care. For more than 30 years our busy, 407-bed acute care facility has been dedicated to quality and devoted to our community. We have been named a Top 100 Hospital in America five times, and our Intensive Care Unit has been named a Top 100 ICU.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Families trust us to meet their needs, knowing that they have access to these Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Spine Care Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care * Women&#39;s &amp; Children&#39;s Center</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Join our friendly community hospital with its close-knit staff of caring professionals located just south of Tampa and discover how we care.</DIV>\n&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The Medical Surgical RN&nbsp;provides direct nursing care in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols.</DIV>','<DIV>Required Job Qualifications include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN</LI>\n<LI>Current BLS certification&nbsp;through the American Heart Association.</LI>\n<LI>Minimum 1 year previous experience as a RN in a Med/Surg setting.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI