lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=25558-2752','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=25558-2752',0,0,0,0,1311938199,1311938199),(273,9,5,'01384-4739','certified-or-tech-open-heart-ft-days-01384-4739',NULL,'Certified OR Tech Open Heart (FT Days)','United States-Florida-Brandon','Clincal Techs - CV Cath Lab Surg Vasc & Central Sterile',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>Brandon Regional Hospital is committed to providing our patients and their families with compassionate care. For more than 30 years our busy, 407-bed acute care facility has been dedicated to quality and devoted to our community. We have been named a Top 100 Hospital in America five times, and our Intensive Care Unit has been named a Top 100 ICU.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Families trust us to meet their needs, knowing that they have access to these Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Spine Care Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care * Women&#39;s &amp; Children&#39;s Center</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Join our friendly community hospital with its close-knit staff of caring professionals located just south of Tampa and discover how we care.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The Operating Room Technician assists in nursing care and preparation of surgical patient by performance of routine and delegated duties, according to standards and policies of the center.&nbsp; Is responsible for assisting the surgeon, helping in the central sterile processing department, restocking and changing over rooms between procedures.&nbsp; Performs housekeeping duties as necessary and assists in maintenance of all supplies.&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>\n</DIV>','<DIV>Job Requirements:&nbsp;</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>High School Diploma/GED</LI>\n<LI>Surgical&nbsp;Tech Certification required.</LI>\n<LI>Minimum 1 year of previous experience as a OR Tech required, Previous experience in CVOR preferred.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>BLS Certification required through the American Heart Association.</LI>\n<LI>Excellent communication skills.</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>At HCA West and Central Florida&#39;s 15 hospitals we&#39;re not just caregivers, we&#39;re devoted to caring. Located throughout Tampa, St. Petersburg, Sarasota and the greater Orlando area, we&#39;re on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients. As an integral part of the nation&#39;s largest healthcare system with more than 15,000 healthcare professionals on our team, we foster an environment where you will be supported, valued and encouraged to grow.</DIV>\n<DIV>Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to www.MoreCareerChoices.com.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The Comprehensive Hospital System Serving West &amp; Central Florida</DIV>\n<DIV>Blake Medical Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Brandon Regional Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Central Florida Regional Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Community Hospital of New Port Richey</DIV>\n<DIV>Doctors Hospital of Sarasota</DIV>\n<DIV>Edward White Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Englewood Community Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Fawcett Memorial Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Largo Medical Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Northside Hospital &amp; Tampa Bay Heart Institute</DIV>\n<DIV>Oak Hill Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Osceola Regional Medical Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point</DIV>\n<DIV>South Bay Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>St. Petersburg General Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>EOE</DIV>\n<DIV><BR/>\n&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11016/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-4739','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11016/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-4739',0,0,0,0,1311938201,1311939720),(274,9,5,'25558-3799','rn-behavioral-health-prn-25558-3799',NULL,'RN Behavioral Health (PRN)','United States-Florida-Largo','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>The Behavioral Health RN manages the nursing care of patients in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Performs initial and on-going physical and psychosocial assessment according to accepted standards of nursing practice.</LI>\n<LI>Assesses plans and evaluates patient care needs.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Carries out physician orders.</LI>\n<LI>Administers prescribed medications, changes dressings, cleans wounds, monitors vital signs.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in treatment team conferences to assist in planning and revising goals, objectives and interventions appropriate to the age-related and problem-specific needs of each patient.</LI>\n<LI>Implements nursing plan of care for assigned patients and conducts and/or co-leads group therapy sessions for patients.</LI>\n<LI>Evaluates patient&#39;s response to interventions and revises nursing plan of care as needed.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Collaborates with the treatment team to revise goals, objectives and interventions appropriate to the changes in patient status.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Instructs and educates patients and families.</LI>\n<LI>Assesses and coordinates patient&#39;s discharge planning needs with members of the healthcare team.</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN.</LI>\n<LI>Current American Heart Association Certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider.</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI>Minimum of 2 years Psych&nbsp;acute care experience preferred.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=25558-3799','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=25558-3799',0,0,0,0,1311938203,1311938203),(275,9,5,'01323-3135','cardiovascular-tech-i-prn-01323-3135',NULL,'Cardiovascular Tech I (PRN)','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Clincal Techs - CV Cath Lab Surg Vasc & Central Sterile',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>Specializes in invasive cardiovascular/radiology technology, providing expertise, knowledge and skills in performing cardiac angiographic procedures in a Cath Lab environment.&nbsp; Adheres to hospital/departmental policies and procedures.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<DIV>Graduate of an accredited School of Cardiovascular Technology and one year recent scrub experience in a Cath Lab or Radiology special procedures preferred.&nbsp; One year recent scrub experience in an interventional Cath Lab preferred.&nbsp; Completion of a Basic EKG and Hemodynamics preferred.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current CPR and ACLS certifications thru&nbsp;American Heart Association</LI>\n<LI>RCVT or RCIS preferred.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3135','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3135',0,0,0,0,1311938205,1311938205),(276,9,5,'00327-2630','monitor-technician-3w-tele-ft-nights-00327-2630',NULL,'Monitor Technician (3W Tele) FT Nights','United States-Florida-Sanford','Nursing Support',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>The Certified Monitor Tech&nbsp;monitors patients&#39; EKG waveforms in a centralized monitoring station.&nbsp;&nbsp;</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<DIV>Duties and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<DIV><BR/>\n<UL>\n<LI><SPAN>Interprets Rhythms and Arrhythmias.</SPAN></SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Reports all changes in heart rate/rhythm to appropriate nursing staff.</SPAN></SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Maintains Telemetry Supplies.</SPAN></SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Records patient condition utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</SPAN></SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Performs duties with full understanding of&nbsp; related age specific factors.</SPAN></SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Orients and mentors new staff members.</SPAN></SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</SPAN></SPAN></LI>\n</UL>\n</DIV>','<DIV>Qualifications include:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum of a high school degree or equivalent required.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; BLS through the American Heart Association required upon hire.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Previous clerical experience and CMT/cardiac experienced preferred.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Previous experience as a monitor tech in a hospital setting required.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong customer service skills required.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiarity with medical terminology is desired.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Computer literacy is required.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Completion of basic EKG/Arrhythmia course.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-2630','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-2630',0,0,0,0,1311938208,1311938208),(277,9,5,'00144-3758','physical-therapist-prn-weekdays-weekends-00144-3758',NULL,'Physical Therapist (PRN) Weekdays Weekends','United States-Florida-Largo','Therapy & Rehabilitation',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>In accordance with&nbsp; physicians orders,&nbsp; the Physical Therapist assesses, evaluates, plans, and carries out physical therapy programs to restore maximum reasonable function and to minimize disability following disease, injury, or genetically acquired disabilities.&nbsp; Position tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Plans and uses therapies involving physical exercise, massage, heat, water, light and electricity.</LI>\n<LI>Utilizes various mechanical and electrical equipment and prosthetic and orthotic devices.</LI>\n<LI>Evaluates, records and reports on patient&#39;s response to treatment and progress toward identified goals.</LI>\n<LI>Integrates physical therapy treatments with other aspects of patient care.</LI>\n<LI>Assists patients reach their maximal reasonably levels of function and to cope with their limitations.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Instructs and educates patients and families.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in patient discharge planning.</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>Experience a higher degree of patient care at Largo Medical Center, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system. Our 456-bed acute care hospital is located on two campuses-in mid-Pinellas County on the West Coast of Florida, providing medical care for the residents of Largo, and the nearby cities of Clearwater, Seminole, St. Petersburg and the Gulf Beach communities. We are the only area hospital with all private patient rooms.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>We offer career growth, top technologies, and these Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center with PCI *Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Spine &amp; Neuro Center * Breast Center * Cancer Care</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>See how we care and you will experience a supportive environment, great people and a wide array of unique services. &nbsp;Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>. &nbsp;EOE</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of Physical Therapy.</LI>\n<LI>B.S. or M.S. in Physical Therapy.</LI>\n<LI>State licensure as a Physical Therapist.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider (American Heart Association).</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11011/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-3758','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11011/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-3758',0,0,0,0,1311938210,1311939148),(278,9,5,'00144-4968','manager-cardiac-surgery-unit-and-neuro-icu-00144-4968',NULL,'Manager Cardiac Surgery Unit and Neuro ICU','United States-Florida-Largo','Nursing Mgmt & Admin',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV><SPAN><STRONG>Bring&nbsp;your vision for the future and strong customer service focus to the leadership&nbsp;our Cardiac Surgery Unit and Neuroscience ICU.&nbsp;&nbsp;At Largo Medical,&nbsp; you will play an</STRONG> <STRONG>active role&nbsp; in developing&nbsp; patient satisfaction and serving our community.&nbsp; We are an osteopathic teaching hospital with a strong emphasis on education.&nbsp; You will be part of a progressive division organization that values innovation and constant improvement.&nbsp;&nbsp;</STRONG></SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV><SPAN>NSICU is a newer unit that opened last June for our complex spine surgeries and neuro surgical patients.&nbsp; Fabulous staff that desire that strong leader to encourage teamwork and develop the unit further.</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV><SPAN>CSU is a strong cardiovascular surgical unit (post open hearts) with tenured staff.&nbsp; All staff are required to undergo a stringent open heart training program and receive specialty pay.</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV><SPAN>Both units have wonderful staff!</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>CSU - 10 beds, NSICU - 10 Beds&nbsp;&nbsp; 40 plus FTE &#39;s</DIV>\n<DIV>Staffing ratio - 1:2 typically</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;The Nursing manager demonstrates twenty-four hour responsibility and accountability for nursing practice, and quality of care and services within assigned departments. Ensures assessment and care is appropriate and patient specific and documented in a timely, accurate and complete manner.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West Florida we are on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients; their families and the communities we serve.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Rich Moore</DIV>\n<DIV>Lead Nurse Recruiter</DIV>\n<DIV><A HREF=\"mailto:richard.moore2@hcahealthcare.com\">richard.moore2@hcahealthcare.com</A></DIV>\n<DIV>Referrals are always appreciated.</DIV>','<DIV>BSN required MS preferred</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>3 years Critical Care&nbsp;management experience required</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>CCRN (or be willing to obtain).</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>Special requirement - MUST have taken open hearts and some knowledge of neuro required.&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11011/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-4968','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11011/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-4968',0,0,0,0,1311938212,1311939155),(279,9,5,'00144-404LMC','rn-surgical-services-operating-room-prn-00144-404lmc',NULL,'RN Surgical Services Operating Room PRN','United States-Florida-Largo','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P>The Operating Room RN provides nursing care in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</P><UL><LI>Assesses, plans and evaluates the nursing care needs of the patient before, during and after a surgical procedure. </LI><LI>Provides nursing care to the patient undergoing surgical procedures. </LI><LI>Provides comfort and support for pre-operative patients. </LI><LI>Participates in the care of patients receiving conscious sedation. </LI><LI>Carries out physician orders. </LI><LI>Administers prescribed medications, applies dressings, monitors vital signs. </LI><LI>Assists physician during procedures. </LI><LI>Maintains aseptic techniques and actively monitors situations which could lead to breaches in aseptic technique. </LI><LI>Coordinates the operating room with respect to sterility, cleanliness, availability of functioning equipment and supplies.&nbsp; </LI><LI>Ensures the proper handling of specimens. </LI><LI>Serves as the primary coordinator of all disciplines for well coordinated patient care. </LI><LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp; </LI><LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care. </LI><LI>Orients and mentors new staff members. </LI><LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI></UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P><UL><LI>Current licensure as an RN. </LI><LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider. </LI><LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing. </LI><LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills. </LI><LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment. </LI><LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs. </LI></UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-404LMC','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-404LMC',0,0,0,0,1311938214,1311939908),(280,9,5,'00367-677','rn-emergency-services-prn-00367-677',NULL,'RN Emergency Services (PRN)','United States-Florida-St Petersburg','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>Emergency Department</DIV>\n<DIV>Founded in 1976, Edward White Hospital is a 167-bed facility located in the heart of South Pinellas County, Florida.&nbsp;&nbsp; Edward White Hospital is part of the HCA West Florida Division of Hospitals, a comprehensive network of hospitals, outpatient surgery and diagnostic imaging facilities, and a complete continuum of specialized healthcare programs that meet the healthcare needs of residents and businesses in West and Central Florida communities.&nbsp; Our parent company, HCA, is the nation&#39;s leading provider of healthcare services.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>As an Accredited Stroke Center by the Joint Commission, EWH is committed to ensuring our patients have access to the highest levels of emergency care available.&nbsp; Our <B>Emergency Department,</B> with 12 main ED beds and 5 &quot;Fast Track&quot; beds, offers exceptional 24-hour emergency care for the patients we serve.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Number of Staff: 25</LI>\n<LI>Skill Mix:&nbsp; RNs, Paramedics, Emergency Department Technicians, and Patient Care Techs</LI>\n<LI>Special Certifications Needed:&nbsp; ACLS, BLS</LI>\n<LI>Special Competencies/Skills Needed:&nbsp; Past experience in an acute care emergency department setting required</LI>\n<LI>Schedules:&nbsp; 12-hour shifts (varied hours 7-7, 9-9, 11-11);&nbsp; Full Time is considered 36 hours per week, including every other weekend</LI>\n<LI>Dress code:&nbsp; Tasteful scrubs (individual provides their own)</LI>\n<LI>Complete computerized charting through the Meditech System (&quot;Electronic Health Record&quot;) for patient assessment and care documentation; specific Emergency Department Module for documentation used; NIH Computerized Stroke Scale utilized</LI>\n<LI>Electronic medication administration record (eMAR) is used for the delivery of all medications provided to patients and has significantly reduced errors associated with the&nbsp; administration of medication hospital-wide</LI>\n<LI>Family atmosphere hospital where &quot;everybody knows your name&quot;</LI>\n<LI>Ratings! Ratings!! Ratings!!! --&nbsp; In the Top 15%&nbsp;of all of HCA (nationwide) for Employee satisfaction</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider through the American Heart Association.</LI>\n<LI>ACLS Certification required.</LI>\n<LI><EM><STRONG>Prior ED RN experience required.</STRONG></EM></LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00367-677','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00367-677',0,0,0,0,1311938217,1311938217),(281,9,5,'01377-928','speech-language-pathologist-prn-hospital-weekends-01377-928',NULL,'Speech Language Pathologist (PRN) Hospital Weekends','United States-Florida-Englewood FL','Therapy & Rehabilitation',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>The Speech Language Pathologist is responsible for planning and administering medically prescribed treatment programs for the rehabilitation of speech, language, cognitive and oral motor disorders.&nbsp; Job tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Counsels, educates and instructs patients and their families regarding their speech-language pathology treatment</LI>\n<LI>Demonstrates competency in rehabilitation procedures</LI>\n<LI>Maintains accurate patient records</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>At Englewood Community Hospital we work hard to contribute to the health of our patients by ensuring the happiness of our people. As part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system, we focus on your needs while providing excellent care to our patients. Our intimate 100-bed hospital has earned major accolades for our Orthopedic, Stroke and Cardiac achievements. We are also an accredited Chest Pain Center offering many \"big-city\" services to our patients.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Discover how we care in our vibrant, beachfront community where the patient and our community always come first.&nbsp; Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>. EOE</DIV>\n<DIV><BR/>\n</DIV>','<P>Job qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Masters Degree in Speech Language Pathology required.</LI>\n<LI>Must be currently licensed by the state as a Speech Language Pathologist</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider required (American Heart Association).</LI>\n<LI>Previous experience in an acute care hospital setting required.</LI>\n<LI>Requires strong communication and interpersonal skills.</LI>\n<LI>Must be able to work in a fast-paced environment.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01377-928','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01377-928',0,0,0,0,1311938219,1311939557),(282,9,5,'00367-1285','rn-medical-surgical-medical-unit-full-time-days-experience-required-00367-1285',NULL,'RN Medical Surgical (Medical Unit) Full Time Days Experience Required','United States-Florida-St Petersburg','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>Medical/Surgical Nursing Department</SPAN></SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV>Founded in 1976, Edward White Hospital is a 167-bed facility located in the heart of South Pinellas County, Florida.&nbsp;&nbsp; Edward White Hospital is part of the HCA West Florida Division of Hospitals, a comprehensive network of hospitals, outpatient surgery and diagnostic imaging facilities, and a complete continuum of specialized healthcare programs that meet the healthcare needs of residents and businesses in West and Central Florida communities.&nbsp; Our parent company, HCA, is the nation&#39;s leading provider of healthcare services.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Our patient profile ranges from a diabetic care patient to one who&#39;s just undergone an elective surgery.&nbsp; Our Medical/Surgical Nursing Department consists of two units/floors:&nbsp; the 6<SUP>th</SUP> floor medical unit consists of 36 beds (semi-private and private rooms) and the 5<SUP>th</SUP> floor surgical unit consists of 19 beds (all private rooms).&nbsp; Each unit has its own dedicated staff.&nbsp; The Medical/Surgical Nursing staff is committed to the care of the general medical and post-op surgical patients we serve.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV><I>At EWH, we utilize complete computerized charting (&quot;Electronic Health Record&quot;) for our patient assessment and care documentation.&nbsp; We also utilize eMAR, our electronic medication administration record for the delivery of all medications provided to our patients, which has significantly reduced errors associated when administering medications.&nbsp;</I>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Number of Staff: 40</LI>\n<LI>Skill Mix:&nbsp; RN, LPN, Unit Secretary, CNA, Student Nurse</LI>\n<LI>Major Equipment Used:&nbsp; IV pumps, IVAC, Dinamaps, Dopplers, Lifting Equipment, Accu-Check, Omni-Cell, Crash Cart, Feeding pumps, etc.</LI>\n<LI>Special Certifications Needed:&nbsp; BLS required, ACLS preferred</LI>\n<LI>Special Skills or Competencies Needed:&nbsp; Prior nursing experience, preferable in an acute care setting; critical thinker, positive attitude, organized, team player, eager to learn and teach others; Orthopedic experience desired</LI>\n<LI>Schedules:&nbsp; 12-hour shifts (7-7)&nbsp; Full Time is considered 36 hours per week, including every other weekend; Self-scheduling is available</LI>\n<LI>Dress code:&nbsp; Professional scrubs (individual provides their own)</LI>\n<LI>Designated Charge Nurse who DOES NOT regularly take an assignment</LI>\n<LI>Lifting equipment available:&nbsp; Opera, Encore, Maxislides, Z-slides</LI>\n<LI>Family atmosphere hospital where &quot;everybody knows your name&quot;</LI>\n<LI>Ratings! Ratings!! Ratings!!! --&nbsp; In the Top 15%&nbsp;of all of HCA (nationwide) for Employee satisfaction</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN in Florida.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider through the American Heart Association.</LI>\n<LI>Prior RN experience in an acute care medical/surgical nursing department desired.</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00367-1285','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00367-1285',0,0,0,0,1311938224,1311939917),(283,9,5,'01384-5002','director-cath-lab-registered-nurse-01384-5002',NULL,'Director Cath Lab Registered Nurse','United States-Florida-Brandon','Nursing Mgmt & Admin',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV><SPAN>Bring&nbsp;your vision for the future and strong customer service focus to the leadership&nbsp;of our Cardiac Cath department .&nbsp; Develop your multi-unit leadership with responsibility for&nbsp;Cardiac Cath, EP and Intervential Radiology.&nbsp;&nbsp;You will thrive in our 6 suite&nbsp;Cath Lab&nbsp;unit performing the full spectrum of catheter based interventions, Peripheral and Coronary.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You will also be part of a progressive division organization that values innovation and constant improvement.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;\n\n<DIV>Brandon Regional Hospital is committed to providing our patients and their families with compassionate care. For more than 30 years our busy, 407-bed acute care facility has been dedicated to quality and devoted to our community. We have been named a Top 100 Hospital in America five times, and our Intensive Care Unit has been named a Top 100 ICU.</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;The Nursing Director demonstrates twenty-four hour responsibility and accountability for nursing practice, and quality of care and services within assigned departments. Ensures assessment and care is appropriate and patient specific and documented in a timely, accurate and complete manner.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West Florida we are on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients; their families and the communities we serve.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Rich Moore</DIV>\n<DIV>Lead Nurse Recruiter</DIV>\n<DIV><A HREF=\"mailto:richard.moore2@hcahealthcare.com\">richard.moore2@hcahealthcare.com</A></DIV>\n<DIV>Referrals are always appreciated.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Associate Degree/Diploma. &nbsp;Bachelor&#39;s Degree is preferred.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>','<P>Bachelors degree in Nursing required;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Masters a plus</P>\n<P>Licensed RN</P>\n<P>Coronary experience required,&nbsp; Open Heart facility experience preferred</P>\n<DIV>Three - five years&nbsp;hospital leadership experience.&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>BLS /ACLS certification</DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11011/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-5002','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11011/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-5002',0,0,0,0,1311938226,1311939181),(284,9,5,'01384-5125','clinical-pharmacist-evenings-hospital-experience-residency-preferred-join-our-dynamic-pharmacy-team-01384-5125',NULL,'Clinical Pharmacist (Evenings) Hospital Experience Residency preferred Join our Dynamic Pharmacy Team ','United States-Florida-Brandon','Pharmacy & Pharmacy Tech',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV>The Clinical Pharmacist&nbsp;will work&nbsp;primarily based in the patient care area and will include some operational coverage.&nbsp;&nbsp;Succesful candidate will&nbsp;participate in&nbsp;key clinical initiatives and focus on areas of expertise. Tasks include consistent documentation of clinical interventions, rounding with medical staff, attending care management rounds, involvement in P&amp;T Committee i.e. presentations, data collection for medication use evaluations, acting as preceptor/mentor for Pharmacy students. Requires outstanding written and verbal communication skills, ability to converse with medical staff and healthcare providers.\n\n <DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp; Additional duties include:\n\n <UL>\n<LI>Maintains strong knowledge of hospital policies and government regulations and dispenses accordingly.</LI>\n<LI>Consults with physicians and nursing staff regarding patient reactions, errors and complaints.</LI>\n<LI>Determines and consults on possible drug interactions.</LI>\n<LI>Assists in the supervision and training of pharmacy technician personnel.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in Drug Utilization Review.</LI>\n<LI>Assists with quality improvement initiatives, inventory and ordering of pharmaceuticals.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Utilizes knowledge of age specific needs of patient in performance of duties and responsibilities.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>\n</DIV>\n</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of a college of Pharmacy accredited by the American Council on Pharmacy Education.</LI>\n<LI>BS or Pharm.D degree; Residency preferred; recent hospital experience</LI>\n<LI>State of Florida&nbsp;licensure as a Pharmacist.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11014/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-5125','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11014/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-5125',0,0,0,0,1311938228,1311938630),(285,9,5,'00642-1496','rn-case-manager-prn-00642-1496',NULL,'RN Case Manager (PRN)','United States-Florida-Sun City Center','Case Management',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>&nbsp;\n\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">South Bay Hospital is situated in the beautiful Sun City Center, serving one of the fasted growing areas in the state. Close to beaches and Florida attractions, our growing 125-bed acute care hospital offers a full spectrum of healthcare services, including:</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">Emergency</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Inpatient/Outpatient Surgery</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;* Orthopedics</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Vascular</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Wound Care Center</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">Job Requirements:</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</P>\n<UL CLASS=\"noindent\">\n<LI>Current Florida RN license.</LI>\n<LI>Minimum&nbsp;3 years of clinical nursing experience.</LI>\n<LI>Knowledge of CMS guidelines and experience working with payor specific guidelines and contractual rules preferred.</LI>\n<LI>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">To learn more about South Bay Hospital please visit: www.MoreCareerChoices.com</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</SPAN></P>\n</LI>\n</UL>\n</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current Florida RN license.</LI>\n<LI>Minimum&nbsp;3 years of clinical nursing experience.</LI>\n<LI>Knowledge of CMS guidelines and experience working with payor specific guidelines and contractual rules preferred.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision meeting firm deadlines.</LI>\n<LI>Assertive and persuasive communication skills, action oriented.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00642-1496','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00642-1496',0,0,0,0,1311938230,1311939562),(286,9,5,'01323-2321','rn-overflow-prn-01323-2321',NULL,'RN Overflow (PRN)','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>The Overflow RN provides direct nursing care in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include taking care of various types of &nbsp;patients from Medical, to Intermediate to Cardiac.</DIV>','<UL>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Current FL RN license</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Current BLS and ACLS certifications thru American Heart Association</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Previous Telemetry experience preferred</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>Proficient in EKG is a must</LI>\n<LI>2 years previous experience in Med/Surg Tele</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-2321','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-2321',0,0,0,0,1311938232,1311938232),(287,9,5,'00311-3277','rn-quality-management-coordinator-00311-3277',NULL,'RN Quality Management Coordinator','United States-Florida-Hudson','Quality Risk & Safety',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point, part of the growing HCA West and Central Florida hospital system, has served Florida&#39;s Gulf Coast for the last 25 years. Our 290-bed facility boasts many awards and accolades, particularly for our work in cardiac care. Centers of Excellence here include:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Chest Pain Center * Stroke Center * Cancer Care Center * Spine Care Center</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Join us here in the suburbs- not far from Tampa- where you&#39;ll enjoy a friendly, close knit work environment and more fun in the sun!</DIV>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P><SPAN>Participates to</SPAN> <SPAN>maintain systematic data collection and flow of information between departments and into applicable committees.</SPAN> <SPAN>Assists in Core Measure data collection, analysis and trending as well as identification or organizational approaches to improve Core Measure performance results</SPAN></SPAN></P>','<P>Current&nbsp;FL RN state licensure<BR/>\n3-5 years hospital nursing experience; Quality Improvement experience is preferred<BR/>\nData analysis skills<BR/>\nStrong communication skills</P>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10141/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-3277','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10141/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-3277',0,0,0,0,1311938234,1311939022),(288,9,5,'01323-2356','rn-admin-pool-non-critical-care-01323-2356',NULL,'RN Admin Pool (Non Critical Care)','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV><B>Position Summary:&nbsp;</B> Assesses patient/family health problems and resources; takes a leadership role in the development, implementation and outcomes evaluation of a plan for nursing care provided by the nursing team.&nbsp; Provides technical nursing care and interventions to designated patient populations.&nbsp; This position requires providing service to one or more age populations including young adult through geriatric patient population in a manner that demonstrates an understanding of the functional/developmental age of the individual served.&nbsp; This position floats into several units within the facility.</DIV>','<UL>\n<LI>Current FL RN license</LI>\n<LI>Current&nbsp; BLS certifications thru American Heart Association</LI>\n<LI>1-3 years critical care experience preferred</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-2356','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-2356',0,0,0,0,1311938237,1311939838),(289,9,5,'00309-3037','coord-clerical-pre-post-op-interv-rec-ft-days-00309-3037',NULL,'Coord Clerical (Pre Post Op Interv Rec) FT Days','United States-Florida-Bradenton','Admitting Registration Clerical & Scheduling',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<UL>\n<LI>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>Under the direct supervision of the Director or clinical manager, the technical resource coordinator assists in planning, organizing, implementing and evaluating the activities occurring in the department.&nbsp; Responsible for scheduling procedures; collating charges; entering billing; care, upkeep, cleaning of equipment; maintenance of office equipment; ordering and maintaining inventory and supplies.&nbsp; Responsible for patient and schedule coordination, answering telephones and nurse call system.&nbsp; Coordination between preadmission nurses with close interactions between central patient scheduling, surgery center room, Anesthesia, and physicians&#39; offices.&nbsp; Performs above in accordance with the established Policies and Procedures of Blake Medical Center.</DIV>\n</DIV>\n</LI>\n</UL>','<UL>\n<LI>\n<DIV>High School Graduate/Equivalent.</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Ability to handle confidential information appropriately.&nbsp;</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Computer knowledge, good interpersonal skills.&nbsp;</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Good organizational skills.&nbsp;</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Ability to multi-task and work independently with minimum supervision.&nbsp;</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Detail oriented.&nbsp;</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Ability to effectively communicate.&nbsp;</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Tasks initiative.&nbsp;</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Ability to work and participate in a team environment within and across departments.</DIV>\n</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-3037','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-3037',0,0,0,0,1311938239,1311938239),(290,9,5,'00327-1951','certified-nursing-asst2-west-prn-00327-1951',NULL,'Certified Nursing Asst.(2 West) PRN','United States-Florida-Sanford','Nursing Support',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P>Working under the supervision of a nurse, the Patient Care Tech performs various patient care activities necessary in caring for the personal needs and comfort of patients.&nbsp; The position&#39;s tasks and responsibilities include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Bathes, dresses/undresses patients assist with personal hygiene.</LI>\n<LI>Serves and collects food trays.&nbsp; Assists with patient feeding.</LI>\n<LI>Transports, positions&nbsp; and drapes patients for exams and treatments.</LI>\n<LI>Assists patients in ambulating.</LI>\n<LI>Takes and records vital signs, weights and I &amp; O.</LI>\n<LI>Performs non sterile dressing changes.</LI>\n<LI>Passes and collects bed pans.</LI>\n<LI>Changes bed linens.</LI>\n<LI>Provides encouragement, support and comfort to patients and family members.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<DIV>Required Job Qualifications Include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>High School Graduate or equivalent required.</LI>\n<LI>American Heart Association (AHA) BLS Certifications&nbsp;is required</LI>\n<LI>Successful completion of a Nursing Assistant training program.</LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Certification as a Nurse Assistant and as a Patient Care Tech required</SPAN></LI>\n<LI>6-12 months C.N.A Experience required.</LI>\n<LI>Working knowledge of medical terminology.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Ability