n segments of the plan of care including proper use of wheelchairs, crutches, canes braces and prosthetic appliances and devices.</LI>\n<LI>Documents in computerized documentation system.&nbsp; Prepares correspondence and reports related to plan of care and patient progress.</LI>\n<LI>Directs activities of technicians, students, and volunteers as assigned.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in performance improvement and program development as assigned, to include but not limited to: data gathering, chart reviews, compilation of data into a report.</LI>\n<LI>Performs duties with full understanding of&nbsp; related age specific factors.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited Physical Therapy Assistant program</LI>\n<LI>State licensure as a Physical Therapy Assistant.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking and judgment particularly in determining when to inform the therapist of a significant change in the patients condition.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting patients and /or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3749','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3749',0,0,0,0,1311938378,1311938378),(349,9,5,'01384-5134','director-ortho-neuro-service-line-registered-nurse-01384-5134',NULL,'Director Ortho Neuro Service Line Registered Nurse','United States-Florida-Brandon','Directors & Managers',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV><SPAN>As the Director Ortho/Neuro&nbsp;Service Line; you will lead the development, implementation and facilitation of service l