torage of supplies.<BR/>\n&bull;&nbsp;Assembles patient charts.<BR/>\n&bull;&nbsp;Answers unit telephone, transferring calls, determining when staff members should be paged and taking and forwarding messages.<BR/>\n&bull;&nbsp;Serves as an important link in the communication chain ensuring information is transmitted between nursing personnel, other hospital personnel,&nbsp; physicians, patients, family members and other guests.<BR/>\n&bull;&nbsp;Assists in entering patient information in Meditech computer system.<BR/>\n&bull;&nbsp;Maintains nursing station in neat and orderly manner.<BR/>\n&bull;&nbsp;Completes special projects for unit director, supervisors and charge nurses.<BR/>\n&bull;&nbsp;Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.&nbsp;<BR/>\n&bull;&nbsp;Orients and mentors new staff members.</P>','<P>Required Qualifications include:<BR/>\n&bull;&nbsp;High school degree or equivalent<BR/>\n&bull;&nbsp;Previous clerical experience.<BR/>\n&bull;&nbsp;Previous experience as a Unit Secretary in a hospital setting preferred.<BR/>\n&bull;&nbsp;Strong customer service skills.<BR/>\n&bull;&nbsp;Familiarity with medical terminology.<BR/>\n&bull;&nbsp;Computer literacy is preferred.<BR/>\n&bull;&nbsp;Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching and some lifting.</P>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-2358','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-2358',0,0,0,0,1311938397,1311938397),(357,9,5,'01385-3673','rn-endoscopy-same-day-surgery-full-time-days-01385-3673',NULL,'RN Endoscopy Same Day Surgery Full Time Days','United States-Florida-St Petersburg','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV><SPAN><B><I>Northside</I></B> <B><I>Hospital</I></B></SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV><SPAN><EM><STRONG>Same Day Services and Endoscopy</STRONG></EM></SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV>Founded in 1976, Northside Hospital is a 288-bed facility located in the heart of South Pinellas County, Florida.&nbsp;&nbsp; Northside Hospital is part of the HCA West Florida Division of Hospitals, a comprehensive network of hospitals, outpatient surgery and diagnostic imaging facilities, and a complete continuum of specialized healthcare programs that meet the healthcare needs of residents and businesses in West and Central Florida communities.&nbsp; Our parent company, HCA, is the nation&#39;s leading provider of healthcare services.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>At Northside Hospital, we provide the highest quality of care in a warm, personalized setting for the patients we serve.&nbsp; We pride ourselves on both our professionalism and compassion. Our staff is comprised of dedicated professionals who have worked for Northside any length of time, ranging from 2 years to 28 years.&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Number of Staff:&nbsp; 16</LI>\n<LI>11 Total SDS/Pre-Op Beds</LI>\n<LI>2 GI Procedure Rooms</LI>\n<LI>Type of Procedures Performed: &nbsp;Assessment of Pre-op patients, monitoring of post-procedure GI and Radiology patients, Insertion of PICC lines, Assist with A-lines, Endoscopy cases</LI>\n<LI>500 SDS patients per month; 3-20 daily Endo procedures (bronchoscopy, EGD, ERCP, colonoscopy, polypectomy)</LI>\n<LI>Skill Mix:&nbsp; RNs, LPNs, Patient Transporters</LI>\n<LI>Major Equipment Used:&nbsp; Patient monitors, glucose monitors, ultrasound machine (for PICC lines), computers, IV pumps and supplies; video systems and endoscopes in Endoscopy</LI>\n<LI>Special Certifications Needed:&nbsp; BCLS certification required</LI>\n<LI>Special Competencies/Skills Needed:&nbsp; IV skills required</LI>\n<LI>Schedules:&nbsp; 8-10 hour shifts, Monday-Friday (with on-call requirements for PICC line insertion and Endoscopy teams)</LI>\n<LI>Dress code:&nbsp; Scrubs (individual provides their own)</LI>\n</UL>','<P>&lt;Flexible schedule with varied start times ranging from 5:30am, 7am, and 9am.&nbsp; Typical 8-hour shifts.&nbsp; Built around a 40-hour work week with on-call rotations.&gt;</SPAN></EM></P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN in the State of Florida.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS and ACLS Healthcare Provider certifications through the American Heart Association.&nbsp; NIHSS (National Institute of Health Stroke Scale) certification required--available online at <A HREF=\"http://www.strokeassociation.org\">www.strokeassociation.org</A>.</LI>\n<LI>Prior Endoscopy&nbsp;RN&nbsp;circulator experience&nbsp;desired; prior&nbsp;Endo&nbsp;scrub experience&nbsp;desired.&nbsp; Prior&nbsp;Pre-Op/Day Surgery Recovery/PACU RN experience desired.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01385-3673','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01385-3673',0,0,0,0,1311938399,1311939628),(358,9,5,'00327-2523','or-tech-certified-00327-2523',NULL,'OR Tech Certified','United States-Florida-Sanford','Clincal Techs - CV Cath Lab Surg Vasc & Central Sterile',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV>Provide safe and effective nursing care through the performance of specific duties as the Surgical Technician during surgical and or the procedures, under the direction of a Registered Nurse.&nbsp; Performs routine scrub as well as specifically delegated duties according to AORN standards, and established policies and procedures of the department of surgery.&nbsp; Assists in the maintenance of a safe environment for all.&nbsp; Keeps current with operating room techniques, procedures, instruments, supplies, and equipment; assists with the ongoing CQI program.</DIV>\n</DIV>','<DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of approved Surgical Technical Program</LI>\n<LI>Current BLS certification thru American Heart Association</LI>\n<LI>CST certification required</LI>\n<LI>Previous experience as Certified OR Tech is a plus</LI>\n</UL>\n</DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-2523','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-2523',0,0,0,0,1311938401,1311938401),(359,9,5,'00643-00011','rn-registered-nurse-oak-hill-hospital-brooksville-florida-00643-00011',NULL,'RN Registered Nurse Oak Hill Hospital Brooksville Florida','United States-Florida-Brooksville','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>&nbsp;</P>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN\n </LI><LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider. ACLS PALS NRP may be required in specific areas&nbsp;\n</LI><LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing. </LI></UL>\n<P>loney.moses@hcahealthcare.com</A></P>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-00011','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10140/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-00011',0,0,0,0,1311938404,1311939886),(360,9,5,'01323-3278','rn-picc-iv-therapy-prn-3100-per-hour-01323-3278',NULL,'RN PICC IV Therapy PRN $31.00 per hour','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P>The Operating Room RN provides nursing care in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</P><UL><LI>Assesses, plans and evaluates the nursing care needs of the patient before, during and after a surgical procedure. </LI><LI>Provides nursing care to the patient undergoing surgical procedures. </LI><LI>Provides comfort and support for pre-operative patients. </LI><LI>Participates in the care of patients receiving conscious sedation. </LI><LI>Carries out physician orders. </LI><LI>Administers prescribed medications, applies dressings, monitors vital signs. </LI><LI>Assists physician during procedures. </LI><LI>Maintains aseptic techniques and actively monitors situations which could lead to breaches in aseptic technique. </LI><LI>Coordinates the operating room with respect to sterility, cleanliness, availability of functioning equipment and supplies.&nbsp; </LI><LI>Ensures the proper handling of specimens. </LI><LI>Serves as the primary coordinator of all disciplines for well coordinated patient care. </LI><LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp; </LI><LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care. </LI><LI>Orients and mentors new staff members. </LI><LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI></UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P><UL><LI>Current licensure as an RN. </LI><LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider. </LI><LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing. </LI><LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills. </LI><LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment. </LI><LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs. </LI></UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3278','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3278',0,0,0,0,1311938406,1311938406),(361,9,5,'25558-3934','telecomm-operator-prn-3p-11p-11p-7p-25558-3934',NULL,'Telecomm Operator (PRN) 3p 11p 11p 7p','United States-Florida-Largo','Admitting Registration Clerical & Scheduling',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P>The PBX Operator responds to incoming calls in a timely manner and directs caller to appropriate destination providing a smooth, clear and professionally courteous communication practice.</P><UL><LI>Answers multiple incoming telephone lines. </LI><LI>Obtains necessary information and transfers calls to correct extensions. </LI><LI>Provides information to callers as appropriate.&nbsp;</LI><LI>Performs overhead paging.&nbsp;</LI><LI>Monitors all alarms located in PBX and notifies appropriate personnel as required.&nbsp;</LI><LI>Responds quickly and accurately to disaster and emergency situations as required, remaining calm.&nbsp;</LI><LI>Corrects and updates posted information as needed.&nbsp; Assists with the maintenance of directories on-call list, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;</LI><LI>Accurately utilizes the features of the PBX consoles, headsets, telephones and other related equipment.&nbsp;</LI><LI>Assist with maintaining cleanliness, safety and security of the PBX area.&nbsp;</LI><LI>Maintains confidentiality, security and integrity of patient and organizational data.&nbsp;</LI><LI>Ensures release of information is consistent with all privacy policies.&nbsp;</LI><LI>Orients and mentors new staff members. </LI></UL>','<UL><LI>Experience in customer service position. </LI><LI>Previous PBX experience is desirable.&nbsp;</LI><LI>Ability to fluently speak and understand English.&nbsp;</LI><LI>Previous experience in hospital setting preferred.&nbsp;</LI><LI>Ability to perform calmly, competently and quickly in emergency situations.&nbsp;</LI><LI>Customer service abilities.&nbsp;</LI><LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching and some lifting.<BR></LI></UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=25558-3934','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=25558-3934',0,0,0,0,1311938408,1311938408),(362,9,5,'00309-2267','rn-quality-specialist-prn-00309-2267',NULL,'RN Quality Specialist (PRN)','United States-Florida-Bradenton','Quality Risk & Safety',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P CLASS=\"MsoBodyTextIndent\">PRN Status: Hours may vary and scheduled on an as needed basis:</P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoBodyTextIndent\">&nbsp;</P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoBodyTextIndent\">**Weekend Hours Only**</P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoBodyTextIndent\">&nbsp;</P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoBodyTextIndent\">The <STRONG>PRN Quality Specialist</STRONG> is responsible for identification and concurrent monitoring of Core Measures patients; follow-up with clinical staff on resolution of outliers; may assist with retrospective abstraction.</P>','<UL>\n<LI>RN licensure required</LI>\n<LI>2 years recent experience in a hospital setting&nbsp;&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Meditech experience a plus</LI>\n<LI>&nbsp;Previous experience with Core Measures preferred.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-2267','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-2267',0,0,0,0,1311938413,1311939647),(363,9,5,'00144-4098','nursing-admin-supervisor-prn-registered-nurse-00144-4098',NULL,'Nursing Admin Supervisor (PRN) Registered Nurse','United States-Florida-Largo','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV><B>Largo</B> <B>Medical Center</B></DIV>\n<DIV>More choices.&nbsp; More career paths. More ways for you to express your passion for quality and expand your potential for success. Join us at Largo Medical Center, part of the growing HCA West Florida hospital system. We&#39;re located only ten minutes from the beautiful Gulf of Mexico beaches. Features at our 256-bed acute care facility include:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Spacious Emergency Department</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * 29 Private ED Treatment Rooms</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * State-Of-The-Art Surgery &amp; Ambulatory Care Center</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * 16 Private Pre-Op Rooms</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Four Endoscopic Suites</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Ten Multifunction Surgical Suites</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Two Dedicated Heart Surgery Suites</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>The Supervisor-Nursing/Administration will supervise and coordinate the operational and personnel activities throughout the facility.&nbsp; The Supervisor-Nursing/Administration will act as an administrative liaison for all departments for the defined shift for which he/she is responsible.&nbsp; The&nbsp;Supervisor recognizes that each patient is an individual to be treated with dignity and respect, and is also committed to being responsive to the needs of the patient&#39;s family or significant other.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;The Supervisor-Nursing/Administration combines the knowledge bases of nursing and management to make decisions and or recommendation relative to:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The delivery of responsive quality patient care based on the nursing process</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The assessment of unit staffing needs and the appropriate placement of nursing personnel.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The serving as a resource person and role model for all personnel.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The communication of identified problem situations to the Director of Nursing Services.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To promote continuity of hospital operations through the interpretation and enforcement of hospital policies and procedures.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Meets with patients, family members and other customers to discuss concerns and unmet needs.&nbsp; Coordinates the response.<BR/>\n<BR/>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manages the resolution of issues that arise during the course of the shift .Executes decisions in the absence of the Hospital Administrator.&nbsp; Determines need to contact Administrator on Call.<BR/>\n<BR/>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Evaluates issues and identifies trends.&nbsp; Communicates trends to hospital leadership and collaborates on problem solving to address trended issues.<BR/>\n<BR/>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Serves as the leader of the hospital safety plan in the absence of hospital administrators and other leaders.&nbsp; Includes coordinating the response to reported incidents including employee injuries.<BR/>\n&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Monitors and evaluates clinical standards within the Hospital.<BR/>\nEnsures that age and culturally appropriate care is given.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>This position will not include reimbursement for interview or relocation expenses.</DIV>\n</DIV>','Required Job Qualifications include:<BR/>\n&nbsp;Current licensure as an RN.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Minimum of&nbsp;5 years of clinical nursing experience.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Basic knowledge of main functional areas within the Hospital.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Minimum 2 years&nbsp;managerial experience in clinical nursing within hospital environment preferred.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment, strong communication skills and leadership abilities.<BR/>\n<BR/>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-4098','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-4098',0,0,0,0,1311938415,1311938415),(364,9,5,'00642-1521','certified-nursing-assistant-telemetry-f-t-days-wkend-rotate-00642-1521',NULL,'Certified Nursing Assistant Telemetry F T Days Wkend Rotate','United States-Florida-Sun City Center','Nursing Support',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>Working under the supervision of a nurse, the CNA/Patient Care Tech/Aide&nbsp;performs various patient care activities necessary in caring for the personal needs and comfort of patients.&nbsp; The position&#39;s tasks and responsibilities include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Bathes, dresses/undresses patients assist with personal hygiene.</LI>\n<LI>Serves and collects food trays.&nbsp; Assists with patient feeding.</LI>\n<LI>Transports, positions&nbsp; and drapes patients for exams and treatments.</LI>\n<LI>Assists patients in ambulating.</LI>\n<LI>Takes and records vital signs, weights and I &amp; O.</LI>\n<LI>Performs non sterile dressing changes.</LI>\n<LI>Passes and collects bed pans.</LI>\n<LI>Changes bed linens.</LI>\n<LI>Provides encouragement, support and comfort to patients and family members.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications Include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>High School Graduate or equivalent required.</LI>\n<LI>Current BLS certification&nbsp;through the <SPAN>American Heart Association</SPAN> required.</LI>\n<LI>Successful completion of a Nursing Assistant training program.</LI>\n<LI>Florida Certification as a Nurse Assistant required.</LI>\n<LI>Previous hospital related experience is desired.</LI>\n<LI>Working knowledge of medical terminology.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to quickly make decisions to report patient condition with minimal supervision.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00642-1521','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00642-1521',0,0,0,0,1311938417,1311938417),(365,9,5,'01323-3436','rn-cardiac-and-vascular-01323-3436',NULL,'RN Cardiac and Vascular','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'Assess patient/family health problems and resources; takes a leadership role in the development implementation and outcomes evaluation of a plan for nursing care provided by the nursing team.&nbsp; Provides technical nursing care and interventions to designated patient populations such as Surgical Cardio, Cardiac and Surgical vascular patients.','<UL>\n<LI>Current FL RN license</LI>\n<LI>Current BLS and ACLS thru American Heart Association</LI>\n<LI>Previous experience in Cath Lab recovery and Cardiac</LI>\n<LI>Experience in management of groins</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11011/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3436','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11011/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-3436',0,0,0,0,1311938419,1311939264),(366,9,5,'01384-4555','security-officer-unarmed-prn-01384-4555',NULL,'Security Officer Unarmed PRN','United States-Florida-Brandon','Facilities Mgmt Plant Ops & Security',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<UL>\n<LI CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">Must be knowledgeable of hospital security systems and procedures, local, state and federal codes/statutes, (related to safety and asset protection) OSHA, ACHA and JCAHO standards.&nbsp;</SPAN></LI>\n<LI CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">Must perform security &amp; safety duties.</SPAN></LI>\n</UL>','<P>Job Qualifications include:</SPAN></P>\n<UL>\n<LI><SPAN><SPAN>Class D Security license</SPAN></SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN><SPAN>Valid Florida driver&#39;s license&nbsp;</SPAN></SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN><SPAN>satisfactory driving record</SPAN></SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN><SPAN>2 years minimum&nbsp;security experience preferred</SPAN>&nbsp;</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN><SPAN>Good interpersonal and organizational skills</SPAN></SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Demonstrated leadership skills</SPAN></LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-4555','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-4555',0,0,0,0,1311938421,1311938421),(367,9,5,'00642-1045a','physical-therapy-assistant-licensed-prn-00642-1045a',NULL,'Physical Therapy Assistant (Licensed) PRN','United States-Florida-Sun City Center','Therapy & Rehabilitation',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>Under the supervision and direction of a licensed physical therapist, The Licensed Physical Therapy Assistant (LPTA) assists in the practice of physical therapy. Responsibilities and tasks include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Carries out treatment plans that have been established by a licensed physical therapist for inpatients and outpatients.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Directs and aids patients in therapeutic exercise, gait and functional training, applies therapeutic modalities, and performs other activities according to the plan of care established by the licensed physical therapist and as permitted by the State Board of Physical Therapy Examiners.</LI>\n<LI>Assists the physical therapist during patient testing, evaluations and complex procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Instructs patients on segments of the plan of care including proper use of wheelchairs, crutches, canes braces and prosthetic appliances and devices.</LI>\n<LI>Documents in computerized documentation system.&nbsp; Prepares correspondence and reports related to plan of care and patient progress.</LI>\n<LI>Directs activities of technicians, students, and volunteers as assigned.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in performance improvement and program development as assigned, to include but not limited to: data gathering, chart reviews, compilation of data into a report.</LI>\n<LI>Performs duties with full understanding of&nbsp; related age specific factors.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>Help deliver superior service to the patients at South Bay Hospital, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system. Our team strives to provide effective and efficient care in our 112-bed hospital, which will soon be joined by an all-new medical complex. With new communities breaking ground each year, this is an ideal location to experience our commitment to your career and our community.&nbsp; We support our talented staff with advanced technologies throughout our hospital and Centers of Excellence including:</DIV>\n<DIV>* Chest Pain Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>.&nbsp; EOE</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited Physical Therapy Assistant program</LI>\n<LI>State licensure as a Physical Therapy Assistant.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking and judgment particularly in determining when to inform the therapist of a significant change in the patients condition.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider (American Heart Association).</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting patients and /or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00642-1045a','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00642-1045a',0,0,0,0,1311938423,1311938423),(368,9,5,'00643-1566','transporter-prn-as-needed-schedule-00643-1566',NULL,'Transporter (PRN) As Needed Schedule','United States-Florida-Brooksville','Nursing Support',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV><SPAN>The Transporter is responsible for transporting patients and and equipment.&nbsp; Job tasks and responsibilities include:</SPAN></DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI><SPAN>Transport patients to and from clinical, ancillary and support areas as requested.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Assist clinical personnel in transferring patients to and from beds, wheelchairs or stretchers.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Greet and offer assistance to customers throughout the hospital.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Collect and deliver specimens, orders, requisitions and equipment to appropriate destinations.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.&nbsp;</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Orients and mentors new staff members.</SPAN></LI>\n</UL>','<DIV><SPAN>Job qualifications include:</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV><SPAN>&nbsp;</SPAN></DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI><SPAN>High school diploma or GED <STRONG>required.</STRONG></SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Current BLS Card (American&nbsp;Heart Association)&nbsp;is <STRONG>required</STRONG>.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>At least one year of related experience preferred.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Strong interpersonal and customer service skills <STRONG>required</STRONG>.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Able to work in a fast-paced environment.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.</SPAN></LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-1566','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-1566',0,0,0,0,1311938426,1311938426),(369,9,5,'25558-3995','certified-nursing-asst-prn-nights-med-surg-2-25558-3995',NULL,'Certified Nursing Asst (PRN) Nights Med Surg 2','United States-Florida-Largo','Nursing Support',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P>Working under the supervision of a nursing, the Certified Nursing Assistant performs various patient care activities 