taff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>Osceola Regional Medical Center, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system, has a proud tradition of providing excellent patient care in the Kissimmee area. Our 235-bed hospital offers the county\'s only Level II Neonatal and Open Heart programs and empowers its employees to strive for a higher standard of care. Several Centers of Excellence also highlight our clinical expertise:</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center with PCI * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Orthopedics &amp; Spine Care Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Experience our enhanced services and advanced technologies by joining a team of leading professionals. Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>.&nbsp; EOE</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of Occupational Therapy.</LI>\n<LI>B.S. or M.S. in Occupational Therapy.</LI>\n<LI>State licensure as an Occupational Therapist.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider (American Heart Association).</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-2287','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-2287',0,0,0,0,1311938442,1311938442),(375,9,5,'01323-2863','sterile-processing-tech-prn-01323-2863',NULL,'Sterile Processing Tech (PRN)','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Nursing Support',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>To provide aseptic supplies and equipment to be used in patient care by utilizing the proper processing of instrumentation and supplies, i.e. cleaning, sterilizing, storage, etc</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>&nbsp; Demonstrates proficiency in all dimensions of performance to align individual performance with organization goals and objectives.</LI>\n<LI>&nbsp;Adheres to established hospital and department guidelines &amp; protocols.&nbsp; Supports hospital mission, vision and values.</LI>\n<LI>&nbsp;Performs position specific job functions at an acceptable level.</LI>\n<LI>&nbsp;Able to manage stress appropriately</LI>\n<LI>&nbsp;Able to make decisions under pressure</LI>\n<LI>&nbsp;Able to manage anger/fear/hostility/violence of other appropriately</LI>\n<LI>&nbsp; Able to handle multiple priorities&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>&nbsp; Able to&nbsp;work alone</LI>\n</UL>','<UL>\n<LI>1 year experience required.</LI>\n<LI>American Heart Association (AHA) BLS certifications <SPAN>preferred</SPAN></LI>\n<LI>Excellent communication skills</LI>\n<LI>MEDITECH experience a plus</LI>\n<LI>Read/Comprehend Written Instructions</LI>\n<LI>High School Diploma/GED required</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-2863','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-2863',0,0,0,0,1311938444,1311938444),(376,9,5,'00144-4362','diet-clerk-prn-00144-4362',NULL,'Diet Clerk (PRN)','United States-Florida-Largo','Environmental Services',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>The Diet Clerk performs essential duties associated with the processing of menus and diet orders, patient information related to meal patterns, preferences, allergies, intolerance, religious or cultural food needs pertaining to the nutritional care and food service of all patients.&nbsp; Job tasks and responsibilities include:</SPAN></DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Assists&nbsp;dietitians in screening of all new admissions and obtaining food preferences.</SPAN></DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>Maintains cardexes and computer systems with accurate and current data.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI>Processes, modifies, collects and checks patient menus for each meal updating menus with most current information to assure compliance with dietary modifications and restrictions.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI>Participates in meal services and/or other production related duties as needed.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI></SPAN></LI>\n<LI>Maintains proactive and effective communication with dietary team.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Adheres to sanitation and safety standards&nbsp;(HACCP).</SPAN></LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Utilizes knowledge of age specific needs of patient in performance of duties and responsibilities.</SPAN></DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Orients and mentors new staff members</SPAN>.</DIV>\n</LI>\n</UL>','<DIV><SPAN>Job qualifications include:</SPAN></DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>High School Diploma/GED.</LI>\n<LI>Knowledge of basic principles of nutrition as related to modified diets preferred.</LI>\n<LI>1-2 years experience as a Diet Tech&nbsp;preferred.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to&nbsp;25 pounds.</LI>\n<LI>Strong customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform basic math functions.&nbsp;</SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></LI>\n<LI>Ability to handle multiple priorities.</SPAN></LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-4362','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-4362',0,0,0,0,1311938446,1311938446),(377,9,5,'01385-3733','monitor-technician-ft-days-pcu-ii-01385-3733',NULL,'Monitor Technician FT Days PCU II','United States-Florida-St Petersburg','Nursing Support',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>The Certified Monitor Tech&n