y, or genetically acquired disabilities.&nbsp; Position tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Plans and uses therapies involving physical exercise, massage, heat, water, light and electricity.</LI>\n<LI>Utilizes various mechanical and electrical equipment and prosthetic and orthotic devices.</LI>\n<LI>Evaluates, records and reports on patient&#39;s response to treatment and progress toward identified goals.</LI>\n<LI>Integrates physical therapy treatments with other aspects of patient care.</LI>\n<LI>Assists patients reach their maximal reasonably levels of function and to cope with their limitations.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Instructs and educates patients and families.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in patient discharge planning.</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of Physical Therapy.</LI>\n<LI>B.S. or M.S. in Physical Therapy.</LI>\n<LI>State licensure as a Physical Therapist.</LI>\n<LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider (American Heart Association).</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11011/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-3024','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11011/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-3024',0,0,0,0,1311938501,1311939188),(398,9,5,'00367-750','rn-case-manager-prn-00367-750',NULL,'RN Case Manager PRN','United States-Florida-St Petersburg','Case Management',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>Join us at Edward White Hospital, part of the growing HCA Wes Florida hospital system. Our 167-bed hospital is situated just minutes from downtown St. Petersburg and its beautiful waterfront. In addition to the best of locations, we also offer a full-range of important extras that support clinical excellence including:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>* Tuition Reimbursement Plan</DIV>\n<DIV>* In-House Staff Development &amp; Education Department</DIV>\n<DIV>* Internship Programs</DIV>\n<DIV>* Preceptorship &amp; Mentorship Programs</DIV>\n<DIV>* Career Ladder Initiatives &amp; More</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>As an integral part of the nation&#39;s largest healthcare system, HCA West Florida hospitals give employees more support than you can possibly imagine. Each of our 13 hospitals is fully equipped with the latest technology and the greatest resources, so you can provide the highest quality care possible. In return for your dedication, we offer a generous benefits package, tuition reimbursement and professional learning opportunities. Plus a lot of extra incentives that make life much more rewarding.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>To learn more about Edward White Hospital please visit: www.MoreCareerChoices.com</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.&nbsp; Bachelor&#39;s of Science in Nursing preferred.</LI>\n<LI>CCM preferred&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Minimum 5 years of clinical nursing experience.</LI>\n<LI>Knowledge of CMS guidelines and experience working with payor specific guidelines and contractual rules preferred.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision meeting firm deadlines.</LI>\n<LI>Assertive and persuasive communication skills, action oriented.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10141/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00367-750','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10141/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00367-750',0,0,0,0,1311938503,1311939035),(399,9,5,'00144-0157','pharmacist-reg-prn-infectious-disease-antibiotic-stewardship-exper-00144-0157',NULL,'Pharmacist (Reg) PRN Infectious Disease Antibiotic Stewardship Exper.','United States-Florida-Largo','Pharmacy & Pharmacy Tech',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>Following physicians&#39; orders, the Registerd Pharmacist compounds and dispenses medications and other pharmaceuticals.&nbsp; Position tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Maintains strong knowledge of hospital policies and government regulations and dispenses accordingly.</LI>\n<LI>Consults with physicians and nursing staff regarding patient reactions, errors and complaints.</LI>\n<LI>Determines and consults on possible drug interactions.</LI>\n<LI>Assists in the supervision and training of pharmacy technician personnel.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in Drug Utilization Review.</LI>\n<LI>Assists with quality improvement initiatives, inventory and ordering of pharmaceuticals.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Utilizes knowledge of age specific needs of patient in performance of duties and responsibilities.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>Experience a higher degree of patient care at Largo Medical Center, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system. Our 456-bed acute care hospital is located on two campuses-in mid-Pinellas County on the West Coast of Florida, providing medical care for the residents of Largo, and the nearby cities of Clearwater, Seminole, St. Petersburg and the Gulf Beach communities. We are the only area hospital with all private patient rooms.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>We offer career growth, top technologies, and these Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center with PCI *Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Spine &amp; Neuro Center * Breast Center * Cancer Care</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>See how we care and you will experience a supportive environment, great people and a wide array of unique services. &nbsp;Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>. &nbsp;EOE</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of a college of Pharmacy accredited by the American Council on Pharmacy Education.</LI>\n<LI>BS or Pharm.D degree.</LI>\n<LI>State licensure as a Pharmacist.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-0157','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-0157',0,0,0,0,1311938506,1311938506),(400,9,5,'00327-2601','arnp-cardiovascular-services-00327-2601',NULL,'ARNP Cardiovascular Services','United States-Florida-Sanford','Physicians Physicians Assistants & Extenders',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>Position Summary:</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>This position will provide care for Cardiovascular surgery patients; responsible for rounding with the CV surgeon; enters data into STS data registry; conduct education on the open heart step down unit and chest tube education for new Graduate Nurses; and possibly with setting up a u nit/process for our Chest Pain Observation patients.</P>','<P>Position Requirements:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current FL ARNP license</LI>\n<LI>Current BLS and ACLS certification thru American Heart Association</LI>\n<LI>Masters Degree</LI>\n<LI>Minimum 5 years experience as RN with 1-3 years in CVICU</LI>\n<LI>Certification for prescriptive privileges</LI>\n</UL>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-2601','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-2601',0,0,0,0,1311938509,1311938509),(401,9,5,'00643-2659','operating-room-asst-prn-as-needed-schedule-00643-2659',NULL,'Operating Room Asst (PRN) As Needed Schedule','United States-Florida-Brooksville','Nursing Support',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P>The Operating Roomy under the supervision of the Registered Nurse transports patients to and from the perioperative area as needed.&nbsp; He/she is responsible for maintaining the surgical suites in a clean, safe and organized condition, assist in moving and positioning patients, and maintain supplies.&nbsp;&nbsp; He/she will also transport specimens, lab and pharmacy items, and equipment to and from surgery and other departments. The orderly assumes the responsibility for performing assignments in a timely and conscientious manner.&nbsp; He/she is responsible for ensuring effective communication with the circulator, the patient, the surgeon and other members of the surgical team. The quality of work will be in keeping with the philosophy, objectives and policies of the hospital and the Department of Nursing.</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>','<P>EDUCATION<BR/>\nHigh school graduate or equivalent</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>EXPERIENCE<BR/>\nMinimum one-year\'s experience in environmental services preferred<BR/>\nWorking knowledge of operating room environment<BR/>\n</P>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-2659','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-2659',0,0,0,0,1311938512,1311938512),(402,9,5,'01384-4601','rn-pcu-neuroscience-center-prn-01384-4601',NULL,'RN PCU Neuroscience Center (PRN)','United States-Florida-Brandon','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV>Brandon Regional Hospital is committed to providing our patients and their families with compassionate care. For more than 30 years our busy, 407-bed acute care facility has been dedicated to quality and devoted to our community. We have been named a Top 100 Hospital in America five times, and our Intensive Care Unit has been named a Top 100 ICU.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Families trust us to meet their needs, knowing that they have access to these Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Spine Care Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care * Women&#39;s &amp; Children&#39;s Center</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Join our friendly community hospital with its close-knit staff of caring professionals located just south of Tampa and discover how we care.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>The&nbsp;RN in the&nbsp;Neuroscience Center&nbsp;Progressive Care Unit manages the nursing care of patients in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Assesses plans and evaluates patient care needs.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Carries out physician orders.</LI>\n<LI>Administers prescribed medications, changes dressings, cleans wounds, monitors vital signs.</LI>\n<LI>Provides respiratory and ventilator management and monitoring for patients.</LI>\n<LI>Serves as the primary coordinator of all disciplines for well coordinated patient care.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Instructs and educates patients and families.</LI>\n<LI>Assesses and coordinates patient&#39;s discharge planning needs with members of the healthcare team.</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required</LI>\n</UL>','<DIV>Required Job Qualifications include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN.</LI>\n<LI>Current BLS and ACLS certification&nbsp;through the American Heart Association.</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI>NIH Stroke Certification a plus, but training provided if necessary.</LI>\n<LI>Previous experience as a RN in a hospital setting&nbsp;required.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West and Central Florida&#39;s 15 hospitals we&#39;re not just caregivers, we&#39;re devoted to caring. Located throughout Tampa, St. Petersburg, Sarasota and the greater Orlando area, we&#39;re on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients. As an integral part of the nation&#39;s largest healthcare system with more than 15,000 healthcare professionals on our team, we foster an environment where you will be supported, valued and encouraged to grow.<BR/>\n<BR/>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to www.MoreCareerChoices.com.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The Comprehensive Hospital System Serving West &amp; Central Florida</DIV>\n<DIV>Blake Medical Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Brandon Regional Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Central Florida Regional Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Community Hospital of New Port Richey</DIV>\n<DIV>Doctors Hospital of Sarasota</DIV>\n<DIV>Edward White Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Englewood Community Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Fawcett Memorial Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Largo Medical Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Northside Hospital &amp; Tampa Bay Heart Institute</DIV>\n<DIV>Oak Hill Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>Osceola Regional Medical Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point</DIV>\n<DIV>South Bay Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>St. Petersburg General Hospital</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>EOE</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV><BR/>\n<BR/>\n&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV><BR/>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;<BR/>\n<BR/>\n<BR/>\n</DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-4601','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-4601',0,0,0,0,1311938518,1311938518),(403,9,5,'00144-4924','director-cath-lab-registered-nurse-00144-4924',NULL,'Director Cath Lab Registered Nurse','United States-Florida-Largo','Nursing Mgmt & Admin',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;\n\n<DIV><SPAN>Bring&nbsp;your vision for the future and strong customer service focus to the leadership of our Cardiac Cath Lab&nbsp;.&nbsp; At our 2 campus Largo Medical Center, you will play an active role&nbsp; in developing&nbsp; patient satisfaction and serving our community.&nbsp; You will lead a high tech department performing 5000 Echo&#39;s, 2100 Catheterizations, and 700 EP&#39;s&nbsp;annually.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;You will be part of a progressive division organization that values innovation and constant improvement.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</SPAN></DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The Nursing Director demonstrates twenty-four hour responsibility and accountability for nursing practice, and quality of care and services within assigned departments. Ensures assessment and care is appropriate and patient specific and documented in a timely, accurate and complete manner.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West Florida we are on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients; their families and the communities we serve.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Rich Moore</DIV>\n<DIV>Lead Nurse Recruiter</DIV>\n<DIV><A HREF=\"mailto:richard.moore2@hcahealthcare.com\">richard.moore2@hcahealthcare.com</A></DIV>\n<DIV>Referrals are always appreciated.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<DIV>Fl Nursing license or ability to obtain prior to start</DIV>\n<DIV>Associate Degree/Diploma. &nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Bachelor&#39;s Degree and Master&#39;s Degree preferred</DIV>\n<DIV>Minimum three - five years nursing leadership experience as a Cath Lab Director&nbsp;in an Interventional Cath Lab.&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Three years previous clinical experience as an RN in a cath lab.</DIV>\n<DIV>BLS /ACLS certification .</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11011/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-4924','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11011/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-4924',0,0,0,0,1311938522,1311939230),(404,9,5,'01371-2807','rn-rehab-unit-7a-7p-01371-2807',NULL,'RN Rehab Unit 7A 7P','United States-Florida-Port Charlotte','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>Renders professional nursing care on assigned geriatric and adult patients with covert, complex nursing care needs in accordance with nursing standards and treatment plans to provide for patients&#39; comfort and well-being.&nbsp; Demonstrates clinical expertise in the areas of assessment, planning, implementation and evaluation of patient care, while concurrently functioning as a resource person for other nursing and ancillary staff.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV><B><SPAN>PRINCIPLE ACTIVITIES</SPAN></B><B>:</B></DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Accountable for adhering to ORMC mission including meeting behavioral expectations (compassion, caring and confidentiality), providing excellence in health care delivery, supporting dignity of all persons (empowerment) and responsible stewardship of resources.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Performs a comprehensive physical assessment utilizing observation techniques and all available data including lab results, procedure/test results, physician findings and findings of other disciplines.&nbsp; Documents accurately and timely on Meditech.&nbsp; Is knowledgeable about MDS and other SNF specific documentation.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Establishes nursing plan of care, utilizes other disciplines in the establishment of plan and determines appropriate nursing interventions in accordance with patient needs and nursing standards.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Evaluates patient&#39;s progress and response to nursing interventions and modifies interventions and patient plan of care as appropriate.&nbsp; Conveys evaluation to the appropriate disciplines or physician and offers alternative modes of treatment.&nbsp; Utilizes his/her advanced level of preparation in all aspects of patient care.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provides guidance and direction to other members of the nursing team (i.e., LPN&#39;s, nurse aides and unit clerks) and coordinates the patient plan of care provided by all health care team members to ensure quality patient care.&nbsp; Serves as a resource and role model to other nursing staff in area of specialty.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Documents care given by recording assessments, nursing care, observations and patient&#39;s progress.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Is knowledgeable about TCU/Rehab specific procedures, admissions, discharges, use of</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; restraints, etc. Is familiar with rehabilitation and restorative procedures, i.e. range of motion,</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; active and passive.&nbsp; Splint and brace assistance, bed mobility, transfers, ambulation,&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; dressing and grooming, amputation and prosthesis care.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Instructs patients and family members regarding treatments, surgical procedures, nursing plans and home care to facilitate successful post-discharge care and patient understanding. Conveys, shares and documents advanced knowledge base.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Follows guidelines that maintain safety for oneself, patients, visitors and co-workers and if classified as a category I or II employee under OSHA regulations, adheres to OSHA standards by wearing personal protective equipment, following universal precautions and being knowledgeable about blood borne pathogens.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>10.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Performs other duties as may be assigned.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','Current state&nbsp;licensure as a Registered Nurse.&nbsp;',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01371-2807','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01371-2807',0,0,0,0,1311938524,1311938524),(405,9,5,'25558-3391','rn-surg-svcs-or-prn-25558-3391',NULL,'RN Surg Svcs OR (PRN)','United States-Florida-Largo','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>The RN Surg Svcs/OR provides nursing care in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Assesses, plans and evaluates the nursing care needs of the patient before, during and after a surgical procedure.</LI>\n<LI>Provides nursing care to the patient undergoing surgical procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Provides comfort and support for pre-operative patients.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in the care of patients receiving conscious sedation.</LI>\n<LI>Carries out physician orders.</LI>\n<LI>Administers prescribed medications, applies dressings, monitors vital signs.</LI>\n<LI>Assists physician during procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Maintains aseptic techniques and actively monitors situations which could lead to breaches in aseptic technique.</LI>\n<LI>Coordinates the operating room with respect to sterility, cleanliness, availability of functioning equipment and supplies.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Ensures the proper handling of specimens.</LI>\n<LI>Serves as the primary coordinator of all disciplines for well coordinated patient care.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN.</LI>\n<LI>Current American Heart Association Certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider.</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=25558-3391','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=25558-3391',0,0,0,0,1311938526,1311938526),(406,9,5,'00309-1976','rn-surg-svcs-or-prn-00309-1976',NULL,'RN Surg Svcs OR (PRN)','United States-Florida-Bradenton','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P>The Operating Room RN provides nursing care in accordance with established policies, procedures and protocols of the healthcare organization.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</P><UL><LI>Assesses, plans and evaluates the nursing care needs of the patient before, during and after a surgical procedure. </LI><LI>Provides nursing care to the patient undergoing surgical procedures. </LI><LI>Provides comfort and support for pre-operative patients. </LI><LI>Participates in the care of patients receiving conscious sedation. </LI><LI>Carries out physician orders. </LI><LI>Administers prescribed medications, applies dressings, monitors vital signs. </LI><LI>Assists physician during procedures. </LI><LI>Maintains aseptic techniques and actively monitors situations which could lead to breaches in aseptic technique. </LI><LI>Coordinates the operating room with respect to sterility, cleanliness, availability of functioning equipment and supplies.&nbsp; </LI><LI>Ensures the proper handling of specimens. </LI><LI>Serves as the primary coordinator of all disciplines for well coordinated patient care. </LI><LI>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp; </LI><LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care. </LI><LI>Orients and mentors new staff members. </LI><LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI></UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P><UL><LI>Current licensure as an RN. </LI><LI>Current certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider. </LI><LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing. </LI><LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills. </LI><LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment. </LI><LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs. </LI></UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-1976','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-1976',0,0,0,0,1311938531,1311938531),(407,9,5,'00311-3303','pharmacist-clinical-coordinator-hospital-experience-join-our-dynamic-pharmacy-team-00311-3303',NULL,'Pharmacist Clinical Coordinator Hospital Experience Join our Dynamic Pharmacy Team ','United States-Florida-Hudson','Pharmacy & Pharmacy Tech',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV>Experience our commitment to compassion and care at Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system. Our 290-bed facility boasts many awards and accolades, particularly for our nationally acclaimed Heart Institute. Our dedication to patients is reflected in the ongoing recognition of our Centers of Excellence, which include:&nbsp; Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Advanced Certification for Heart Failure * Chest Pain Center with PCI * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care. Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point is in the process of application for a Level II trauma designation.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Located on Florida&#39;s West Coast, our suburban location just 45 minutes from Tampa offers a friendly work environment, award winning staff and the opportunity to strengthen your career. Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals.&nbsp; EOE</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Pharmacy Clinical Coordinator duties include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Responsible for the safe, accurate and rational distributions of pharmaceutical agents to patients of all ages, and designated areas of the Hospital.</LI>\n<LI>Responsible for the supervision of the technical personnel, and ensures practice is in accordance with state/federal laws, regulatory agencies and Hospital/Department policies and procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Coordinates clinical pharmacy services.</LI>\n<LI>Maintains strong knowledge of hospital policies and government regulations and dispenses accordingly.</LI>\n<LI>Consults with physicians and nursing staff regarding patient reactions, errors and complaints.</LI>\n<LI>Determines and consults on possible drug interactions.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in Drug Utilization Review.</LI>\n<LI>Assists with quality improvement initiatives, inventory and ordering of pharmaceuticals.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Utilizes knowledge of age specific needs of patient in performance of duties and responsibilities.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of a college of Pharmacy accredited by the American Council on Pharmacy Education.</LI>\n<LI>BS or Pharm.D degree; Residency preferred; hospital/clinical experience required.</LI>\n<LI>State licensure as a Pharmacist.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11014/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-3303','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11014/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-3303',0,0,0,0,1311938533,1311938702),(408,9,5,'01385-2799','rn-wound-care-prn-4-hours-saturday-4-hours-sunday-and-miscellaneous-prn-01385-2799',NULL,'RN Wound Care PRN (4 hours Saturday 4 hours Sunday and miscellaneous PRN)','United States-Florida-St Petersburg','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>The Wound Care Registered Nurse performs the primary function of&nbsp; a RN in assessing, planning, implementing and evaluating the care of patients in the hospital setting.&nbsp;C<SPAN>ommunicates and collaborates closely with physicians, outpatient and inpatient nurses, Wound Care staff and other members of the health care team to provide consistent&nbsp;quality care for patients.&nbsp; Working with a high degree of autonomy, the RN accepts responsibility and accountability for assigned patients as a case manager to plan, implement and evaluate&nbsp;the care for wound care clients.&nbsp; The RN works within the framework of the Florida Nurse Practice Act and follows all hospital policies and procedures.&nbsp;</SPAN></DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>&nbsp;The candidate is responsible for meeting the established WHC Standards of nursing practice in the management of all assigned patients.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>&nbsp;Administers prescribed medications, changes dressings, cleans wounds, monitors vital signs.</LI>\n<LI>&nbsp;Instructs and educates patients and families.</LI>\n<LI>Assesses and coordinates patient&#39;s discharge planning needs with members of the healthcare team.</LI>\n<LI>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Qualifications:</SPAN></EM></STRONG></P>\n<UL CLASS=\"noindent\">\n<LI>\n<P>Certified and experienced wound care nurse that can handle making recommendations on wound care consults, and maintain quality care while initiating the Hospital Acquired Conditions (HAC) initiatives pertaining to decubitis ulcers.&nbsp;</P>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<P>Current certification as a CWOCN or WCS/WCC (Wound Care Specialist) desired.</P>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Graduate from an accredited school of nursing; BSN desired.</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>Current&nbsp;Florida Registered Nurse License.</LI>\n<LI>Previous Wound Care RN experience required.</SPAN></STRONG></LI>\n<LI>Case Management experience preferred.</LI>\n<LI>Current American Heart Association Healthcare Provider&nbsp;BLS certification.<BR/>\n</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01385-2799','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01385-2799',0,0,0,0,1311938535,1311938535),(409,9,5,'00144-933','rn-clinical-educator-prn-00144-933',NULL,'RN Clinical Educator PRN','United States-Florida-Largo','Nursing - Professional',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>Largo Medical Center is a 256- bed acute care hospital located in mid-Pinellas County on the West Coast of Florida near Clearwater.&nbsp; Largo Medical Center enjoys a superb reputation in the community, attributable in large measure to our high customer service to our patients and we are the only area hospital with private rooms for all patients.&nbsp; Additionally, we have been repeatedly ranked among the top 100 U.S. hospitals for overall care, and we&#8217;ve earned the top 100 U.S. designation specifically for our cardiovascular, orthopedic, stroke and intensive care services.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Features at our hospital include:</DIV>\n<UL TYPE=disc>\n<LI>Cardiovascular/Open Heart with 2 dedicated heart surgery suites\n </LI><LI>Comprehensive Cardiac Catheterization Services\n </LI><LI>Florida Knee and Ortho Pavilion (Elective Joint Surgery center)\n </LI><LI>State of the art surgery &amp; ambulatory care center\n </LI><LI>Florida Breast Institute\n </LI><LI>10 Multifunction Surgical Suites\n </LI><LI>4 Endoscopic Suites\n </LI><LI>16 private pre-op rooms\n </LI><LI>Spacious Emergency department with 29 Private ED Treatment rooms</LI></UL>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>We offer a generous benefit package, tuition reimbursement and many professional learning opportunities.&nbsp; Plus a lot of extra incentives that make life more rewarding.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The RN Clinical Educator is responsible for assessing, planning, implementing and evaluating the educational activities for hospital staff.&nbsp; We are looking for recent critical care experience especially in the areas of cardiac disease management, cardiac intervention and cardiac surgery. The tasks and responsibilities of this position include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Collaborates with hospital managers and staff to assess the learning needs and competency gaps.\n </LI><LI>Develops, implements and evaluates educational plans/programs.\n </LI><LI>Facilitates a variety of learning experiences using a range of instructional methods.\n </LI><LI>Demonstrates strong knowledge of healthcare standards and regulations in order to meet related training needs.\n </LI><LI>Participates in the organization\'s compliance with mandatory training requirements.\n </LI><LI>Utilizes methods, measurements and tools to evaluate achievement of learning goals.\n </LI><LI>Serves as a consultant for staff in areas of program development, clinical practice and professional development.\n </LI><LI>Participates in the coordination and continuity of orientation programs.\n </LI><LI>Serves as an active member of committees focused on such areas as safety, infection control and staff competency.\n </LI><LI>Demonstrates strong knowledge of standards and regulations related to staff development and patient education.\n </LI><LI>Researches and recommends the purchase of educational materials and equipment.\n </LI><LI>Coordinates and/or collaborates with external learning institutions as they utilize the hospital as a clinical teaching site.</LI></UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications Include:</P><UL><LI>Current licensure as an RN. </LI><LI>BSN required; Master\'s Degree in Nursing preferred but can be matriculating.&nbsp;</LI><LI>Minimum 2 years of clinical nursing experience. </LI><LI>Previous instruction experience required. </LI><LI>Competency in utilizing computer programs for developing instructional materials, tracking related data and communicating information. </LI><LI>BLS Healthcare Provider. </LI><LI>Able to speak, read and understand English fluently. </LI><LI>Excellent communicator with engaging and effective presentation abilities. </LI><LI>Requires critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision <UL><LI>Knowledge of standards and regulations related to staff development and patient education. </LI><LI>Researches and recommends the purchase of educational materials and equipment. </LI><LI>Coordinates and/or collaborates with external learning institutions as they utilize the hospital as a clinical teaching site.</LI></UL></LI></UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10141/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-933','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10141/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-933',0,0,0,0,1311938537,1311939079),(410,9,5,'00144-4127','fans-assistant-prn-00144-4127',NULL,'FANS Assistant (PRN)','United States-Florida-Largo','Environmental Services',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P>The Food and Nutrition Services Worker performs a variety of tasks that facilitate the provision of food services and nutrition support to patients, employees and visitors. These duties include:</P><UL><LI>Performs routine duties related to preparation and serving of food. </LI><LI>Prepares food for cooking by washing, peeling, shredding, slicing, and mixing various food items. </LI><LI>Operates dishwasher or assists with washing/sterilizing dishes, glassware, silverware, utensils, pots, pans, etc. </LI><LI>Cleans kitchen work areas, collects and disposes of garbage. </LI><LI>May assist with food stocking. </LI><LI>Serves food in&nbsp; cafeteria for visitors and staff and in patients room following dietary, sanitary and safety guidelines.&nbsp; </LI><LI>Clears patients\' dirty trays and works in dish room when needed. </LI><LI>Works on patient tray assembly line following menu directives for determining food items for each tray. </LI><LI>Delivers food trays to patient areas. </LI><LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI></UL>','<P>Job qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>High school diploma or GED preferred\n </LI><LI>6 months food service experience preferred, previous&nbsp; experience in hospital food services preferred.</LI></UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-4127','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-4127',0,0,0,0,1311938539,1311938539),(411,9,5,'00367-1125','cook-prn-00367-1125',NULL,'Cook (PRN)','United States-Florida-St Petersburg','Environmental Services',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV XMLNS=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">The Cook&nbsp;performs a variety of tasks that facilitate the provision of food services and nutrition support to patients, employees and visitors.&nbsp; These duties include:</DIV><UL><LI>Prepares, seasons, and cooks food for patients, staff, visitors, and special functions. </LI><LI>Reviews menus to determine types and quantities of food. </LI><LI>Prepares quality food in sufficient quantities to cover all service requirements. </LI><LI>Coordinates timing of preparation in order to meet service schedules for patients, staff, visitors and catering services. </LI><LI>Adheres to standardization of recipes and portion control to prevent food waste and control cost. </LI><LI>Provides care and sanitation of equipment in production area. </LI><LI>Adheres to sanitation and safety standards&nbsp;(HACCP) </LI><LI>Participates in the process of ordering supplies. </LI><LI>Gives directions to personnel who assist in food preparation. </LI><LI><DIV ALIGN=left>Utilizes knowledge of age specific needs of patient in performance of duties and responsibilities.</DIV></LI><LI><DIV ALIGN=left>Orients and mentors new staff members.</DIV></LI></UL>','<DIV XMLNS=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Job qualifications include:</DIV><UL or more in-depth Certification as Food Service Manager preferred. </LI><LI><DIV ALIGN=left>Ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment. </DIV></LI><LI><DIV ALIGN=left>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.&nbsp; </DIV></LI><LI><DIV ALIGN=left>Ability to deal with stressful situations and to stand for long periods of time</DIV></LI></UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00367-1125','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00367-1125',0,0,0,0,1311938541,1311938541),(412,9,5,'01371-2742','clinical-pharmacist-part-time-evenings-weekends-01371-2742',NULL,'Clinical Pharmacist Part time Evenings Weekends','United States-Florida-Port Charlotte','Pharmacy & Pharmacy Tech',NULL,'Part-time',NULL,'<DIV>Following physicians&#39; orders, the Clinical&nbsp;Pharmacist position tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Maintains strong knowledge of hospital policies and government regulations and dispenses accordingly.</LI>\n<LI>Consults with physicians and nursing staff regarding patient reactions, errors and complaints.</LI>\n<LI>Determines and consults on possible drug interactions.</LI>\n<LI>Assists in the supervision and training of pharmacy technician personnel.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in Drug Utilization Review.</LI>\n<LI>Assists with quality improvement initiatives, inventory and ordering of pharmaceuticals.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Utilizes knowledge of age specific needs of patient in performance of duties and responsibilities.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>The staff at Fawcett Memorial Hospital continually meets the high standards required to care for the unique needs of our patients. As part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system, our 238-bed facility serves the Port Charlotte area and is a trusted provider of quality care and compassion with several accredited Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Joint Care * Chest Pain Center * Spine Care Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV>Located less than 30 minutes from southwest Florida&#39;s most famous beaches, we employ advanced technologies, career stability and the support you need to grow. Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>.&nbsp; EOE</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of a college of Pharmacy accredited by the American Council on Pharmacy Education.</LI>\n<LI>BS or Pharm.D degree.</LI>\n<LI>State licensure as a Pharmacist.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01371-2742','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01371-2742',0,0,0,0,1311938545,1311938545),(413,9,5,'00327-2538','lpn-snu-prn-00327-2538',NULL,'LPN SNU (PRN)','United States-Florida-Sanford','Nursing Support',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV><STRONG>POSITION SUMMARY:</STRONG></DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Responsible for patient care under direct supervision of a Registered Nurse&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>','<DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV><STRONG>LICENSURE/CERTIFICATION:</STRONG></DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current LPN Florida License</LI>\n<LI>Current BLS certification thru American Heart Association.</LI>\n</UL>\n</DIV>\n</DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-2538','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-2538',0,0,0,0,1311938547,1311938547),(414,9,5,'01371-2778','director-medical-and-oncology-registered-nurse-01371-2778',NULL,'Director Medical and Oncology Registered Nurse','United States-Florida-Port Charlotte','Nursing Mgmt & Admin',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV><SPAN><STRONG>Bring&nbsp;your vision for the future and strong customer service focus to the leadership of our medical and oncology units totaling 63 beds.&nbsp; Guide your units in shared governance development as we journey toward Magnet status.&nbsp; Enhance your oncology experience in our ACOS accredited oncology unit. At Fawcett Memorial , you will play an</STRONG> <STRONG>active role&nbsp; in developing&nbsp; patient satisfaction and serving our community.&nbsp; You will be part of a progressive division organization that values innovation and constant improvement.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</STRONG>&nbsp;</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The Nursing Director demonstrates twenty-four hour responsibility and accountability for nursing practice, and quality of care and services within assigned departments. Ensures assessment and care is appropriate and patient specific and documented in a timely, accurate and complete manner.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West Florida we are on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients; their families and the communities we serve.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Rich Moore</DIV>\n<DIV>Lead Nurse Recruiter</DIV>\n<DIV><A HREF=\"mailto:richard.moore2@hcahealthcare.com\">richard.moore2@hcahealthcare.com</A></DIV>\n<DIV>Referrals are always appreciated.</DIV>','<P>BSN required;&nbsp;</P>\n<P>MS preferred</P>\n<P>5 years Director experience in an acute care hospital required</P>\n<P>Medical/Surgical&nbsp;experience required &nbsp;</P>\n<P>Oncology experience preferred</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01371-2778','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01371-2778',0,0,0,0,1311938549,1311939662),(415,9,5,'00327-2452','case-manager-per-diem-prn-00327-2452',NULL,'Case Manager Per Diem PRN','United States-Florida-Sanford','Case Management',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>As part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system, Central Florida Regional Hospital enhances patient care by attracting the most qualified healthcare professionals in the region. Our award-winning 226-bed acute care facility is home to the only open heart program in the county. We offer a commitment to advanced technologies and an opportunity to work with a highly skilled team of professionals. Our recognized Centers of Excellence include:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center with PCI * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Diabetes Education Program (ADA)</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Located along picturesque Lake Monroe in Sanford, Florida, our team is devoted to caring.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West and Central Florida&#39;s 15 hospitals we&#39;re not just caregivers, we&#39;re devoted to caring. Located throughout Tampa, St. Petersburg, Sarasota and the greater Orlando area, we&#39;re on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients. As an integral part of the nation&#39;s largest healthcare system with more than 15,000 healthcare professionals on our team, we foster an environment where you will be supported, valued and encouraged to grow.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to www.MoreCareerChoices.com.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Current licensure as an RN</LI>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited school of professional nursing.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Bachelor&#39;s of Science in Nursing preferred.</LI>\n<LI>CCM preferred&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Minimum&nbsp;3 years of clinical nursing experience.</LI>\n<LI>Knowledge of CMS guidelines and experience working with payor specific guidelines and contractual rules preferred.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision meeting firm deadlines.</LI>\n<LI>Assertive and persuasive communication skills, action oriented.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11016/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-2452','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11016/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00327-2452',0,0,0,0,1311938550,1311939820),(416,9,5,'00311-1842','certified-nursing-asst-spine-center-prn-as-needed-schedule-00311-1842',NULL,'Certified Nursing Asst Spine Center (PRN) As Needed Schedule','United States-Florida-Hudson','Nursing Support',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<P>Working under the supervision of a nurse, the&nbsp;Certified Nursing Assistant performs various patient care activities necessary in caring for the personal needs and comfort of patients.&nbsp; The position&#39;s tasks and responsibilities include:</SPAN></P>\n<UL>\n<LI><SPAN>Bathes, dresses/undresses patients assist with personal hygiene.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Serves and collects food trays.&nbsp; Assists with patient feeding.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Transports, positions&nbsp; and drapes patients for exams and treatments.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Assists patients in ambulating.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Takes and records vital signs, weights and I &amp; O.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Performs non sterile dressing changes.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Passes and collects bed pans.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Changes bed linens.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Provides encouragement, support and comfort to patients and family members.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Monitors, records and communicates patient condition as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Provides age and culturally appropriate care.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Orients and mentors new staff members.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</SPAN></LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications Include:</SPAN></P>\n<UL>\n<LI><SPAN>High School Graduate or equivalent <STRONG>required</STRONG>.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Current <STRONG>American Heart Association</STRONG> certification as a BLS Healthcare Provider <STRONG>required</STRONG>.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Current <STRONG>Florida</STRONG> Certification as a Nurse Assistant <STRONG>required</STRONG>.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Working knowledge of medical terminology.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Ability to quickly make decisions to report patient condition with minimal supervision.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI><SPAN>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 pounds.</SPAN></LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-1842','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/10142/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-1842',0,0,0,0,1311938552,1311938552),(418,9,9,'00144-5100','lead-medical-technologist-ft-days-00144-5100',NULL,'Lead Medical Technologist FT Days','United States-Florida-Largo','Laboratory',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<P>Expand your career as a Lead Medical Technologist in the Clinical Lab at Largo Medical Center.&nbsp; Largo Medical Center the Lead Medical Technologist on the&nbsp;day shift assists the Supervisors in the daily efficient operation in any one area of the Clinical Laboratory as assigned (Chemistry, Hematology, Blood Bank, Microbiology, Point of Care) and performs clinical testing as a Medical Technologist in assigned areas.</P>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>In addition the Lead Technologist&nbsp; performs laboratory testing in one or more sections of the laboratory that assists with the diagnosis of patients.&nbsp; The tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>\n<P>Processes specimens, prepares reagents, performs testing procedures; reports and interprets test results.</P>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<P>Performs quality control testing, instrument maintenance and troubleshooting.</P>\n</LI>\n<LI>Verifies analytic accuracy, precision, sensitivity and references ranges for test methods.</LI>\n<LI>Works with Physician to analyze results and conduct more difficult, non-routine tests.</LI>\n<LI>Serves as a consultant to medical laboratory technicians and phlebotomists as needed.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Nationally recognized certification as a medical technologist or equivalent. ASCP,AMT</LI>\n<LI>Florida State licensure&nbsp;required in all 5 areas of the lab.</LI>\n<LI>Associate&#39;s degree in medical technology with formal medical technology training or qualification under CLIA &#39;88 Regulations.&nbsp; Bachelor&#39;s Degree is preferred.</LI>\n<LI>Minimum&nbsp;2 to 3&nbsp;years of experience as a Medical Technologist in a hospital laboratory.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Strong team work and collaboration abilities.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, walking, lifting, grasping and repetitive motion. Lifting up to 50 pounds.&nbsp; Occasional&nbsp;stooping, squatting, pushing, pulling, climbing, overhead lifting. .</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11016/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-5100','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11016/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00144-5100',0,0,0,0,1311938560,1311939683),(452,9,9,'00643-2945','sepsis-coordinator-rn-licensure-required-icu-experience-preferred-00643-2945',NULL,'Sepsis Coordinator RN Licensure Required ICU experience preferred','United States-Florida-Brooksville','Quality Risk & Safety',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV>Oak Hill Hospital, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system, is a 214-acute care hospital in the community of Brooksville. Our experienced healthcare team is dedicated to diagnosing and treating patients faster than any hospital in the county. We are the area&#39;s second largest private employer and offer the only comprehensive heart program in Hernando County. We go out of our way for our patients by offering an expanded ED and these Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center with PCI * Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Orthopedics &amp; Spine Care Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Located near the family-friendly town of Brooksville, Oak Hill Hospital is situated on Florida&#39;s Nature Coast, which offers fishing, boating, bird watching and hiking. Join us and see why we&#39;re excited to be in one of Florida&#39;s fastest growing counties.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV><STRONG>The RN Sepsis Coordinator is responsible for the following:</STRONG></DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Facilitates the development, implementation and ongoing adherence of sepsis program protocols and therapies.&nbsp; Ensures the protocols and therapies become the standard of care followed within the facility</LI>\n<LI>Collaborates with medical and hospital staff to provide multidisciplinary care to septic patients.&nbsp;&nbsp; Provides education and clinical expertise to care team, patients, and families</LI>\n<LI>Identifies and integrates patient learning needs, abilities and readiness into the Plan of Care.&nbsp; Works in collaboration with the nursing team to develop and implement individualized teaching plans for patients and families.</LI>\n<LI>Collects and analyzes sepsis program patient data to assist with documentation, coding, clinical care, and improved outcomes.</LI>\n<LI>Recognizes and reports signs and symptoms of abuse and neglect to physician(s) and Department Director and/or appropriate agency</LI>\n<LI>Participates in rounding and proactively responds to patient needs to improve patient outcomes and positively impact overall patient experience.</LI>\n<LI>Contributes to a culture of patient centered care by ensuring a quiet healing environment.</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV ID=\"requisitionDescriptionInterface.d71677e319.row1\" TITLE=\"\">&nbsp;</DIV>','<STRONG><SPAN>Qualifications</SPAN></STRONG>&nbsp;\n\n<UL>\n<LI>Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Nursing or a Master&#39;s Degree in Nursing preferred</LI>\n<LI><STRONG>Three to five years of ICU experience with a solid grasp of hemodynamics</STRONG></LI>\n<LI>Current Florida RN License</LI>\n<LI>Current <B>BLS</B> (Basic Life Support)</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking, service excellence and good interpersonal communication skills, ability to read/comprehend written instructions, ability to follow verbal instructions, PC skills, ability to utilize hemodynamic equipment</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-2945','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00643-2945',0,0,0,0,1311938641,1311939571),(508,9,8,'01147-1284','registered-clinical-dietitian-prn-01147-1284',NULL,'Registered Clinical Dietitian (PRN)','United States-Florida-Sarasota','Clincal Techs - CV Cath Lab Surg Vasc & Central Sterile',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV>For more than 40 years, Doctors Hospital of Sarasota has met the growing and changing healthcare needs of the communities it serves. Our full-service, 168-bed hospital extends acute and general care in all major specialties, while offering an environment that combines a dedicated, friendly staff with leading-edge technology.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Recently named a Top 40 Orthopedic &amp; Spine Program highlights our facility&#39;s commitment to superior outcomes that include these Centers of Excellence:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Chest Pain Center * Spine Care Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>As part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system, you will experience the latest technology, enthusiastic coworkers and great benefits all in an upscale</DIV>\n<DIV>resort-like community.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV><STRONG>PRN Schedule: Hours may vary and are scheduled on an as needed basis. (WEEKDAY SHIFT AVAILABLE)</STRONG></DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The <STRONG>Clinical Dietitian</STRONG>&nbsp;leads the processes in place to ensure that the patients&#39; nutritional needs are met.&nbsp; Job tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Conducts and implements comprehensive nutritional assessments for patients</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>Assesses, plans, writes and evaluates patient diets.</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Plans menus in accordance with patient dietary requirements and general dietetic standards and regulations.</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>Instructs and counsels patients on dietary restrictions/recommendations.</LI>\n<LI>Participates in multidisciplinary teams providing input regarding treatment&nbsp;plans.</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Directs and supervises personnel in the process of planning, preparing, and serving food to patients.</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>Maintains records of patient reaction to prescribed diets.</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Monitors, records and communicates as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Utilizes knowledge of age specific needs of patient in performance of duties and responsibilities.</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Orients and mentors new staff members.</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<DIV>Job qualifications include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Bachelors Degree in Dietetics or Nutrition required.</LI>\n<LI>American Dietetic Association Registration strongly preferred (R.D.)</LI>\n<LI>Must have current state licensure as a Dietitian (L.D.)</LI>\n<LI>Previous experience as a hospital dietitian preferred.</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</DIV>\n</LI>\n<LI>\n<DIV>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs</DIV>\n</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West and Central Florida&#39;s 15 hospitals we&#39;re not just caregivers, we&#39;re devoted to caring. Located throughout Tampa, St. Petersburg, Sarasota and the greater Orlando area, we&#39;re on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients. As an integral part of the nation&#39;s largest healthcare system with more than 15,000 healthcare professionals on our team, we foster an environment where you will be supported, valued and encouraged to grow.</DI