al</STRONG> located on the Gulf Coast in beautiful Port Charlotte, Florida, has an opportunity for a seasoned healthcare Facilities Management Director.&nbsp; As the director, you will be a vital part of the success of the hospital&#39;s quality, safety and accreditation programs.&nbsp;&nbsp;The qualified candidate will manage the Plant Operations, Biomedical, and&nbsp;Safety departments and provide oversight and leadership for the support services related to facility and infrastructure utilities of the Hospital&#39;s facilities, grounds and equipment.&nbsp;Job duties also include supervision of the Safety, Transport, Emergency management&nbsp;and Environment of Care programs. The director will represent the hospital and is instrumental in ensuring facility regulatory compliance with all state and federal agencies.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>This is your opportunity to become a&nbsp; part of HCA Healthcare, the nation&#39;s largest healthcare system .HCA fosters an environment where you will be supported, valued and encouraged to grow. Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals.&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>','<UL>\n<LI>Bachelor&#39;s Degree required</LI>\n<LI>5&nbsp;years of healthcare management experience.</LI>\n<LI>Certified Healthcare Engineer (CHE) desirable</LI>\n<LI>Current Florida License with Florida Board of Professional Engineers preferred.</LI>\n<LI>Knowledge of state &amp; federal hazardous and biological waste regulations</LI>\n<LI>Knowledge of OSHA &amp; JCAHO regulations</LI>\n<LI>Organizational, customer relations, analytical skills</LI>\n</UL>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11016/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01371-2765','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11016/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01371-2765',0,0,0,0,1311939289,1311939673),(699,9,11,'00311-3295','or-tech-certified-7pm-7am-701-00311-3295',NULL,'OR Tech Certified 7pm 7am 701','United States-Florida-Hudson','Nursing Support',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>REGIONAL MEDICAL CENTER BAYONET POINT</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Experience our commitment to compassion and care at Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system. Our 290-bed facility boasts many awards and accolades, particularly for our nationally acclaimed Heart Institute. Our dedication to patients is reflected in the ongoing recognition of our Centers of Excellence, which include:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Advanced Certification for Heart Failure * Chest Pain Center with PCI * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Located on Florida&#39;s West Coast, our suburban location just 45 minutes from Tampa offers a friendly work environment, award winning staff and the opportunity to strengthen your career.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point is in the process of application for a Level II trauma designation.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West and Central Florida&#39;s 15 hospitals we&#39;re not just caregivers, we&#39;re devoted to caring. Located throughout Tampa, St. Petersburg, Sarasota and the greater Orlando area, we&#39;re on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients. As an integral part of the nation&#39;s largest healthcare system with more than 15,000 healthcare professionals on our team, we foster an environment where you will be supported, valued and encouraged to grow.</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The Operating Room Technician assists in nursing care and preparation of surgical patient by performance of routine and delegated duties, according to standards and policies of the center.&nbsp; Is responsible for assisting the surgeon, helping in the central sterile processing department, restocking and changing over rooms between procedures.&nbsp; Performs housekeeping duties as necessary and assists in maintenance of all supplies.&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>Assists with and delivers safe, effective intra-operative nursing care until patient is transferred from the operating room suite. &nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensures patient comfort and safety measures are maintained.</DIV>\n<DIV>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Anticipates special needs, equipment and supplies for the patient relative to an accurate physical assessment of the patient by a nurse.</DIV>\n<DIV>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assists in preparing the operative suite for surgery checking supplies, equipment, and instrumentation.</DIV>\n<DIV>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assists in preparing the operative room between cases, as necessary.</DIV>\n<DIV>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assists in assuring the availability of adequate supplies and instruments for posted cases and assists in opening room in a sterile environment.</DIV>\n<DIV>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Utilizes surgeon preference cards to check with each case and updates as needed.</DIV>\n<DIV>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assists the surgeon during a surgical procedure with a high degree of efficiency, anticipating physician and patient needs during the case.</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Interacts with patients, fellow employees, physicians, and other customers in a manner which encourages quality patient care, harmonious working relationships, positive customer relations, and which enhances the image and reputation of the center.</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assist in orienting new staff members to the OR suites and central processing decontam and sterile areas.</DIV>\n<DIV>2.&nbsp;&nbsp; Shares knowledge with co-workers through open communication.</DIV>\n<DIV>3.&nbsp;&nbsp; Follows chain of command regarding intra or interdepartmental issues.</DIV>\n<DIV>4.&nbsp;&nbsp; Evaluates suggestions objectively, accepts constructive criticism, and seeks guidance when needed.</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>Supports the center&#39;s mission by dependability in attendance, punctuality, the timely completion of care and other assignments, resource and information management, and attention to principles of quality service.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Maintains and improves skills and knowledge appropriate for position, personal growth, and for enhancement of patient care.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Assists in daily maintenance of the department, in completing monthly work assignment sheet, restocking, pull cases for the next day, and maintaining equipment in good working order.&nbsp; Utilizes non-chargeable items in a cost-effective manner.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Understands and effectively implements &quot;Best Practices, Risk Management, and Quality Improvement Programs.</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Supports and adheres to HCA Code of Conduct, related Ethics and Compliance policies and HIPAA requirements.</DIV>\n</DIV>','<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>Job Requirements include:</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>Florida OR Tech Certification required.</P>\n<P>American Heart&nbsp;BLS Certification required</P>\n<P>2 year OR Tech experience</P>\n<P>Excellent communication skills</P>\n<P>High School Diploma/GED</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11016/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-3295','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11016/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-3295',0,0,0,0,1311939361,1311939745),(713,9,11,'00311-3283','cardiovascular-tech-ii-days-746-00311-3283',NULL,'Cardiovascular Tech II Days 746','United States-Florida-Hudson','Clincal Techs - CV Cath Lab Surg Vasc & Central Sterile',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>REGIONAL MEDICAL CENTER BAYONET POINT</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Experience our commitment to compassion and care at Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system. Our 290-bed facility boasts many awards and accolades, particularly for our nationally acclaimed Heart Institute. Our dedication to patients is reflected in the ongoing recognition of our Centers of Excellence, which include:</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Heart &amp; Vascular Institute * Advanced Certification for Heart Failure * Chest Pain Center with PCI * Advanced Primary Stroke Center * Cancer Care</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Located on Florida\'s West Coast, our suburban location just 45 minutes from Tampa offers a friendly work environment, award winning staff and the opportunity to strengthen your career.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Regional Medical Center Bayonet Point is in the process of application for a Level II trauma designation.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV>At HCA West and Central Florida\'s 15 hospitals we\'re not just caregivers, we\'re devoted to caring. Located throughout Tampa, St. Petersburg, Sarasota and the greater Orlando area, we\'re on a journey to reach new heights in service excellence for our patients. As an integral part of the nation\'s largest healthcare system with more than 15,000 healthcare professionals on our team, we foster an environment where you will be supported, valued and encouraged to grow.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>The Cath Lab Radiologic Tech collaborates with physicians, nurses, and other clinical disciplines in providing care to patients undergoing procedures in the Cardiac Catherization Lab.&nbsp; The position&#39;s tasks and responsibilities include:<BR/>\n&nbsp;Competently operates radiologic equipment including ability to trouble shoot in order to solve equipment related problems.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Operates hemodynamic monitoring computer during procedures.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Performs decentralized testing, according to protocol.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Assists the R.N. in assessing, planning, implementing, and evaluating the care of the Cath Lab patient.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Coordinates and organizes supplies, equipment and instruments needed for Cath Lab procedures.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Provides assistance to physicians performing Cath Lab procedures.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Participates in activities to plan, measure, assess, and improve the quality of patient care.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Monitors, records and communicates as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;<BR/>\n&nbsp;Utilizes knowledge of age specific needs of patient in performance of duties and responsibilities.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Orients and mentors new staff members.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Practices radiation protection techniques to minimize radiation to patient and staff.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Assists with transporting patients.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Orients and mentors staff.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</DIV>','<BR/>\nRequired Job Qualifications include:<BR/>\n&nbsp;Graduate of an accredited program for Radiographers.<BR/>\n&nbsp;RCIS Certification<BR/>\n&nbsp;Current state licensure.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Working knowledge of computerized hemodynamic monitoring.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Minimum&nbsp;3 years experience as a Radiology Tech<BR/>\n&nbsp;Previous 2 years experience in a Cath Lab setting preferred.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Current American Heart Association Certification in BLS, ACLS<BR/>\n&nbsp;Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.<BR/>\n&nbsp;Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.&nbsp;<BR/>\n&nbsp;Ability to deal with stressful situations and to stand for long periods of time',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11016/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-3283','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11016/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00311-3283',0,0,0,0,1311939408,1311939780),(732,9,6,'00642-1479','reg-pharm-tech-ii-32-hrs-week-mixed-shifts-weekends-rotate-hospital-experience-required-00642-1479',NULL,'Reg Pharm Tech II 32 hrs week Mixed Shifts weekends rotate Hospital Experience Required','United States-Florida-Sun City Center','Pharmacy & Pharmacy Tech',NULL,'Full-time',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV>Interviews for this position will not be conducted until August 2011</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>* Salary ranges from $10.72 to $15.00 per hour based on experience</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Following physicians&#39; orders, the Registered Pharmacy Tech dispenses medications and other pharmaceuticals.&nbsp; Position tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Maintains strong knowledge of hospital policies and government regulations and dispenses accordingly.</LI>\n<LI>Consults with physicians and nursing staff regarding patient reactions, errors and complaints.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Assists with quality improvement initiatives, inventory and ordering of pharmaceuticals.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>\n<DIV>Help deliver superior service to the patients at South Bay Hospital, part of the HCA West and Central Florida hospital system. Our team strives to provide effective and efficient care in our 112-bed hospital, which will soon be joined by an all-new medical complex. With new communities breaking ground each year, this is an ideal location to experience our commitment to your career and our community.&nbsp; We support our talented staff with advanced technologies throughout our hospital and Centers of Excellence including:</DIV>\n<DIV>* Chest Pain Center * Advanced Primary Stroke Center</DIV>\n<DIV>Make excellence your goal by joining our family of hospitals. To learn more and to apply, go to <A HREF=\"http://www.morecareerchoices.com/\">www.MoreCareerChoices.com</A>.&nbsp; EOE</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n</DIV>','<DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>Required Job Qualifications include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>State of Florida Registration as a Pharmacy Tech</LI>\n<LI>National certification as a Pharmacy Tech (CPhT) preferred.</LI>\n<LI>Previous pharmacy tech experience in a hospital preferred.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.</LI>\n</UL>\n</DIV>\n</DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00642-1479','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00642-1479',0,0,0,0,1311939465,1311939465),(734,9,6,'01323-2973','prn-echo-vascular-rvt-required-2500-per-hour-01323-2973',NULL,'PRN Echo Vascular RVT Required $25.00 per hour','United States-Florida-Kissimmee','Clincal Techs - CV Cath Lab Surg Vasc & Central Sterile',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV ID=\"col1\">\n<H1>Central Florida Cardiac &amp; Vascular Institute at Osceola Regional Hospital</H1>\n<P>Your heart. It serves your entire body, and its health is critical to your well-being. So when you need treatment, you need skilled professionals you can trust.</P>\n<P>The Central Florida Cardiac &amp; Vascular Institute is a pioneering facility that is staffed by a highly trained medical team and equipped with state-of-the-art technology. We are the only full-service cardiovascular hospital in the region, offering you comprehensive care when you need it most.</P>\n<P>As a specialized service of Osceola Regional Medical Center, we provide superior cardiovascular assessment, care, and education for the community we serve.</P>\n<H2>Our Mission</H2>\n<P>As part of the Osceola Regional Medical Center, the Central Florida Cardiac &amp; Vascular Institute will provide high-quality, cost-effective, and innovative care to the acutely and critically ill patient, exceeding the expectations of our customers and community.</P>\n<H2>Accomplishments and Expertise</H2>\n<P>Central Florida Cardiac &amp; Vascular Institute is a full-service, cardiac and vascular care facility. Our talented medical team is dedicated to diagnosing, treating and preventing cardiovascular disease.</P>\n<P>website</A>.</P>\n<P><STRONG>Blue Distinction Center for Cardiac Care:</STRONG> By our having this distinction, the BlueCross BlueShield Association recognizes that we have demonstrated our commitment to quality care and have produced better overall outcomes for cardiac patients. This honor means that we have met stringent clinical criteria, developed in collaboration with expert physicians and medical organizations, including the American College of Cardiology and the Society of Thoracic Surgeons.</P>\n<P><STRONG>Primary Stroke Center:</STRONG> We are the only accredited Advanced Primary Stroke Center in Osceola County, as accredited by the Joint Commission.</P>\n<P><STRONG>State-of-the-Art Electrophysiology (EP) Laboratory:</STRONG> Our EP lab is the only one of its kind in Osceola County, so we bring comprehensive electrophysiology services close to our patients-when and where they need it.</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n</DIV>\nJob tasks and responsibilities include:</DIV>\n<UL>\n<LI>Performs Echo and Vascular studies on cardiac patients.</LI>\n<LI>Determines and documents the presence, location and severity or absence of cardiac disease.</LI>\n<LI>Provides a quantitative comparison for evaluation of the stability, improvement, and deterioration of cardiac disease.</LI>\n<LI>Helps determine the need for other more complicated invasive procedures.</LI>\n<LI>Communicates results to physicians and responds to questions and concerns.</LI>\n<LI>Monitors, records and communicates as appropriate utilizing computerized documentation systems.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Utilizes knowledge of age specific needs of patient in performance of duties and responsibilities.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors new staff members.</LI>\n<LI>Assists with transporting patients.</LI>\n<LI>Orients and mentors staff.</LI>\n<LI>Follows Standard Precautions using personal protective equipment as required.</LI>\n</UL>','<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">Job qualifications and requirements include:</SPAN></P>\n<P CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</SPAN></P>\n<UL>\n<LI CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">Graduate of a program in Echocardiography approved by the Council on Medical Education of the American Medical Association or documented equivalent education, experience and training.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">Current RCT license</SPAN></LI>\n<LI CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">Current RVT Required</SPAN></LI>\n<LI CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">Previous experience performing echocardiography procedures preferred.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">Current Certification in Basic Life Support</SPAN> through the American Heart Association.</LI>\n<LI CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</SPAN></LI>\n<LI CLASS=\"MsoNormal\">Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.&nbsp;</SPAN></LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-2973','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01323-2973',0,0,0,0,1311939470,1311939470),(738,9,6,'00309-1849','ultrasound-rvt-ardms-required-prn-for-call-2675-hourly-00309-1849',NULL,'Ultrasound RVT ARDMS Required (PRN for call) $26.75 hourly','United States-Florida-Bradenton','Imaging',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>*MUST LIVE WITHIN A 30 MINUTE RADIUS FOR CALL REQUIREMENTS.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>Our PRN Ultrasound Techs must&nbsp;have the following experience in order to be considered for a PRN On-Call position. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;General and Vascular experience is required. &nbsp;</DIV>','<P>Required Job Qualifications include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Graduate of an accredited program for Radiographers or Ultrasonographers.</LI>\n<LI>Current RDMS or must be registry eligible and registered within one year of eligibility.&nbsp;</LI>\n<LI>Current state licensure or permit to practice medical imagining.</LI>\n<LI>Current Certification in Basic Life Support.</LI>\n<LI>Minimum two years working as an Imaging Tech.</LI>\n<LI>Customer service abilities including effective listening skills.</LI>\n<LI>Critical thinking skills, decisive judgment and the ability to work with minimal supervision in a fast paced environment.</LI>\n<LI>Ability to perform work that requires frequent standing, bending, reaching, squatting, kneeling, moving, lifting of patients and/or equipment up to 50 lbs.</LI>\n</UL>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-1849','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=00309-1849',0,0,0,0,1311939480,1311939480),(739,9,6,'01384-5003','electrophysiology-tech-prn-01384-5003',NULL,'Electrophysiology Tech (PRN)','United States-Florida-Brandon','Clincal Techs - CV Cath Lab Surg Vasc & Central Sterile',NULL,'Per Diem/PRN',NULL,'<DIV>\n<DIV>\n<DIV>Brandon Regional Hospital is committed to providing our patients and their families with compassionate care. For more than 30 years our busy, 407-bed acute care facility has been dedicated to quality and devoted to our community. We have been named a Top 100 Hospital in America five times, and our Intensive Care Unit has been named a Top 100 ICU. Join our friendly community hospital with its close-knit staff of caring professionals located just south of Tampa and discover how we care.</DIV>\n</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<DIV><I><SPAN>POSITION SUMMARY</SPAN></I>:&nbsp; Assists physicians in diagnosing and treating cardiac diseases in the Cath/Electrophysiology labs, specializing in EP devices and ablations. Promotes awareness to patients, peers, and the community.&nbsp; Responsible for the operation of physiologic and radiographic equipment while working in an invasive procedure area. Function in the following roles: scrub, circulate, and record. Proactively collaborates with all disciplines for well-coordinated care. Active participation in department and organizational performance improvement activities in accordance with hospital, JCAHO, and regulatory standards.</DIV>\n</DIV>','<DIV><SPAN>Required:</SPAN></SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV><SPAN>&nbsp;</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV><SPAN>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Two years of full-time, in the field experience (teaching, researching, providing, supervising or managing patient care and diagnosis in cardiovascular medicine).</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV>or</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV><SPAN>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; An associates degree or equivalent college hours in health, science, natural science, nursing, engineering or any primary science and one year of full-time, in the field experience (teaching, researching, providing, supervising or managing patient care and diagnosis in cardiovascular medicine).&nbsp;</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV>and</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV><SPAN>Certified in Advanced Cardiac Life Support (ACLS).</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV><SPAN>R-CIS or HRS Certification required</SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV><SPAN>&nbsp;CPR through the American Heart Association</SPAN></DIV>',0,0,'https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-5003','https://hca.taleo.net/careersection/11009/jobdetail.ftl?lang=en&job=01384-5003',0,0,0,0,1311939483,1311939483),(747,9,6,'01384-4938a','mammography-tech-prn-2575-hourly-01384-4938a',NULL,'Mammography Tech (PRN) $25.75 hourly','United Stat